#0000FF\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</p>\r\n'),
(7, '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">\r\n<div>With reference to the advertisement for various positions (Junior Executive Officer to Assistant Level) published in Nagarik Daily Newspaper on May 9, 2018 and successful completion of Interview, following candidates have been selected.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe below selected candidates are advised to visit NCC Bank, Human Resource Department, Bagbazar on the following mentioned dates along with their Original and Xerox copies of their Mark sheets including Character Certificates and Equivalence Certificates (in case if Degrees are acquired from Foreign Universities), Citizenship and 5 copies Passport Size Photograph.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Congratulation to all the successful candidates.</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Position </strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Visit Date</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Time</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Junior Executive Officer (JEO)</td>\r\n			<td>5-Jul-18</td>\r\n			<td><strong>10.00 am : JEO &ndash; All</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>S. No.</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Position</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>&nbsp;Successful Candidates</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Job Location</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"5\" style=\"vertical-align:middle\"><strong>Junior Executive Officer</strong></td>\r\n			<td>Krishna Ratna Manandhar</td>\r\n			<td>Mahabu Gaupalika-Dailekh</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2</td>\r\n			<td>Padam Pandey</td>\r\n			<td>Hupsekot Gaupalika-Nawalparasi East</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>3</td>\r\n			<td>Subash Bikram Karki</td>\r\n			<td>Chauri Deurali Gaupalika-Kavrepalanchowk</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>4</td>\r\n			<td>Deependra Kumar Sah</td>\r\n			<td>Dhangadimai Nagarpalika-Siraha</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>5</td>\r\n			<td>Dipmala Kumari Gupta</td>\r\n			<td>Dhangadimai Nagarpalika-Siraha</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '<p><span style=\"color:#0000FF\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</p>\r\n'),
(23, 'This portion will contain the description', 'This portion will contain the specification', 'This portion will contain the educational description', 'This will contain the description of the job processing status.', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(25, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>TEAM/PROGRAMME:</strong> Global Fund&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>LOCATION:</strong> National Tuberculosis Center (NTC), Bhaktapur<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>GRADE:</strong> 3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>CONTRACT LENGTH</strong>: Fixed term grant<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>MINIMUM EXPERIENCE</strong>: At least three years (<em>two years for GSI* group</em>) experience in Public Health program management<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>CHILD SAFEGUARDING</strong></u><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Level 3</strong>:</em> the post holder will have contact with children and/or young people either frequently (e.g. once a week or more) or intensively (e.g. four days in one month or more or overnight) because they work country programs; or are visiting country programs; or because they are responsible for implementing the police checking/vetting process staff.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>ROLE PURPOSE: </u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nSave the Children is the leading independent organization for children. We save children&rsquo;s lives; we fight for their rights; we help them fulfill their potential. We work together, with our partners from civil societies and government, to inspire breakthroughs in the way the world treats children and to achieve immediate and lasting change in their lives. We reached approximately two million populations and invests over 40 million US dollars annually to reach more children than ever before, through programs in Health, Nutrition, Education, Protection and Child Rights and Governance, Livelihood, HIV and AIDS, and Humanitarian crises.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe <strong>Program Coordinator - TB (PPM and CSS)</strong>, as a Technical person at NTC, will be responsible for providing technical assistance to NTP in the technical areas of and new approach in TB program such as Community System Strengthening (CSS) and Public Private Partnership (PPM). He/she will support in development of technical guidelines, SOPs, training curriculum in the related areas in close coordination with other technical/program staff at NTC, Regional TB Centre, D(P)HOs and Technical Specialist-TB based at Save the Children under the Global Fund grant. S/he will be responsible for overall planning and implementation of CSS and PPM related activities under the Global Fund and core Government fund of the NTP.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>SCOPE OF ROLE: </u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Reports to:</strong></em> Project Manager - TB, NTC, Global Fund<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Staff reporting to this post:</strong></em> None<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Budget Responsibilities:</strong></em> As per the approved schedule of delegation<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Role Dimensions:</strong></em> Save the Children works in all the districts of Nepal with a current staff complement of approximately 500 staff including around 120 staff under Global Fund and current expenditure of approximately USD 40 million each year which include USD 14.5 million annual budget of Global Fund.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>KEY AREAS OF ACCOUNTABILITY: </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead in designing and implementation of new TB interventions and community system strengthening (CSS) and Public Private Mix (PPM) in the TB program</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical support to develop and update of National Guidelines, Protocols, Training Manuals, Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) related to CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate in developing and maintaining key programmatic partnerships with key national and international technical partners related to CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Attend technical meetings and advocate and provide technical contribution at national forums in regards to CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical support for timely preparation and delivery of routine progress reports</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical support to program staff in implementation of planned CSS and PPM related activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take lead in preparation of progress reports, variance analysis, and programmatic justifications related to CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent NTC PMU section in organizing CSS related technical meetings, seminars, conferences, and workshops</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assess documents and training needs as well as support training plan for series of capacity building activities in the areas of CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor/supervise and on-site technical coaching/mentoring to technical/program GoN, SCI and partners&rsquo; staff at centre, province and local level in implementing CSS and PPM programs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide regular and ad-hoc technical updates on CSS and PPM to NTC team and partners</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare a case study documenting the learning from the project with a focus on programmatic as well as institutional dimensions, reflecting on processes as well as lessons learned</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with TB EDPs, including UN agencies, multi- and bi- lateral donors to for ensuing the timely completion of planned activities and exploring possible support for CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide support to SRs and SDPs to update tools, implement and share the best practices</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take lead on developing and maintaining close working relationships with District Health Officer/Public Health Officer and the Regional Health Director in designated areas, as well as with other individuals and organizations related to CSS and PPM</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Any other duties or assignments as requested by the Project Manager &ndash; Global Fund, relevant NTC government staff and Director of NTC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>SKILLS AND BEHAVIOURS (Our Values in Practice)</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<em><strong>Accountability:</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Holds self-accountable for making decisions, managing resources efficiently, achieving and role modelling Save the Children values</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Holds the team and partners accountable to deliver on their responsibilities - giving them the freedom to deliver in the best way they see fit, providing the necessary development to improve performance and applying appropriate consequences when results are not achieved</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Ambition:</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sets ambitious and challenging goals for themselves and their team, takes responsibility for their own personal development and encourages others to do the same</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Widely shares their personal vision for Save the Children, engages and motivates others</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Future orientated, thinks strategically</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Collaboration:</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Builds and maintains effective relationships, with their team, colleagues, Members and external partners and supporters</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Values diversity, sees it as a source of competitive strength</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approachable, good listener, easy to talk to</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Creativity:</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develops and encourages new and innovative solutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to take disciplined risks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Integrity:</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Honest, encourages openness and transparency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><u>QUALIFICATION:</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Master&rsquo;s degree in Public Health (MPH) or related health sciences</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><u>EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<em><strong>Essential</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum 3 years experience in Public Health program management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer experience with MS Word, Excel and PowerPoint</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent spoken and written skill in English and Nepali language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Desirable</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prior experience in TB Control Programme</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advocacy, leadership and communication skills</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Additional Job Responsibilities:</em></strong><br />\r\nThe duties and responsibilities as set out above are not exhaustive and the role holder may be required to cary out additional duties within reasonableness of their level of skills and expereince.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Equal Opportunities:</em></strong><br />\r\nThe role holder is required to carry out the duties in accordance with the SCI Equal Opportunities and Diversity policies and procedures.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Child Safeguarding:</strong></em><br />\r\nWe need to keep children safe so our selection process, which includes rigorous background checks, reflects our commitment to the protection of children from abuse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Health and Safety:</strong></em><br />\r\nThe role holder is required to carry out the duties in accordance with SCI Health and Safety policies and procedures.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(24, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>TEAM/PROGRAMME: </strong>Programme Development and Quality<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>LOCATION:&nbsp; </strong>Kathmandu<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>GRADE: </strong>2+<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>CONTRACT LENGTH: </strong>1 year with possibility of extension<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>MINIMUM EXPERIENCE: </strong>At least seven years (<em>five years for GSI* group</em>) of experience with 3-4 years&rsquo; experience in new business development.<br />\r\n<em>*GSI group includes Female, Dalit, Madhesi, People with Disabilities and other indigenous/minorities</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>CHILD SAFEGUARDING</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Level 2:</em></strong> <em><u>either</u></em> the post holder will have access to personal data about children and/or young people as part of their work; <em><u>or</u></em> the post holder will be working in a &lsquo;regulated&rsquo; position (accountant, barrister, solicitor, legal executive); therefore a police check will be required (at &lsquo;standard&rsquo; level in the UK or equivalent in other countries).<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>ROLE PURPOSE: </u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nSave the Children is the leading independent organization for children.&nbsp; We save children&rsquo;s lives; we fight for their rights; we help them fulfill their potential. We work together, with our partners from civil societies and government, to inspire breakthroughs in the way the world treats children and to achieve immediate and lasting change in their lives.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe <strong>Senior Specialist</strong> will play a lead role in strengthening SC Nepal staff capacity and business processes to position, capture, and develop competitive proposals for institutional donors. This position helps Save the Children&rsquo;s Nepal Country Office (CO) execute its vision and strategy by building effective Business Development tools, processes and capacities, supporting country team to position the agency for competitive funding opportunities, and responding to those opportunities with a quality process and product. S/he will help the CO develop an understanding of the global and local funding context, including a good knowledge of donor interests and requirements, and works with senior national CO staff to build and strengthen relationships with appropriate contacts in donor, government, and partner organizations. This position will help develop and implement a Business Development learning program tailored to the needs and interests of the Nepal country office.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis position will work closely with a collaborative, experienced, and growing US-based New Business Development team while embedded within the Nepal CO.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn the event of a major humanitarian emergency, the role holder will be expected to work outside the normal role profile and be able to vary working hours accordingly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>SCOPE OF ROLE: </u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Reports to:</em> </strong>Director, Program Development and Quality (PDQ)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Staff reporting to this post:</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Direct: </strong>None</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Indirect: </strong>The senior specialist will work closely with other PDQ, Awards, and Program Operations team members</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Budget Responsibilities:</em> </strong>N/A<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Role Dimensions</strong>:</em><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn addition to PDQ, this position will work closely with the Awards team and Program Operations Department to respond to funding opportunities. S/he will be responsible to strengthen the capacity of CO staff to enhance donor, government and partner relationships. S/he will also coordinate, consult with other departments for effective program designing, planning, and thematic integration. S/he will guide the country office in developing business development tools and guidelines.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>KEY AREAS OF ACCOUNTABILITY: </u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strengthen SCI staff capacity and process to position, capture, and develop competitive proposals for institutional donors. Develop and implement Business Development Learning Program tailored to the training needs and interests of country offices, in partnership with SCUS New Business Development (NBD) team and SCI Strategic Portfolio Planning team (30%)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work with senior country office staff to build and strengthen relationships with appropriate contacts in donor, government, and partner organizations (10%)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop/strengthen and maintain systems to track positioning and donor engagement strategies, monitor opportunity pipelines, and manage information necessary for effective capture planning and proposal development, in collaboration with CO staff (10%)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist CO staff to develop and maintain documentation on the successes, results, and lessons from CO past performance, suitable for proposal and capacity statements (10%)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In partnership with technical leads, provide quality control through reviews and evaluations, including team training on; writing, reviewing and editing documentation; supporting partner relations, and final document submission (20%)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Mobilize and oversee CO technical, operations, and cost contributions for US Government (USG) proposals, in partnership with SCUS proposal leads (20%)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide limited support to non-USG competitive funding opportunities in-country, or limited support to USG bids in other countries</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide support to humanitarian business development efforts on an as-needed basis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><u>SKILLS AND BEHAVIOURS (Our Values in Practice)</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Accountability:</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Holds self accountable for making decisions, managing resources efficiently, achieving and role modelling Save the Children values</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Holds the team and partners accountable to deliver on their responsibilities - giving them the freedom to deliver in the best way they see fit, providing the necessary development to improve performance and applying appropriate consequences when results are not achieved</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Ambition:</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sets ambitious and challenging goals for themselves and their team, takes responsibility for their own personal development and encourages others to do the same</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Widely shares their personal vision for Save the Children, engages and motivates others</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Future orientated, thinks strategically</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Collaboration:</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Builds and maintains effective relationships, with their team, colleagues, Members and external partners and supporters</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Values diversity, sees it as a source of competitive strength</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approachable, good listener, easy to talk to</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Displays cultural, gender, religion, race and age sensitivity and adaptability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Creativity:</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develops and encourages new and innovative solutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to take disciplined risks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Integrity:</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Honest, encourages openness and transparency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><u>QUALIFICATIONS: </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Master&rsquo;s degree in a related field</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS:</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Essential</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">7 &ndash; 10 years of work experience with 3 &ndash; 5&nbsp; years relevant work experience in new business development</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Significant knowledge of and direct experience developing proposals for USG donor agencies, particularly USAID. Experience with USG contract mechanisms</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven experience creating and delivering face-to-face trainings and blended learning resources in cross-cultural contexts</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to work independently and under tight deadlines, manage multiple tasks simultaneously, and effectively lead and work in multi-cultural, cross-functional capture and proposal teams</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communication, negotiation, interpersonal, and networking skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and spoken English</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated skill in proposal and report writing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Desirable</strong></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working in South Asia, specifically Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent writing and presentation skills using Microsoft Office Suite platforms</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong skills in SharePoint, graphics software and virtual collaboration platforms (Preferred)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><strong>Additional Job Responsibilities:</strong></em><br />\r\nThe duties and responsibilities as set out above are not exhaustive and the role holder may be required to carry out additional duties within reasonableness of their level of skills and experience.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Equal Opportunities:</strong></em><br />\r\nThe role holder is required to carry out the duties in accordance with the SCI Equal Opportunities and Diversity policies and procedures.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Child Safeguarding:</strong></em><br />\r\nWe need to keep children safe so our selection process, which includes rigorous background checks, reflects our commitment to the protection of children from abuse.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Health and Safety:</strong></em><br />\r\nThe role holder is required to carry out the duties in accordance with SCI Health and Safety policies and procedures.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n'),
(49, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Web Designer<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Analyze the requirements and research the feasibility as well as market trends for the design.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">All stages of design activities: focusing on User Interface and User Experience.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent knowledge in front-end languages like HTML, CSS, JQuery and Javascript.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Creative design using Photoshop/Illustrator or any other design tools</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">PSD to HTML slicing with good speed.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Must be willing to work in accordance with the company&#39;s norms</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establishing design guidelines, standards, and best practices.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Communicating design ideas using user flows, process flows, sitemaps and wireframes.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Perform all phases of front-end development including requirements analysis, design, development and testing OR Executing all visual design stages from concept to final product delivery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Knowledge on PHP will be plus point.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Other Specific Requirements:</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good command over English with a desire to expand your skills.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Passion for design, always learning and open to new ideas.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Candidates should be very focused and committed to achieving goals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should be a very good team player.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should be a good team player. Female candidates are encourage to apply.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should always have encouragement in suggesting ideas to improve the product.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Qualification and Experience</u></strong><br />\r\n- Candidates who meet the above requirement can apply.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(27, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Manager- Administration and Human Resources<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> Administration and Human Resources (HR)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Deputy Executive Director / Deputy Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO), Administration and Management<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> D<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This&nbsp;position&nbsp;will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Manager - Administration and Human Resources under the supervision of the DED/DCEO, Administration and Management, is responsible for the daily execution, monitoring, and supervision of a range of activities supporting the overall Administration and Human Resources component, ensuring consistency with established work plans and implementation guidelines.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em>Human Resources Systems &amp; Management</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor administration, operations, human resources and contracts activities, ensuring that these are consistent with established MCA-N guidelines and that issues and discrepancies are resolved and reported</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare organization chart, job design and conduct job evaluation and recommend changes as needed</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute and/or oversee a range of project implementation and support activities as defined by the project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives, and ensure consistency of quality</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate project statistics from multiple sources and review these for accuracy and compliance with established formats to support implementation, monitoring, and analytics</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise DED/DCEO, Administration and Management of issues related to the implementation of the project in order ensure the continuity of project delivery</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In conjunction with the Finance function, administer payroll disbursements to employees in a timely manner, and ensure proper deduction/adjustment of taxes, benefits and allowances</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>Recruitment &amp; Staffing</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work with program managers to determine staffing needs by developing Scope of Work, and Terms of References</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain current job descriptions and create new descriptions as necessary&mdash;done in conjunction with appropriate Line Project Managers, ED/CEO, and DED/DCEO</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>Administration &amp; Compliance </em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Be the custodian of key systems for accountability such as time-keeping, attendance, leave balance and others</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Safeguard confidentiality, privacy and integrity of HR related matters such as Grievance procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure Administration support to staffs with a conductive environment for workplace that protects the staffs&rsquo; well-being, health, safety &amp; security</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor project timelines and milestones, anticipate delivery issues, and ensure that staff and external stakeholders are kept informed of administration and human resources status to support overall project management and delivery</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain project documentation and Operations Manuals ensuring that these are current and reflecting lessons learned to support the improvement of projects/processes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>Capacity Building &amp; Staff Development</em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide training, support and advice on performance management and staff development plans</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In conjunction with line Project Managers, organize and lead workshops, retreats and continuing learning to boost morale, productivity and performance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>Performance Management </em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure a transparent, fair and accountable performance management and evaluation plan is in place</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the evaluation process at each and every staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide guidance and advise as they carry out evaluations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (minimum) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in Human Resources Management, Business Administration, Business Information Systems, Public Administration, Economics, Social Sciences, Humanities or equivalent fields</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Seven (7) years of experience or more preferred (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s degree) in managing the HR function in managing projects of similar size and managing direct reports of at least 5 personnel</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in acquisition of human resource through: HR planning, recruitment, selection, orientation, and employee socialization</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in taking the lead in the interview process for new recruitments, while making sure the organization benefits from the intake of most qualified candidates</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in preparing organization chart, job design and conduct job evaluation and recommend changes as needed</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in managing and administering compensation/benefits while recommending more cost effective ways of offering/administering such benefits</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Preparing and managing operational budgets for hiring, evaluating the administration, procurement and hiring processes, negotiation and awarding the contracts, and managing the recruitment, selection and hiring of new staffs and consultants and contractors for a timely and quality implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred; completed project references will be given additional advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in administration and HR in the context of international development program management is desired</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n'),
(50, '<strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Oversee delivery of various IT services (e.g. infrastructure maintenance, database management, etc.) across the RPPL &nbsp;ensuring that the quality of execution meets organization needs and established IT standards</li>\r\n	<li>Advise management on overall issues regarding day-to-day IT operations and provide inputs to improve delivery and efficiency of services rendered&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Provide recommendations on network and hardware developments or upgrades for organization use in support of increased efficiency and productivity of wider program deliverables</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Develop regular testing, update, and maintenance schedule for IT infrastructure to ensure continuity of functionality and capacity to service the needs of the RPPL</li>\r\n	<li>Assess existing procedures/protocols to incorporate improvements based on user feedback to facilitate seamless delivery of services</li>\r\n	<li>Fulfill the following tasks (some of them being covered and added in the future IT Scope of Work)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li>Provide new staffs with IT equipment set up to their needs</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the networks</li>\r\n	<li>Manage network prioritization due to limited bandwidth</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and put in place sound back-up systems</li>\r\n	<li>Establish and enforce various IT policies (setting up e-mails, use of internet, accounts delection, etc)</li>\r\n	<li>Provide resolution to IT issues (repairs and maintenance)</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain confidentiality, privacy and integrity of IT infrastructure through cybersecurity</li>\r\n	<li>Support procurement in gaining new hardware and also provide maintenance and updates to ensure smooth running of IT systems</li>\r\n	<li>Install and configure computer networks and system</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience)</em>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (Required) from a recognized institution in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Electronic &amp; Communications Engineering, and Business Information System or equivalent fields</li>\r\n	<li>Significant prior experience in the provision of IT services will be a plus point</li>\r\n	<li>Network Certification such as CCNA, RHCE will be a plus point</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><u><strong>Fresher can apply </strong></u></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Other Requirements</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Good command over English with a desire to expand your skills.</li>\r\n	<li>Passion for design, always learning and open to new ideas.</li>\r\n	<li>Candidates should be very focused and committed to achieving goals</li>\r\n	<li>Should be a very good team player.</li>\r\n	<li>Should be a good team player. Female candidates are encourage to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Should always have encouragement in suggesting ideas to improve the product</li>\r\n	<li>Salary is negotiable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(26, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Board of Directors<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> F<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Minimum Experience :</strong> 15 years<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position&nbsp;will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO), accountable to the MCA-N Board, is responsible for leading the MCA-N, the direct management of the MCA-N&rsquo;s Program and Operational Support Functions and serving as the primary representative of the MCA-N in the country to stakeholders, the MCA-N Board and MCC.The ED/CEO will be responsible for the overall implementation of the Compact Program in Nepal and will provide high-level executive leadership and management for the MCA-N office.The ED/CEO is accountable to the Millennium Challenge Account-Nepal (MCA-N) Board of Directors and will report to the Board on a regular basis.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Perform all tasks as indicated in the Millennium Challenge Account Development Board Formation Order, 2074 (2018) section 7: Function, Duties and Power of Executive Director</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the MCA-N, aligning both the Programmatic and Operations functions, and develop systems and strategies that establish the targets for the Compact and ensure its delivery</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Guide functional and project heads across the MCA-Nand ensure a collaborative environment is established to facilitate cooperation, sharing of information, and shared accountability for the success of the Compact</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Serve as the official point of contact on behalf of the Government of Nepal in its relations with MCC</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the Compact program to the Nepali public and serve as the lead representative of MCA-N to the donor community, civil society, the private sector, and other constituencies</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to the Board of Directors on a regular basis to inform it of progress, issues, and risks related to the implementation of the Compact program and link inputs from the MCA-N Board with the MCA-N&rsquo;s strategic development</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute overall guidance and instructions from the Board of Directors to implement the Compact in a timely and effective manner</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide high-level executive leadership and management for the MCA-N office</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to the MCA-N Board on a regular basis to inform it of progress, issues, and risks related to the implementation of the Compact program, and link inputs from the MCA-N Board with the MCA-N&rsquo;s strategic development</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Evaluate the Compact&rsquo;s programmatic, statutory, and operational requirements and develop Operations and Program frameworks, and allocate budgets and resources, to ensure the MCA-N&rsquo;s ability to deliver</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide high-level degree of accountability to ensure financial expenditures and implementation milestones are time-bound and on track</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide guidance and advice, and when needed, manage and coordinate for the development of the implementation plans of MCA-N; including final approval of the budgets, work plans, procurement plans, and monitoring and evaluation (M&amp;E) plans related to the Compact program; and recommend these to the Board of Directors and to MCC for their approval</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide guidance in the implementation of projects and other types of Compact activities and ensure continuous improvement of operational efficiency in Compact implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work closely with the senior leadership of relevant government units to ensure dissemination of critical information, commitment of resources, and the timely progress related to the Compact program</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Direct, motivate, and coordinate the various divisions of MCA-Ntowards achieving their objectives and targets</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Build the country management team and identify technical resources (e.g. external consultants, MCC technical resources) aligned to the needs of the MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Guide functional and project heads across the MCA-N and ensure a collaborative environment is established to facilitate cooperation, sharing of information, and shared accountability for the success of the Compact</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the selection process of the MCA-N staff, especially, at the management level</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide on-going communications and logistical support to the MCA-N team in the consultation process (includes attending the stakeholder committee meetings)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Promote and track action on MCC eligibility indicator performance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support GoN/MCA-Nrelations by building, maintaining, and leveraging a good network of contacts to facilitate and/or promote the program</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor and liaise with the media to ensure that accurate information about the program reach the public domain</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Arrange for press conferences, outreach to the media, and manage the development and execution of a media plan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Master&rsquo;s degree required from a recognized institution in following or equivalent fields: engineering, business administration, business management, finance, international development, development finance, economics, banking, statistics, commerce, chartered accountancy, international affairs and public policy, public administration, corporate law</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Managing a team of executives who in turn manage multi-dimensional projects, manage consultants and construction contractors and prepare reports and performance reviews on a regular basis. Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fifteen (15) or more years of cumulative experience (earned after Bachelor&rsquo;s degree) in senior management position in a reputable organization preferably both inside and outside government</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Extensive Experience in Development Program Management, in Nepal, in the region or globally</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated project management experience and proven management skills in managing similar programs (cumulative budget of at least US$ 50 million) and at least thirty (30) personnel</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with Nepali government public financial management and donor project management or similar systems is a plus</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with MCC policies and procedures is a plus</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Full computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, the Internet, and familiarity with Management Information Systems and project management systems</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English and Nepali</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Has high degree of integrity, code of conduct and ethics and exercises good judgement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(38, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communications Specialist </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Communications and Outreach</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Manager, Administration and HR</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nReporting to the Manager, Administration and Human Resources (HR), the Communications Specialist will execute broad-based strategic communications strategies and plans to effectively promote and publicize MCA-Nepal projects and activities and to strengthen stakeholder participation in the Compact.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Outreach</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Implement a communications strategy and plan with clearly defined objectives, messages, and an outreach plan with timeline of outreach activities to targeted stakeholders and liaise with MCC counterparts during the development and refinement of these plans</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain and strengthen relationship with stakeholders, focusing primarily on the political parties, Government and the media</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage all MCA-N public events such as forums, press events, workshops and seminars</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee public consultation sessions, in coordination and collaboration with the ESP/GSI teams</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Be responsible as the contract manager for any external communications consultancy that is awarded; this includes monitoring the consultancy&rsquo;s work, as defined in their scope of work, on a regular basis and ensuring that MCA-N, MCC guidelines are being followed, verifying the consultant&rsquo;s work and associated invoice before recommending for payment</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and execute of annual and monthly work plans for all communications and outreach activities, clearly detailing roles/responsibilities, deadlines and budgets for each activity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the Finance office, develop and manage of annual and quarterly budgets for communications and outreach activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop the consultative process plan, in compliance with MCC&rsquo;s requirements, in collaboration with the Environmental Social Performance/Gender &amp; Social Inclusion (ESP/GSI) teams</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Reporting</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work in coordination with Monitoring &amp; Evaluation (M&amp;E) to accurately promote MCA-N results and success stories</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Commission where appropriate photographers, journalists, columnists or film crews to cover issues linked to project activities or special events</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor political developments and develop strategies on behalf of the Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO) and the MCA-N to deal with a dynamic political environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Communications &amp; Productions </u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In collaboration with the Information Technology (IT) department, co-manage and co-direct the development of the MCA-N website</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In collaboration with other MCA-N offices/departments, ensure that minutes of meetings of the BoDs are properly recorded and made public in both English and Nepali, within two weeks of the meeting date, via the MCA-N website</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure quality output in MCA-N social media plan, brochure and other promotional materials</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Solicit media partners in electronic, printed and social media for the MCA-N to disseminate information about Compact project opportunities and achievements</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the engagement with the media to ensure that accurate information about the program reach the public domain</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Act as the conduit for all of MCA N&rsquo;s, and its employees interactions with the media</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop MCA-N Branding Guidelines that will adhere to the mandatory MCC Branding Guidelines and manage the MCA-N brand</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take direction from the Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO) in serving as the spokesperson of MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare speeches for ED/CEO and other executives public speaking engagements</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Write press releases, answer press enquiries</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Perform other tasks and special projects as assigned by the ED/CEO&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree from a recognized institution in Communications, Development Communications, Creative Writing, Mass Communications, Journalism,&nbsp; Photography, Filmmaking, Community Development, Business Administration or&nbsp; equivalent field</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) or more years of experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in corporate communications, community and public outreach. Experience in development communications is a plus</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge and expertise in crafting and delivering messages to diverse stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in managing development of print, audio/visual, advertising and promotional communication products</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge in the development of proposals, such as grant proposals, financing proposals or business plans will be an advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both English and Nepali</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good Information and Technology skills, e.g. word processing, power point and other communications and publishing applications</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and demonstrated the ability to effectively interact and collaborate with people in multidisciplinary teams as well as work across departments, divisions and institutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge and expertise in group and public facilitation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated high degree of courtesy, tact and discretion</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have creativity and capability to be flexible to respond to changing requirements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(34, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Assistant to the CEO</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Administration</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Executive Director/CEO (ED/CEO)</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; B</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Assistant, reporting directly to the ED/CEO, provides support in a range of administrative services including organization of event logistics, travel arrangements, and maintenance of office inventories and filing systems related to the ED/CEO.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Office Management</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains an inventory of office supplies and equipment ensuring that stocks are replenished on a regular basis and faulty equipment are repaired as needed facilitating workplace efficiency</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains filing systems and databases of all division and project documentation to ensure that activities are well-documented in support of planning and auditing processes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Administration</em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Submit and reconcile expense reports</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take accurate minutes of meetings</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Produce and distribute correspondences, memos, letters, faxes and other forms of communications</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Handle sensitive communication with highest degree of confidentiality and integrity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Initiates communication within MCA-N and with external service providers, to ensure that logistical preparations for workshops, meetings, and events are in place allowing sufficient leeway in case of changes in schedule or venue</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize and schedule meetings and appointments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Logistics</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organizes logistics and materials for workshops, meetings, and events to support smooth-running activities for the ED/CEO</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Processes visa applications and travel arrangements, travel disbursements, and other travel-related requirements in accordance with MCA-N&rsquo;s&nbsp;&nbsp; travel policy in order to support leadership activities for ED/CEO</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree from a recognized institution in Human Resources Management, Business Administration, Business Information Systems, Public Administration, General Management, Office Management, Economics, Natural Sciences, Social Sciences, Humanities, Arts, Commerce, Public Policy or equivalent fields</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum three (3) years of cumulative experience in General Office Administration &amp; Management (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent time management skills and ability to multi-task and prioritize work</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communications skills in speaking and writing and note-taking</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Attention to detail</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Problem-solving skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A self-starter who is proactive, takes ownership and initiative</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(30, '<strong>Position:</strong> Deputy CEO / Deputy ED Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> E<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nAs a member of MCA-N Senior Management Team, the Deputy Executive Director/Deputy Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO) for Management will be responsible to lead day-to-day management of MCA-N, provide guidance and support to the ED/CEO on the execution of Compact projects and cross-cutting sector activities, and to ensure sound coordination and project management in achieving Compact targets. The incumbent will ensure that appropriate resources, and MCA-N internal policies, are aligned with the achievement of work plans within agreed-upon time lines and budgets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Leads day-to-day project workflows across the Management unit</li>\r\n	<li>Leads and works closely with the Managers on quarterly fund disbursement processes for each project for a comprehensive and timely submission</li>\r\n	<li>Provides project oversight and works closely with the Managers to develop, update and implement work plans</li>\r\n	<li>Leads and ensures appropriate progress, coordination, collaboration and synergy with the ED/CEO, DED/DCEO of Project Delivery, and General Counsel to ensure exchange of relevant information, and to identify issues and risks, assess impacts and develop mitigation strategies</li>\r\n	<li>Makes recommendations and provide strategic guidance for the projects and cross cutting sectors development and implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Leads and maintains regular communications and good partnership with MCC to support projects operation</li>\r\n	<li>Ensures continuous improvement of projects and implementation efficiency in the Management team</li>\r\n	<li>Leads in formulating, coordinating, and recommending of issues to address to the Board of Directors, which includes preparation of the implementation plan, budget, Compact program activities, and subsequently, through the ED/CEO, endorses these to the Board of Directors for its approval</li>\r\n	<li>Provides oversight and works closely with Managers to ensure compliance with MCC guidelines and procedures, also the Government of Nepal regulatory framework</li>\r\n	<li>Leads and be responsible for coordinating the preparation of periodic reports related to the program that are required by MCC and the Board of Directors</li>\r\n	<li>Assists the Executive Director in representing the MCA-N and its Compact program to the Nepali public and MCA-N&rsquo;s partners/stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li>May acts as officer-in-charge in the absence of the ED/CEO</li>\r\n	<li>Performs other tasks and special projects as assigned by the ED/CEO</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution is desired in following or equivalent fields: business administration, finance, international development, development finance, economics, banking, statistics, commerce, chartered accountancy, international affairs, public policy, public administration, corporate law, Social Science, or a technical/engineering field</li>\r\n	<li>Experienced senior manager with proven record in a senior management position in project/program development and implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Internationally-recognized project management credentials would be an advantage</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum 10 years&rsquo; demonstrated cumulative experience (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s degree) building teams and managing staff to ensure effective project implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Managing a team of minimum of fifteen (15) direct reports such as project managers who in turn manage multi-dimensional projects, manage consultants and construction contractors, and prepare reports and performance reviews on a regular basis</li>\r\n	<li>Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Familiarity with international development in Nepal or another similar developing country and/or a strong background and experience in designing or implementing similar projects is an advantage</li>\r\n	<li>Proven record in high level facilitation and negotiation, and experienced developing and preparing strategies and in their implementation</li>\r\n	<li>Familiar or have experience in monitoring and evaluation, environment and social performance or gender development</li>\r\n	<li>Capable of building and maintaining productive relationships with a range of stakeholders, including Government officials, communities, NGOs, education institutions, private sectors and international donors</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent command of English and Nepali, both written and spoken, is essential</li>\r\n	<li>Good Information Technology, computer skills</li>\r\n	<li>Proven coordination and management skills and experience, especially in projects with multi-disciplinary components</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Excellent strategic thinking, facilitation and negotiation skills</li>\r\n	<li>Has high degree integrity, ethics, and code of conduct and exercise good judgement</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, and demonstrated ability to effectively interact and collaborate with people in multidisciplinary teams as well as work across departments, divisions and institutions</li>\r\n	<li>Has capability to be flexible to respond to changing requirements</li>\r\n	<li>Values the continuous improvement and learning, and committed to mentoring and coaching</li>\r\n	<li>Is results-focused</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n'),
(53, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><u><strong>POSITION SUMMARY:</strong></u><br />\r\nWinrock International seeks a Law and Governance Manager to successfully lead programming aimed at strengthening the national and local government of Nepal efforts to combat human trafficking.&nbsp; S/he will also lead all justice-related programming including legislative analysis, legal aid, and training for justice actors. The Law and Governance Manager will be the primary liaison with the Government of Nepal at the national level, will manage a team of Field Coordinators who provide support to provincial and municipal level actors and oversee the quality of work done by grantees in related areas. S/he will have a high level of technical understanding of the legal and policy framework governing trafficking in persons, including trafficking during the foreign migration process and relevant international conventions. The Law and Governance Manager will have a deep understanding of the drivers of trafficking and unsafe migration and an enthusiasm for driving the Hamro Samman project forward to achieve meaningful and sustainable impact that reduces human trafficking.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>ESSENTIAL RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></u><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and maintain strong relationships national, provincial and municipal level government institutions and justice actors</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with government officials to improve data collection, sharing and usage to strengthen policy, coordination, and public reporting</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assess capacity of and strengthen national and sub-national committees for controlling human trafficking to prevent, protect and prosecute TIP</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assess capacity of and strengthen government capacity at national and sub-national levels to monitor and enforce policies related to labor recruitment and TIP</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support initiatives to implement national and international recommendations to mitigate and address human trafficking</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support initiatives to strengthen regional networks and cooperation mechanisms in support of national counter trafficking legislation in Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Reduce legal barriers for survivors to access justice and increase prosecution\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Oversee and engage in the design and delivery of training for justice actors</li>\r\n		<li>Oversee and engage in legislative analysis, legislative drafting and policy recommendations and advocacy at the municipal, provincial and national level</li>\r\n		<li>Oversee delivery of a sustainable legal aid program by partners</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee and engage in design, implementation and finalization of high quality CTIP research</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide high quality, written analysis and reporting in English</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other duties as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>QUALIFICATIONS: </strong></u><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Education:&nbsp;</strong>Bachelor degree (Masters preferred) in law, human rights, or other relevant field<br />\r\n<strong>Technical: </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum 7 years&rsquo; experience in policy and legal work related to countering human trafficking, safe migration or other relevant field such as human rights</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Relevant experience implementing policy development and advocacy programs with the government at the national level</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience building the capacity of government entities as the national and sub-national level</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience managing international projects to the highest ethical and quality standards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Skills/Knowledge:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge or understanding of social, economic, and political context governing anti-trafficking and safe migration issues</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge of international and national laws and regulations pertinent to labor migration and human trafficking</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge of human and institutional capacity building tools and approaches, particularly in a decentralized governance system</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Understanding of policies and enforcement mechanisms related to TIP in Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer literacy in Microsoft Word, Excel, and Powerpoint.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Core Competencies:</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Professionalism</strong>: Strong knowledge of the relevant technical areas.<br />\r\n<strong>Planning &amp; Organizing</strong>: Ability to plan work and manage conflicting priorities.<br />\r\n<strong>Communication</strong>: Excellent spoken and written communication skills, including the ability to liaise with technical staff and present information in a clear and concise style. Fluency in written in English.<br />\r\n<strong>Teamwork</strong>: Good interpersonal skills and ability to establish and maintain effective partnerships and working relations in a multi-cultural, multi-ethnic environment with sensitivity and respect for diversity.<br />\r\n<strong>Analytical skills</strong>: Ability to analyze information and solve problems with excellent attention to detail.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>Women, people with disabilities and those belonging to discriminated groups are strongly encouraged to apply.</strong></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">All employees should adhere to USAID and Winrock International&rsquo;s code of ethics, and specifically child safeguarding and trafficking in persons provisions covered in the project agreement.<br />\r\nEEOE/AA.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(54, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><u><strong>Position Summary:</strong></u><br />\r\nHamro Samman is building partnerships with the private sector to increase access to services for peo[ple at risk of being trafficked and trafficking survivors.&nbsp; Particularly, Hamro Samman is partnering with private sector companies to increase access to information to help reduce the risk of trafficking and to increase access to services such as skills-building and livelihoods. The Partnerships and CommunicationsCoordinator willwork under the supervision of the Private Sector Engagement Specialist to support the successful implementation of the private sector engagement activities for the Hamro Samman project including supporting innovation challenges, livelihoods activities, skills-building and outreach. This role will also involve taking the lead on developing a strategic communication campaign targeted at changing behaviors to reduce the risk of human trafficking in the foreign labor migration process and in the entertainment sector within Nepal.&nbsp; In addition to supporting the work of private sector partnerships, under the supervision of the Chief of Party, the Partnerships and Communications Coordinator will be the primary communication focal point for the project, providing technical support to the project&rsquo;s government and civil society partners on strategic communication initiatives and ensuring the visibility of project activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>ESSENTIAL REPONSIBILITIES:</strong></u><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and establish strong working relationships with private sector partners under the guidance of the Private Sector Engagement Specialist</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support private sector partners to successfully implement activities including but not limited to an ICT innovation challenge and the resulting ICT solution; livelihoods training and a communications campaign</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide programmatic coordination and technical support for all private sector engagement activities ensuring quality, timeliness and integration with other project components</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage in the monitoring, evaluating and reporting on all private sector partner activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Conceptualize and lead the development of an integrated mass-media campaign to be rolled out by private sector partners focusing on reducing the risk of trafficking in the foreign labor migration process and in the entertainment sector</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical support to the project&rsquo;s private sector, civil society and government partners in developing and implementing effective communication strategies to counter human trafficking</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Design and produce quality audio and visual materials including photographs, short videos, brochures, banners, and social media posts</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate project events, liaise with media and develop press releases and external communications</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure implementation of the USAID branding and marking plan</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Edit all project documents prior to publication to ensure consistency and accuracy</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other duties as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>QUALIFICATIONS: </strong></u><br />\r\n<strong>Education:&nbsp;</strong>Bachelor degreein communications, marketing, international developmentor related field<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Technical: </strong>Minimum of 3 years of professional experience in communications, marketing, public relations.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Experience:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience supporting the project cycle (programmatically)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in behavior change communications;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in developing effective communication campaigns and measuring results;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Design experience</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Skills/Knowledge:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong program management skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent networking skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to engage in desk research to determine communication themes and messaging for advocacy campaigns to prevent trafficking in persons</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong training and presentation skills, with the ability to represent the project in public forums</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience enlisting media practitioners and other key stakeholders in planning and executing major events and campaigns</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experienced utilizing appropriate traditional and social media to achieve objectives</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and oral communication skills in English and Nepali required</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent visual, design and formatting skillswith strong attention to detail required</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advanced computer skills in Microsoft Word, Excel, Editor, Movie Maker and Powerpoint</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical experience or knowledge of human trafficking, labor migration and related themes preferred</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Core Competencies:</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Professionalism</strong>: Strong knowledge of the relevant technical areas.<br />\r\n<strong>Planning &amp; Organizing</strong>: Ability to plan work and manage conflicting priorities.<br />\r\n<strong>Communication</strong>: Excellent spoken and written communication skills, including the ability to liaise with technical staff and present information in a clear and concise style. Fluency in written in English.<br />\r\n<strong>Teamwork</strong>: Good interpersonal skills and ability to establish and maintain effective partnerships and working relations in a multi-cultural, multi-ethnic environment with sensitivity and respect for diversity.<br />\r\n<strong>Analytical skills</strong>: Ability to analyze information and solve problems with excellent attention to detail.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>Women, people with disabilities and those belonging to discriminated groups are strongly encouraged to apply.</strong></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">All employees should adhere to USAID and Winrock International&rsquo;s code of ethics, and specifically child safeguarding and trafficking in persons provisions covered in the project agreement.<br />\r\nEEOE/AA.</span></div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(51, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><u><strong>POSITION SUMMARY:</strong></u><br />\r\nThe Grants and Contracts Coordinator will coordinate the award of allgrants by Hamro Samman, monitor award-relatedwork flows to ensure compliance with USAID regulations and internal processes, ensure the smooth operation of the award systems; and strengthen the capacity of grantees to comply with award terms and conditions, as well as applicable regulations and Winrock International policy.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>ESSENTIAL REPONSIBILITIES:</strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop, analyze, review and negotiate requests for quotations, selection memos, contracts and purchase orders for the procurement of goods and services in compliance with Winrock and USAID rules and regulations</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop, review, and finalize terms of reference for grant opportunities in coordination with relevant program team</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Publicize grant opportunities, and coordinate the proposal review and award process ensuring compliance with USAID regulations and internal Winrock procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide training and capacity building support to grantees as needed</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop, analyze, review and negotiate contract documents for subawards and grants</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review sub-award modifications, notify senior management of problems and risks</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Processtimely advance requests and reconciliation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review grantee narrative and financial reports to ensure accuracy and completeness</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Track contracts and agreements to ensure timely advances, renewals and close out</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure grantee compliance with all aspects of the agreements</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Visit grantees&rsquo; offices and project activities regularly to assess compliance and provide capacity building support</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain high ethical standards of integrity;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Respect confidentiality and represent Winrock International at all times</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>QUALIFICATIONS: </strong></u><br />\r\n<strong>Education:&nbsp;</strong>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Business Administration, Finance, or related field, with relevant work experience in a regulatory environment; or equivalent combination of education and five years&rsquo; work experience<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Technical:&nbsp;</strong>A minimum of four years&rsquo; experience with grants and/or contracts management under USAID or other international projects<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Experience:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience supporting international projects to the highest ethical standards</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated administrative skills in supporting the management of complex, multi-activity programming, on time and on budget</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience developing and implementing of grants manuals, solicitations, award documents and award modifications</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience coordinating procurement of goods and services</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong workflow management skills; flexibility; good interpersonal and organizational skills for coordinating a variety of tasks simultaneously; attention to detail; team player</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Skills/Knowledge:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sound knowledge of procurement, donor contracts, financial and accounting regulations and procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent knowledge of oral and written English</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer literate in word processing, spreadsheet, and presentation software (Microsoft)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Adhere to USAID and Winrock International&rsquo;s code of ethics, and specifically child safeguarding and trafficking in persons provisions covered in the project agreement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"color:#FF0000\">Women, people with disabilities and those belonging to discriminated groups are strongly encouraged to apply.</span></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">All employees should adhere to USAID and Winrock International&rsquo;s code of ethics, and specifically child safeguarding and trafficking in persons provisions covered in the project agreement.</span></div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(62, '<strong><u>Server Administrator Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nKeeping a company server operating at maximum efficiency involves several duties and responsibilities. We analyzed job descriptions to come up with the following list of most common Server Administrator duties and responsibilities.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>User Administration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nServer Administrators are responsible for creating new user accounts for new employees and removing the accounts of ex-employees. They are also responsible for recovering lost passwords and keeping user data secure. Part of this duty requires Server Administrators to help non-IT employees with any technical issues.\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop and Implement Network Maintenance Standard Operating Procedure</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo keep a server operating at its best condition, Server Administrators must create and implement a network maintenance SOP. This involves regularly updating operating systems and databases with the latest updates, as well as checking all hardware within employee workstations for issues.\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diagnose and Repair Hardware and Network Malfunctions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWhen employees have an issue with their workstation, they call the Server Administrator to find and fix the problem. This involves running diagnostic tests to determine whether the issue is hardware or software. Sometimes it is as simple as a loose wire, and other times the machine is fried completely. It is the Server Administrator&rsquo;s responsibility to determine the severity of the issue and respond accordingly.\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop and Implement Network Security Strategy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIn today&rsquo;s digital age, network security is crucial. It is the responsibility of the Server Administrator to ensure security firewalls are updated regularly and remain fully functional.\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Keep Upper Management Informed With Regular Reports</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nUpper management doesn&rsquo;t need to know all of the technical details involved in keeping their network running &ndash; that&rsquo;s what they pay their Server Administrator for. The Server Administrator provides upper management with regular reports outlining pertinent information.<br />\r\n<strong>Server Administrator Skills</strong><br />\r\nThe role of Server Administrator is a technical position that requires hard IT skills and knowledge. Server Administrators must have a working knowledge of TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP, LAN and WAN to troubleshoot and address server issues. They must also know about firewalls, proxy and databases to keep the network and user information secure. Server Administrators also have to be good communicators as part of their job involves helping non-IT users with common hardware and software issues. Here are the skills that most employers are looking for in Server Administrator candidates.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Using knowledge of TCP/IP, DNS, LAN and WAN to maintain server functionality</li>\r\n	<li>Using analytical and reasoning skills to troubleshoot and repair server issues</li>\r\n	<li>Communicating effectively with colleagues across teams as well as company management</li>\r\n	<li>Best knowledge in cloud server</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(52, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><u><strong>POSITION SUMMARY</strong>: &nbsp; </u><br />\r\nThe Gender Equality and Social Inclusion Specialist will provide technical leadership in applying a social inclusion and gender equity framework in planning, implementation, and performance monitoring across Nepal CTIP objectives and program components and monitor cross-cutting approaches for integrating this framework in prevention, protection and prosecution; s/he will also advise on case management of aftercare for survivors of trafficking.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>ESSENTIAL REPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Conduct a gender and social discrimination analysis and develop a framework to effectively integrate gender equality and social inclusion into NCTIP objectives and strategies, M&amp;E plan, workplans, and activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Periodically assess the integration of the gender framework in project activities and results and promote creative and gender responsive solutions to addressing TIP at national and sub-national levels</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide strategies and support the staff in the development of messages and content for the behavioral change campaign to address gender inequality and other forms of social discrimination</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead staff and partner capacity building in gender-responsive programming</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support capacity building of CSO partners to carry out research, analysis and advocacy for gender responsive and inclusive policies and services related to TIP</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Act as the focal person for linking NCTIP with national efforts to promote gender equality and social inclusion, and engage organizations focusing on marginalized groups such as castes, ethnic minorities and LGBT to develop their capacity to reduce TIP vulnerabilities.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical support to design and implement gender-sensitive and inclusive aftercare services for survivors of trafficking and labor exploitation.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and maintain relationships with relevant local organizations, Government of Nepal, as well as private sector partners to improve referral mechanisms and services; implement and maintain standards of care for survivors</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Contribute to preparation of quarterly and other reports as required, specifically highlighting the integration of a gender framework in NCTIP and progress on gender and social inclusion indicators</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other duties as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>QUALIFICATIONS: </strong></u><br />\r\n<strong>Education:&nbsp;</strong>Advanced degree in gender studies, social work, psychology, human rights, international development or related field; or equivalent professional experience in gender in development, youth engagement or related fields<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Technical:&nbsp;</strong>A minimum of five years&rsquo; professional experience in gender analysis and programming in the field of human trafficking prevention, labor migration, victim support services, gender-based violence, women&rsquo;s empowerment&nbsp; preferably within the Nepali context; Minimum three years&rsquo; experience direct assistance through case management process for reintegration of victims of human trafficking and/or other forms of abuses<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Work Experience:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience implementing international projects to the highest ethical standards</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Extensive experience in networking and collaborative activities with relevant government agencies as well as local and international NGOs addressing human trafficking and labor migration issues in Nepal and the SAARC region</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in training and integrating gender equality and women&rsquo;s empowerment in project design and implementation, preferably in Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong programming and M&amp;E experience in gender-related work</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to lead, advocate for, train and work effectively with partners and transfer knowledge on gender-related work to diverse audiences through workshops, training, meetings applying participatory methods</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience with USAID and other gender and social inclusion frameworks for service delivery and policy programming a strong plus.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Skills/ Knowledge:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge or understanding of social, economic, and political context governing anti-trafficking and safe migration issues in developing countries, specifically contextualized in South Asia, and preferably in Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge of the social, psychosocial, health and economic aspects of survivor care and current survivor service providers in Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience with private sector engagement and partnerships in supply chains desirable</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent facilitation skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to work both independently and in a team</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Skilled in MS Office including Word, Excel, Outlook</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">English and Nepali language proficiency required</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Core Competencies:</strong></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Professionalism: Strong knowledge of the relevant technical areas.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Planning &amp; Organizing: Ability to plan work and manage conflicting priorities.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Communication: Excellent spoken and written communication skills, including the ability to liaise with technical staff and present information in a clear and concise style. Fluency in written in English.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Teamwork: Good interpersonal skills and ability to establish and maintain effective partnerships and working relations in a multi-cultural, multi-ethnic environment with sensitivity and respect for diversity.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Analytical skills: Ability to analyze information and solve problems with excellent attention to detail.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Women, people with disabilities and those belonging to discriminated groups are strongly encouraged to apply. All employees should adhere to USAID and Winrock International&rsquo;s code of ethics, and specifically child safeguarding and trafficking in persons provisions covered in the project agreement.<br />\r\nEEOE/AA.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>Women, people with disabilities and those belonging to discriminated groups are strongly encouraged to apply.</strong></span>&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000\">All employees must adhere to USAID and Winrock International&rsquo;s code of ethics, and specifically child safeguarding and trafficking in persons provisions covered in the project agreement.</span></div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(64, '<strong><u>Qualification:</u></strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nMinimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree/any other equivalent graduate/post graduate degree from a recognized university by Government of Nepal with at least 50% aggregate marks/3 CGPA in either Bachelor&#39;s or Master&#39;s Degree preferably in management.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Experience:</u></strong><br />\r\nPrior experience is not required but candidates having relevant experience will be preferred.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Age:</u></strong><br />\r\nNot exceeding 28 years of age as on January 9, 2019.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Other desirable competencies/qualifications:</u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must be a Nepali citizen.</li>\r\n	<li>Fluency in written and spoken English and Nepali.</li>\r\n	<li>Working knowledge of office applications.</li>\r\n	<li>Good interpersonal skills, communication skills and ability to maintain effective working relations with people.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', 'All applications and information contained within the Electronic Recruitment Application (ERA) are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature and will be treated as HIGHLY CONFIDENTIAL. The provided information&nbsp; will be strictly used for the recruitment process and will not be used to reproduce for any other process/es.'),
(59, 'A Heli service officer supports emergency care assistant. He/she after interacting with the customer, checks the availability of helicopter and doctors and acts accordingly.<br />\r\nTypical duties of the job include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>responding to emergency calls</li>\r\n	<li>assessing patients, providing emergency treatment and making diagnoses</li>\r\n	<li>monitoring and administering medication, pain relief and intravenous infusions</li>\r\n	<li>dressing wounds/injuries</li>\r\n	<li>using specialist equipment including ventilators and defibrillators</li>\r\n	<li>transporting patients to hospital and continuing to provide treatment while in transit</li>\r\n	<li>providing hospital staff with patient information including condition and treatment</li>\r\n	<li>helping provide patient care in hospitals and other medical facilities</li>\r\n	<li>communicating effectively with patients and their relatives/friends</li>\r\n	<li>teaching and training members of the public to use first aid techniques correctly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(58, '<p>A hospital accountant handles the financial aspect of a hospital. The hospital accountant oversees every area of finance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Education</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Minimum Bachelor of Science degree in accounting or finance, experience in the health care industry, as well as accounting experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Responsibilities</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Hospital accountants need to know the following responsibilities in accounting: preparing financial papers for internal and external vendors, write monthly reports to determine whether the financial information generated are accurate, perform account receivable duties and assist with preparing the hospital&rsquo;s budget.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(57, '<strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong><br />\r\nThe CFO is responsible for all the functions related to the financial operations of a hospital. These responsibilities include the accounting, insurance, financial systems, and auditing of all medical departments. CFOs gather and analyze all the financial data and information to make sure the hospital is operating within budget and to determine how to allocate funds to various areas. These officers create detailed reports of their findings and must explain to department heads and boards of directors why these financial decisions are being made. The CFO is typically a member of the senior leadership team of the hospital.<br />\r\nAdditionally, the CFO:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Is responsible for the operating and capital budgets, including revenue and expense budgets, cash forecasts, profit planning, and programs for capital investments and financing</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitates communication among staff, management, vendors, and other financial resources within the organization</li>\r\n	<li>Manages the cost-reporting process and understands financial impacts</li>\r\n	<li>Provides assistance to the organization&rsquo;s CEO, and leadership and guidance to designated departments to ensure the financial stability of the organization and that the delivery of patient/resident and healthcare service programs continues to respond to the needs of both patients and the community at-large</li>\r\n	<li>Provides guidance to capital equipment purchases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE</strong><br />\r\nCFOs of most acute care hospitals require a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in accounting, finance, or a related field. A master&rsquo;s degree in health/hospital administration, business administration, or related field is highly desirable. Hospital CFOs typically possess a minimum of 5 years of experience with increasing responsibilities for financial reporting, financial planning, and personnel management.<br />\r\n<strong>CORE COMPETENCIES AND SKILLS</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Outstanding interpersonal skills including the ability to effectively communicate with persons throughout the organization, including clinicians and governing board members</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge of the principles and skills needed to provide fiscal control for a diverse set of healthcare services</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge of systems design and development processes, including requirements analysis, feasibility studies, software design, programming, pilot testing, installation, evaluation, and operational management</li>\r\n	<li>Oversee the management and coordination of all fiscal reporting activities for the hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to link and apply complex financial instruments to business strategies</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in negotiating contracts with vendors, contractors, and others</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to analyze and resolve complex issues, both logical and interpersonal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(56, '<span style=\"font-size:12px\">&bull; Focus on identifying new business opportunities that fit the strategic direction of the Hospital, and maximizing the outcomes of those opportunities<br />\r\n&bull; Maintain extensive knowledge of current market conditions and ensure that any directly relevant information is communicated to key stakeholders<br />\r\n&bull; Develop and implement Public Relations Strategies to position the Hospital as the health care supplier of choice.<br />\r\n&bull; Develop and execute business plans<br />\r\n&bull; Develop relationships with businesses and community groups to promote the Hospital and Hospital Services<br />\r\n&bull; Develop and/or market new services of the Hospital<br />\r\n&bull; Create and be accountable for all client proposals, contracts, and associated documentation<br />\r\n&bull; Coordinate with the Corporate Marketing Team to monitor and analyze hospital media exposure.<br />\r\n&bull; Oversee the development of marketing literature, both electronic and paper based<br />\r\n&bull; Develop, draft and distribute media releases/advertisements that meet the marketing strategy of the Hospital and that comply with set policy guidelines<br />\r\n&bull; Plan and execute events (public awareness campaigns, media and publicity campaigns, staff annual function and social responsibility projects) in coordination with the Marketing Department and the Hospital Directorate<br />\r\n&bull; Ensure that budgets are prepared and managed in line with EHL standards and that cost reports are analyzed and variances clarified/reported on a monthly basis</span>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Requirements</span></strong></span></h4>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><span style=\"color:black\">&bull; Proficient in English/Nepali (speak, read, write)<br />\r\n&bull; Good computer literacy (MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Email, Internet)<br />\r\n&bull; Proven ability to build and maintain industry networks<br />\r\n&bull; Proven ability to use own initiative, and the ability to act decisively on own authority when required<br />\r\n&bull; Excellent negotiation skills and persuasiveness whilst maintaining a professional approach<br />\r\n&bull; Good communication skills, both written and verbal<br />\r\n&bull; Proven ability to both lead and work within a marketing team, and to employ both non-traditional and traditional approaches toward problem solving<br />\r\n&bull; Related managerial experience in a hospital or similar environment<br />\r\n&bull; 5 years relevant experience<br />\r\n&bull; A Degree or Diploma in Marketing or equivalent qualification as a minimum requirement</span></span><span style=\"color:black\"><!--[endif]--></span></p>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(61, 'Rolling Plans Pvt. Ltd constantly requires Roster of Domain Expert&nbsp;for multi-fucntional professional involvement and variety of functions, at different levels. The rosters are a call for applications for future fucntion- specific opportunity, determining by emerging needs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe role of professional involvement may be as consultant, Interview panelist, team member etc.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo be listed in the roster, the registration should be completed as per the need.<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 51, 204)\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:rgb(255, 0, 0)\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(60, '&nbsp;\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>NEPAL WATER FOR HEALTH</strong></span></div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n&nbsp;<strong><u>Job Position: MIS and M&amp;E Officer </u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Summary of the Position:</u></strong><br />\r\nOverall responsible for managing Monitoring &amp; Evaluation including database of all NEWAH&rsquo;s program and integration of PMIS, GIS, and Akvo Flow.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Line Manager:&nbsp; </u></strong><br />\r\nReport to the Program Manager<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Job Responsibilities:</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To keep systematic record of the progress and the development of the monitoring and evaluation data and information</li>\r\n	<li>To make regular field visit to ensure M&amp;E activities in projects level and provide support to the HQ, Province and field-based staff as per need</li>\r\n	<li>To provide professional support to headquarter and province offices M&amp;E member staff on data base</li>\r\n	<li>To collect the project completion report from province offices and HQ and update in data base</li>\r\n	<li>Integration of NEWAH databases into GIS and Akvo Flow</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and maintain database for different aspect of NEWAH and make analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct Training and orientation on the new developed databases</li>\r\n	<li>Data administrative work; assist users with access and queries to all key databases</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain file, email server and manage user access restrictions to files on file server</li>\r\n	<li>Oversee data entry and integration of data collected from field in different aspects</li>\r\n	<li>Update NEWAH website regularly with reports on NEWAH progress and important announcements and achievements as well as link with social media</li>\r\n	<li>General IT troubleshooting, make recommendations for repair</li>\r\n	<li>Manage any other specific task assigned by the line manager</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Working Condition:</u></strong><br />\r\nHeadquarter based with frequent visit to province offices and project sites<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Minimum Qualification/ Experience:&nbsp; </u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelor degree in Computer Science or similar courses with at least two (2) years of experience in similar works</li>\r\n	<li>Strong knowledge and experience on MS Office, GIS and Database</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication skill in both English and Nepali</li>\r\n	<li>Analytical skills</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Salary and Benefits:</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Starting Salary NRS 33,000.00 per Month</li>\r\n	<li>Dearness Allowance NRS 15,950.00</li>\r\n	<li>One-month Dashain Bonus of Basic salary</li>\r\n	<li>PF as per rules</li>\r\n	<li>Accidental &amp; Medical insurance as per rules.</li>\r\n	<li>Total 33 annual leave and 15 days public holiday</li>\r\n	<li>Others: AS per the rules of the organization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(70, '<strong>Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Minimum plus two/intermediate pass.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>One year of experience in office management and secreterial practice.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Knowledge of recod keeping, filing,correspondences, inventory management and public relation.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(69, '<strong>Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Bachelor in management/ HRM/Accounting/Finance/CA/ACCA or related field.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Minimum 2 years of experience in banking and financial institutions or Fin Tech Companies.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(68, '<strong>Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Bachelors in IT(especially in Fin Tech)</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Minimum 2 years of experience in banking and financial institutions or Fin Tech Companies.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(67, '<strong>Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelors in IT (especially in Fin Tech) or related field</li>\r\n	<li>Minimum 3 years of experience in managing/leading technology team or Fin Tech companies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(55, '<strong>General Manager:</strong><br />\r\nJob Summary:<br />\r\nGeneral Manager is responsible for monitoring and improving hospital performance, modernization and service improvement, co-coordinating the annual budget process, and assisting in the development of the overall site Facilities Master Plan. The position is an evolving post and the duties and responsibilities may change as the posts develop according to service needs. The post holder will be expected to participate in the Hospital on call rotation.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPerformance Management:<br />\r\n- Manage performance within the hospital ensuring achievement of agreed Key Performance Indicators, completion of Performance Books, and take corrective action when performance falls below target.<br />\r\n- Gather, analyze and use information to make service changes to enhance performance, including monitor hospital activity and reporting trends.<br />\r\n-&nbsp;Monitor monthly financial performance.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlanning and Finance:<br />\r\n- Working with the Department of Strategic Planning, develop long-term objectives that are turned into effective and affordable service development plans.<br />\r\n- In conjunction with the Management Team, develop Business Cases for consideration that have agreement from key stakeholders, are fully appraised, and offer a range of options.<br />\r\n- Ensure approved Business Cases are delivered to time and within budget.<br />\r\n<strong>Requirements</strong><br />\r\n- Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Business Administration or healthcare admin, finance or equivalent for related discipline.<br />\r\n-&nbsp;Significant Public/Private industry experience including Working at Senior Management level.<br />\r\n- Leading change projects. Working knowledge of modernization/service improvement. Managing complex financial arrangements including budget setting.<br />\r\n- Language Skills: English-fluent<br />\r\n<br />\r\nKey Competencies:<br />\r\n- Demonstrative leadership abilities.<br />\r\n- Strategic and long term planning abilities.<br />\r\n- Interpretation and interrogation of data<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(28, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Chief Financial Officer (CFO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> Financial Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> D<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Chief Financial Officer (CFO) leads the Financial Management Directorate and has overall responsibility for MCA-N financial management activities.&nbsp; The CFO reports directly to the ED/CEO of MCA-N.&nbsp; He/she manages up to 4 full-time financial management staff, overseas the external Fiscal Agent, as well as short-term consultants as required.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<u> <strong><em>Financial Management</em></strong></u><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ensures adherence to all financial management provisions of the Compact and related documents;</li>\r\n	<li>Oversees the Fiscal Agent contract to ensure that the Fiscal Agent is providing all the financial management services, such as funds control and payment processing, required in its contract and in the Fiscal Agent Agreement</li>\r\n	<li>Reviews and updates a financial management operation manual, known as the Fiscal Accountability Plan (FAP), which outlines all procedures necessary for financial management operations, documents sound internal controls, and designates the officials that have the authority to approve obligations, verify receipt of goods and services, and execute payments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u> Planning </u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In coordination with the Project/Unit Managers, estimate the future period cash flow requirements for each Project/Unit, and ensures that all accompanying reports are delivered according to the required schedule</li>\r\n	<li>Oversee automated accounting and financial management system. As necessary, manages system updates and improvements in coordination with external consultants</li>\r\n	<li>Plans and oversees audit requirements and ensures audit findings are resolved timely</li>\r\n	<li>Develops and manages all program accounting reports, including special reports required by the MCA-N or the Board of Directors and the Government of Nepal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>&nbsp; <u>&nbsp;Risk Management</u></em></strong>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Monitors and ensures compliance with all aspects of the FAP</li>\r\n	<li>Ensures that MCC funds are exempt from all taxes and refunds for taxes are paid as detailed in the Compact Agreement, Program Implementation Plan, and/or any other associated agreements</li>\r\n	<li>Supports preparation of MCA-N&rsquo;s annual Program budget for the entire Compact period, as well as detailed budgets with the Projects/Unit and any Implementing Entities</li>\r\n	<li>Monitors expenses against budgets to ensure adequate resources and control of funds. Provides quarterly contract disbursements and other necessary information to the M&amp;E Directorate in order to track process milestones for the Compact</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinates the development of quarterly disbursement requests for funding from MCC</li>\r\n	<li>Serves as liaison with the Project/Unit Managers, other personnel, and any Implementing Agencies on financial matters and issues</li>\r\n	<li>Supervises the processing and analysis of project-related expenses and ensures that they are in accordance with approved budget, MCC policies, and government procedures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<u><strong><em>Administration &amp; Operations</em></strong></u><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manages and reviews the work of related personnel and ensure quality of outputs and provide day-to-day supervision</li>\r\n	<li>Assists in matters related to office insurances, which includes assets insurance, public liability insurance, directors&rsquo; and officers&rsquo; liability insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Reviews and provides advices to contracts related to the day to day operations of MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li>Performs other tasks and special projects as assigned</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must hold Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (minimum) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Accounting, Banking &amp; Finance,&nbsp; Commerce,&nbsp; Finance, Financial Control, Chartered Accountancy Business Administration, Business Management, General Management, Economics, or in equivalent field</li>\r\n	<li>Chartered Accountant, Certified Public Accountant holding a Certified Accountancy or equivalent Financial Management certification is a plus</li>\r\n	<li>Seven (7) or more years of progressive professional experience preferred, (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in managing the corporate finance or finance function, preferably in international development, governmental organizations, or donor agencies</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to oversee and manage daily operations of a financial management unit</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to develop complex budgets and manage related financial transactions</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in developing and managing financial management processes, preferably involving development-partner assistance</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in managing balance sheets, managing costs and containing risks</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in instilling a financial discipline within the organization, while dealing complex internal and external regulations</li>\r\n	<li>Experience in the development, implementation and maintenance of automated accounting and financial management systems. Advantage for specific experience in SAP-based systems</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledgeable about taxation issues especially relevant to project development organization</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent command of English and Nepali languages, both written and spoken</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication, coordination skills, management and supervisory skills; demonstrated ability to interact and collaborate with people across departments, divisions and institutions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(66, '<strong>Requirements:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Masters degree in Finance/accounting/management/IT(especially in Fin Tech)</li>\r\n	<li>3-5 years of experience in managerial positions.</li>\r\n	<li>Good understanding of digital payments solutions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(37, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Management Specialist</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial Management</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Chief Financial Officer (CFO)</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India-helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Financial Management Specialist, under the supervision of the Chief Financial Officer, is responsible for examining the daily execution of accounting and finance transactions, monitoring the banking relationship, communicating with the fiscal agent, and serving a facilitating role in budget management and as focal point for the preparations for budgeting and auditing activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Financial Management </u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor budgets and daily cash flow ensuring that issues of overspend/underspend are anticipated and that remedial measures are raised to management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the preparation and organization of finance and accounting documentation for budgeting, reporting, and audit activities, ensuring that information is accurate and traceable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Risk Management</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review and verify a range of transactions (including disbursements, transfers, etc.) and ensure MCA-N/MCC finance and accounting guidelines are properly observed, and documentation is current and accurate to support reporting and audit activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Examine bank records/reports to determine if any inconsistencies exist and advise the CFO and MCA-N management of issues related to the banking relationships of the MCA-N</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Train MCA-N staff on the proper use of accounting forms and accomplishment of finance and accounting transactions to ensure consistent compliance with MCA-N guidelines and strengthen the transparency of the accounting function</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Administration &amp; Operation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate and maintain documentation on issues and best practices to support process improvement activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree required from a recognized institution in Accounting, Finance, Banking &amp; Finance, Commerce, Chartered Accountancy, Financial Control, or Business Administration, Business Management, Financial Engineering, Economics, General Management, , or equivalent field</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) or more years of cumulative experience preferred (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree), preferably in international development and with governmental organizations and donor agencies</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience managing financial management processes, preferably with development-partner assistance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communication, coordination skills; demonstrated ability to interact and collaborate with people across departments, divisions and institutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good command of English and Nepali languages, both written and spoken</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(42, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Environmental &amp; Social Performance (ESP) Specialist (Environment)</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines/Substations or Lead ESP Specialist/Coordinator</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description </u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Specialist, Environmental &amp; Social Performance (ESP), under the supervision of the Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines (or the Environmental Coordinator, as designated), is responsible for assisting in providing technical input to ensure the environmental and social performance of all Compact funded activities. This involves assisting the Project Manager in ensuring compliance of the Program activities with relevant national environmental and social laws and regulations, MCC Environmental Guidelines, and the International Finance Corporation (IFC) Performance Standards on Environment and Social Sustainability.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA-N Staff, MCC Staff, and other government counterparts to effectively integrate environmental and social considerations into project planning, development, and implementation, including Terms of Reference, work plans, designs, supervision contracts, budgets, timelines, and monitoring mechanisms</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate closely with all MCA-N Staff in the project team and government counterparts to ensure proper oversight of the implementation of all Compact-funded activities, including participating in field missions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and/or review, with guidance from the Quality Assurance Managers (EHS and Social) of ESP documents including, but not limited to, Environmental and Social Management System, Environmental and Social Impact Assessments and Management Plans, Resettlement Action Plans, Stakeholder Engagement Plans, etc., and under the guidance of the Project Manager, ensure the dissemination and implementation of these tools to improve environmental and social performance on Compact activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the adherence of the project team and implementing partners to ESP plans and schedules across different project stages, to ensure efficient implementation of ESP elements and strengthen quality of ESP outputs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains documentation and databases related to ESP information to support reporting and communications activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social Science, Sociology, Social Work, Community Development, Development Economics, Political Science, Environmental Science, Environmental Studies, Environmental Engineering, Environmental Planning, Environmental Management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years cumulative experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in environmental and social impact assessment on projects of a similar nature</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with international environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(82, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Sales and Marketing Head&nbsp;&nbsp; -1</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Job Summary:</strong><br />\r\n			We are currently seeking an ambitious and highly-skilled sales and marketing manager with a track record of exceptional, transformative management practices. In this role, you will increase productivity, inspire and motivate junior employees, and optimize our company&rsquo;s market share. You will have tremendous opportunities to develop innovative policies and campaigns that shape the future of our organization. Candidates for this role will be creative, charismatic, knowledgeable, and exceptionally well-versed in the latest sales and marketing techniques as well as tried-and-true practices.<br />\r\n			<strong>Salary: Negotiable </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Sales and Marketing Head Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee day-to-day sales ensuring team being on track for achieving KPI&rsquo;s, monitoring, and forecasting to better understand the market</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Continually assess our marketing techniques and their efficacy in affecting sales</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Stay up-to-date on current market trends</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work collaboratively with the sales team to assess current projections</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Own ultimate responsibility for successfully meeting or exceeding sales goals</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Collaborate with marketing team to creatively reach more potential customers</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take calculated risks to increase profitability and brand recognition</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work in a hands-on fashion, building the team&mdash;provide motivation and inspiration</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Set the precedent for excellence through leading by example</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Cultivate and deepen client relationships and partnerships that add value</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Background of the Sales and Marketing Head:</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">All round sales and marketing experience gained from a similar sized organization.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent motivational and leadership skills to inspire performance.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Relevant industry experience ideally from a competitor.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Highly motivated with a genuine drive to succeed.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Sales and Marketing Head Requirements and Qualifications</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in business or related field</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">5+ years&rsquo; experience in management in a corporate setting</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Transformative approach to leadership that inspires and empowers others</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Aware of the latest market trends and shifts, as well as projections for the future</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Evidence of ability to innovate and implement change successfully</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Exceptional communication and presentation skills</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Able to be persuasive and procure buy-in from upper management</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Solid computer skills and awareness of web-based marketing and social media</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Driven and committed to success while maintaining integrity</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(72, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">HR officer should maintain employee relations, careers coaching, health and safety and headhunting and should look after the health, safety and welfare of all employees. Organizing staff training sessions and activities.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Preparing regular financial and administrative reports.</li>\r\n	<li>Administration of company databases.</li>\r\n	<li>Manage office stock and place orders.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare regular reports on expenses and office budgets.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and update company databases.</li>\r\n	<li>Organize a filing system for important and confidential company documents.</li>\r\n	<li>Monitoring and maintaining office equipment, inventory supplies; orders replacement supplies as needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Answer queries by employees.</li>\r\n	<li>Update office policies as needed.</li>\r\n	<li>Administer employee services.</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate and supervise the work of specialists and support staff.</li>\r\n	<li>Oversee an organization&rsquo;s recruitment, interview, selection, and hiring processes.</li>\r\n	<li>Handle staffing issues, such as mediating disputes and directing disciplinary procedures.</li>\r\n	<li>Link an organization&#39;s management with its employees.</li>\r\n	<li>Administer employee service.</li>\r\n	<li>Formulation and Implementation of HR policies or procedures.</li>\r\n	<li>Formulating &amp; implementing monetary evaluation system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(79, '<div>\r\n<hr /></div>\r\nA Client Relationship Officer is involved in building and maintaining relationships with clients and key personnel within customer companies.\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must have excellent communication skills</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to manage a varied workload to achieve priorities and objectives</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent Command in English and Nepali (Speaking, Reading, Writing)</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft Application Skills (Word, Excel, PPT, Internet)</li>\r\n	<li>Highly Skilled in Customer Services</li>\r\n	<li>Should have good knowledge and skill to deal with corporate houses.</li>\r\n	<li>Effective Teamworking Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Experience on tv channel is preferred</li>\r\n	<li>Should be flexible in the rotation system of working days</li>\r\n	<li>Freshers may apply&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Deliver a high-quality client service and customer retention approach to managing client relationships to enhance product sales and new client growth targets</li>\r\n	<li>Handling queries of customers over the phone, through emails, or through online chat services on time with effective way</li>\r\n	<li>Respond to emails and letters from customers regarding queries, in a timely manner</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the professional relationship with customer</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate with the back-end Customer Care team for seeking information on the issues faced and inform the customer on same Coordinate and follow-up with other internal Departments, if required, for obtaining relevant information for resolution of queries of customers.</li>\r\n	<li>Create and Manage the professional relationship with customer and corporate houses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(78, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position Responsibilities:</strong><br />\r\nMaster Control Operator is responsible for monitoring the quality and accuracy of our on-air signals as well as ensuring the transmission meets government regulations and the station&rsquo;s high standards. Additional responsibilities include troubleshooting equipment malfunctions and preparing programming for play out.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Duties will include, but are not limited to:</strong><br />\r\n&middot; Perform on-air switching for live events<br />\r\n&middot; Operate recording hardware, satellite receivers and computer based systems<br />\r\n&middot; Prepare and check material for on-air playback via automation system<br />\r\n&middot; Verify all material airing by referencing program logs<br />\r\n&middot; Monitor on-air signals for quality control<br />\r\n&middot; Monitor transmitter and tower lights accurately to meet FCC regulations<br />\r\n&middot; Anticipate and troubleshoot issues when they occur<br />\r\n&middot; Perform other duties as assigned<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(77, '<strong>Program Presenters</strong> act as the public face (or voice) on <strong>television</strong> and radio programs; they are responsible for introducing and interviewing guests, linking segments, and generally holding the show together.The role is to entertain and inform the audience by presenting information or entertainment in an accessible and attractive way. Should introduce, host (or co-host) a programme, create links between items, introduce and interview guests and interact with the audience. The exact nature of the job may vary according to a programme&#39;s subject matter, for example, if it covers news, weather, sport, music or lifestyle.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ability to imagine &amp; direct TV programmes.</li>\r\n	<li>Well-groomed appearance, articulate speech patterns and the ability to create a person that resonates with audiences.</li>\r\n	<li>Writing and rehearsing scripts.</li>\r\n	<li>Research and interviewing skills, and inquisitive nature.</li>\r\n	<li>Undertaking relevant background research.</li>\r\n	<li>Interviewing guests via the telephone or in person.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(76, 'News reader should be able to use their public speaking skills to accurately and concisely deliver the news to their audience.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Research local community, state, national and international current events.</li>\r\n	<li>Collaborate with the news director to choose stories to broadcast considering audience preferences.</li>\r\n	<li>Organize the news to present the most interesting pieces first.</li>\r\n	<li>Revise scripts and prepare to deliver them on-air.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure late-breaking news is added to newscasts.</li>\r\n	<li>Engage in commentary.</li>\r\n	<li>Introduce news correspondents reporting on scene and ask them relevant questions.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep abreast of news developments by studying papers, attending events, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Stay in contact with industry professionals.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Keep a clear, pleasant speaking voice and nice appearance, good grooming and hygiene practices are essential.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(75, 'Graphic designers create visual concepts, by hand or using computer software, to communicate ideas that inspire, inform, or captivate consumers. They develop the overall layout and production design for advertisements, brochures, magazines, and corporate reports.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cultivate a solid body of work.</li>\r\n	<li>Take the design &ldquo;brief&rdquo; to record requirements and client&rsquo;s needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Schedule project implementation and define budget constraints.</li>\r\n	<li>Work on various marketing and promotional materials such as flyers, logos, and corporate identity including website art work, booklets, newsletters and more.</li>\r\n	<li>Work with a wide range of media and use graphic design software</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare rough drafts and present your ideas.</li>\r\n	<li>Amend final designs to clients&rsquo; comments and gain full approval.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(74, 'A reporter researches, investigates and presents news on current affairs content for <strong>television</strong> through various sources.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp;News Reporter Duties and Responsibilities&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nTo accomplish their primary goal of broadcasting current and accurate information to consumers, News Reporters perform many tasks. We analyzed several job listings to identify these core News Reporter duties and responsibilities.<br />\r\n<strong><u>Gather and Write News</u></strong><br />\r\nNews Reporters collect information on assigned topics to report accurate and timely news. They talk to sources, follow-up on leads, and do research to be as well informed as possible. They fact-check their findings, then write them up in an article for printing or a script to be read on-air.<br />\r\n<strong><u>Report On-Air</u></strong><br />\r\nIn broadcasting, News Reporters are filmed or recorded presenting the news. They may be recorded in a studio or in the field, depending on the story. They usually read off of a script, but also must be knowledgeable about the topic that they are reporting on.<br />\r\n<strong><u>Conduct Interviews</u></strong><br />\r\nA key component of a News Reporter&rsquo;s job is to conduct interviews. These may be broadcast live, or pre-recorded and edited. The News Reporter must have done research in advance and be prepared to to ask pointed and interesting question of the interview subject.<br />\r\n<strong><u>Generate Stories</u></strong><br />\r\nNews Reporters are tasked with generating new and interesting news stories to cover. They must always be looking for unique, relevant and urgent topics to bring to the public, and investigating interesting new angles of stories that have already been covered.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>News Reporter Skills</strong><br />\r\nInquisitive, outgoing and driven, successful News Reporters are curious to find out as much as they can about any given topic and share it with the public. They are driven and persistent, and have excellent interpersonal skills and strong ethics. In addition to these general skills and personality traits, employers are seeking News Reporter candidates with the following skills.<br />\r\n<strong>Core skills</strong>: Based on job listings we looked at, employers want News Reporters with these core skills. If you want to work as a News Reporter, focus on the following.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strong writing skills, and ability to convey information in a clear, concise and conversational manner</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent live reporting skills and strong on-camera presentation skills</li>\r\n	<li>Able to work a flexible schedule, including nights and weekends</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to interact professionally and build relationships and sources</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to shoot and edit digital video</li>\r\n	<li>Strong research skills, including the ability to navigate online search engines</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent understanding of Associated Press style</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(73, '<span style=\"font-family:calibri,sans-serif; font-size:11.0pt\">A <strong>cameraman</strong> is responsible for recording shots for a variety of film and broadcast purposes. They use technical aspects of lenses, filters, zooms and other camera settings to capture scenes to the liking of clients and film directors.</span> The role of a cameraman is to do more than just silently stand behind the camera and record things for posterity. Cameramen provide expertise and knowledge that enable directors, editors and producers to present &quot;stories&quot; visually. Cameramen are also known as camera operators or videographers, depending on the work context and job duties. Camerapersons work with the director, actors and other professionals to get the best creative shots.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Responsible for capturing all the correct footage and angles for TV shows, news &nbsp;&nbsp;broadcasts, live events, interviews, and other important occasions.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure that lenses and camera angles are appropriate.</li>\r\n	<li>Read charts and compute ratios to determine variables such as lighting, shutter angles, filter factors, and camera distances.</li>\r\n	<li>Set up cameras, optical printers, and related equipment to produce photographs and special effects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', ''),
(71, 'Visual engineers set up, operate, maintain and repair equipment used to enhance live events, such as microphones, video recorders, projectors, lighting and sound mixing equipment. They record meetings and presentations with video cameras, operate spotlights, adjust amplifiers, coordinate graphics used in displays and provide technical support for teleconferences, webinars and distance-learning classes. Technicians may also edit, copy and store videotapes and DVDs, track inventory of equipment and order supplies.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Monitor and troubleshoot television services, broadcast equipment and RF system.</li>\r\n	<li>Analyzing technical faults on equipment and system.</li>\r\n	<li>Minimizing loss of services when equipment fails by quickly identifying and implementing an alternative method of service provision.</li>\r\n	<li>Implementing request from supervisors and colleagues inside the department practice.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Communicating effectively and sharing information with members of the team.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Service and package testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(81, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Desk Editor- 12</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">A desk editor, also known as an assignment editor, manages and delegates the coverage of news items for print, broadcast, or online news media. Desk editors monitor wire services, police scanners, newsroom telephones, and Internet sources to gather leads on possible news stories.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Requirements:</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">Education: Intermediate</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">Industry: Television Media</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">Salary: Negotiable</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Job description:</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should be able in providing the community with accurate and relevant news coverage</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should be able to assign coverage to reporters, writers, photographers, and other news team members, working quickly to ensure that they will be able to meet deadlines.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should monitor the status of news teams and coordinate the coverage of multiple stories at once, which requires organization and management skills.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">As the publication or broadcast deadline nears, desk editors at print outlets should be able to edit and review completed work, check for accuracy, select photographs, and correct errors.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Desk editors at broadcast news outlets may need to write stories, edit video, and check facts with sources. They make decisions regarding the final layout or content of the publication or broadcast, adding or dropping material as needed.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(83, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:29px; text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Sales and Marketing executive &ndash; 2 </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Job Purpose:</strong><br />\r\n			Provides first-class service in order to push the sales of a certain product. Acts as an intermediary between producers and clientele. Makes necessary phone calls and meetings to help sales. Allows people to make inquiries as necessary.<br />\r\n			<strong>Salary: Negotiable</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><strong>Sales and Marketing Job Duties:</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engages in superior customer service by making information readily available</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Persists in sales even in the face of failure</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrates products and services as deemed necessary by clients and management</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Schedules appointments and meetings as necessary</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Answers questions from clients</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Makes product knowledge readily available to self and other sales people through various resources</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Finds ways to sell products in the face of a down market</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Researches client base to find new types of customers and sells to them accordingly</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Creates a plan for gaining customers and then retaining them based on warranties or guarantees</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Analyzes and creates a plan for engaging the target market</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Analyzes the competition to create a plan for engagement</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Makes product appeal to the target market</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Trains other sales people in the art of selling</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Makes sure that all salespeople meet quota during a given period</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sets up booths at trade shows and demonstrates the quality or uses of a product</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:638px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrates superior time management skills and meets sales deadlines</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\"><br />\r\n			<strong>Sales and Marketing Skills and Qualifications:</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">Superior Written and Verbal Communication Skills, Math Skills, Product Knowledge, Creativity, Demonstrated Experience, Courteous, Basic Computer Literacy, Microsoft Office, Database Skills, Business, Accounting, Marketing, Finance, Target Market Analysis, Presentation Skills, Persistent, Flexible</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(65, 'This is an invitation to all the vendors of various areas of specialization who are eager to offer their&nbsp;products and services&nbsp;to get listed with Rolling Plans Pvt. Ltd.', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:rgb(0, 51, 204)\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;'),
(31, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Deputy Executive Director (DED) / Deputy CEO (DCEO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> Project Delivery<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> E<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u> </strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nAs a member of MCA-N Senior Management Team, the Deputy Executive Director/Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO) for Project Delivery will be responsible for leadership and management of MCA-N staff implementing the Electricity Transmission Project (ETP) and Transportation Project on the Nepal Compact. The Deputy Executive Director will also provide guidance and support to the Executive Director /Chief Executive Officer (ED/CEO) on the execution of Compact projects and cross-cutting sector activities, and to ensure sound coordination and project management in achieving Compact targets. The incumbent will ensure that appropriate resources, and MCA-N internal policies, are aligned with the achievement of work plans within agreed-upon time lines and budgets.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversees and leads Project Managers and Quality Assurance Managers responsible for multi-disciplinary teams implementing the Electricity Transmission Project (ETP) and the Transportation Project to achieve all Compact goals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advises and oversees Project Managers and Quality Assurance Managers to undertake all project management tasks including financial management through developing and monitoring budget and implementing quarterly fund disbursement processes; procuring and managing consultants and works contractors ; developing and managing work plans ; and establishing and monitoring quality assurance and control frameworks</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Leads and ensures appropriate progress, coordination, collaboration and synergy with the ED/CEO and DED of Management to ensure exchange of relevant information, and to identify issues and risks, assess impacts and develop mitigation strategies &nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Through coordination with ED/CEO and DED/DCEO for Management, ensures that MCA-N resources required for the ETP and Transport Project are available and applied in order to achieve project goals;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with Project Managers and Quality Assurance Managers, builds the ETP and Transport Project teams through recruitment, training and development, and performance management of staff to ensure a capacity to deliver the Projects&rsquo; objectives</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Makes recommendations and provides strategic guidance for the projects and cross cutting sectors development and implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Leads and maintains regular communications and good partnership with MCC to support projects operation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensures continuous improvement of projects and implementation efficiency in the Project Delivery team</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Leads in formulating, coordinating, and recommending of issues to address to the Board of Directors, which includes preparation of the implementation plan, budget, Compact program activities, and subsequently, and through the ED, endorses these to the Board of Directors for its approval&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provides oversight and works closely with Project Managers and Quality Assurance Managers to ensure compliance with MCC, Government of Nepal and other relevant guidelines and procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Leads and be responsible for coordinating the preparation of periodic reports related to the ETP and Transportation Project that are required by MCC and the Board of Directors</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the Executive Director in representing the MCA-N and its Compact program to the Nepali public and MCA-N&rsquo;s partners/stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">May act as officer-in-charge in the absence of the ED/CEO; and</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Performs other tasks and special projects as assigned by the ED/CEO</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree</strong> preferred from a recognized institution in one of the following or equivalent fields: Electrical Engineering, Electrical Power Engineering, Electronics Engineering, Civil Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experienced senior manager with proven record including <strong>at least 10 years&rsquo;</strong> cumulative experience (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s degree) in project/program development and implementation. Internationally-recognized project management credentials would be an advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience with technical infrastructure development projects in electricity or transportation sectors is required, with <strong>overall budget of at least US$ 20 million</strong> and <strong>at least fifteen (15) personnel management</strong></li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum 10 years&rsquo; demonstrated cumulative experience (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s degree) building teams and managing staff to ensure effective project implementation. Managing a team of project managers who in turn manage multi-dimensional projects, manage consultants and construction contractors, and prepare reports and performance reviews on a regular basis</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated project management experience and proven management skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with donor-funded development projects in Nepal or another similar developing country is an advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven record in high level facilitation and negotiation and experienced developing and preparing strategies and in their implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity or experience with monitoring and evaluation, environment and social performance or gender development. Capable of building and maintaining productive relationships with a range of stakeholders, including Government officials, communities, NGOs, education institutions, private sectors and international donors</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent command of English and Nepali, both written and spoken, is essential</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good information technology skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven coordination and management skills and experience, especially in projects with multi-disciplinary components</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent strategic thinking, facilitation and negotiation skills</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Has high integrity and exercises good judgement</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, and demonstrated ability to effectively interact and collaborate with people in multidisciplinary teams as well as work across departments, divisions and institutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Has capability to be flexible to respond to changing requirements</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Values the continuous improvement and learning, and committed to mentoring and coaching</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Is results-focused</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n'),
(32, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Information Technology (IT) Specialist-Software &amp; Hardware<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> IT<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Manager, Administration and Human Resources<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> C<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u> </strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe IT Specialist, under the supervision of the Manager, Administration and Human Resources, is responsible for the delivery and implementation of Information Technology (IT)-related services to include network management and data infrastructure oversight, ensuring that services rendered support the work of the MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u> </strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee delivery of various IT services (e.g. infrastructure maintenance, database management, etc.) across the MCA-N, ensuring that the quality of execution meets organization needs and established IT standards</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise management on overall issues regarding day-to-day IT operations and provide inputs to improve delivery and efficiency of services rendered</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide recommendations on software and hardware developments or upgrades for organization use in support of increased efficiency and productivity of wider program deliverables</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop regular testing, update, and maintenance schedule for IT infrastructure to ensure continuity of functionality and capacity to service the needs of the MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assess existing procedures/protocols to incorporate improvements based on user feedback to facilitate seamless delivery of services</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fulfill the following tasks (some of them being covered and added in the future IT Scope of Work)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide new starters with IT equipment set up to their needs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage and maintain MCA-N official website</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage the networks across all sites</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage network prioritization due to limited bandwidth</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and put in place sound back-up systems</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and enforce various IT policies (setting up e-mails, use of internet, accounts delection, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide resolution to IT issues (repairs and maintenance)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain confidentiality, privacy and integrity of IT infrastructure through cybersecurity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support procurement in gaining new hardware and also provide maintenance and updates to ensure smooth running of IT systems</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (Required) from a recognized institution in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Electronic &amp; Communications Engineering, Mathematics, Computational Mathematics, and Business Information System or equivalent fields</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Significant prior experience in the provision of IT services</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years of experience or more preferred (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s degree), managing IT infrastructure, systems and solutions in an environment with 10 or more staff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n'),
(33, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position: Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nDivision: Project Delivery<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nReports to: Deputy Executive Director (DED) for Project Delivery<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nBand: D</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Transmission Lines Manager is responsible for achieving the delivery of the Transmission Lines Activity of the Electricity Transmission Project (ETP) through management of an integrated team of technical experts. The Manager will employ rigorous contract and project management techniques to ensure implementation of the Transmission Lines Activity on time and within budget while complying with all relevant policies and standards.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong><em>Operations </em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure integration of all relevant technical requirements in implementing through Transmission Line Activity through management of multidisciplinary team of experts including engineers and environmental, social, health &amp; safety, and resettlement experts</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the ETP Transmission Line Activity team to implementing the Activity across all project requirements and ensure that these are aligned to the established strategies, frameworks, budgets and resources defined by the Compact</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Secure and integrate support from other MCA-N departments including procurement, fiscal management, monitoring &amp; evaluation, and communications, to ensure timely and effective contracting, management, and monitoring processes for the Transmission Line Activity; Lead the Transmission Line Activity team in securing and overseeing high-quality contractors by developing comprehensive scoping documents; preparing tender documents; conducting high-quality procurements; and implementing robust contract management procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the ETP Transmission Line Activity as an integrated component of the Country MCA-N program to project stakeholders (e.g., with national/local government counterparts, civil society, project beneficiaries, etc.) ensuring that collaborative relationships are built and maintained to facilitate the delivery of the program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp; Planning </em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee development and application of critical project management tools to support the implementation of the Transmission Line Activity including work plans for schedule control, Quality Assurance/Quality Control (QA/QC) and change management plans, risk management tools, contract administration tools, budget and contingency management tools, and others as required</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Guide ETP Transmission Line Activity team to ensure the use of resources and the implementation of project activities are aligned to the overall project plan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Evaluate ETP Transmission Line Activity components and activities as these are developed to ensure their relevance to the country context and ensure that these adapted to address requirements on the ground. Establish and implement framework to ensure successful management of the Activity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide MCA-N leadership with consistent progress updates and risk analysis to ensure timely and effective organizational action to advance the goals of the Transmission Lines Activity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em>Recruitment &amp; Staffing</em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Build the ETP Transmission Line Activity team through recruitment, training and development, and performance management of staff to ensure a capacity to deliver the project&rsquo;s objectives</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required), and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields:&nbsp; Electrical Engineering, Electrical Power Engineering, Electronics Engineering, Civil Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Formal training in Project Management preferred (e.g., certified Project Management Professional)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ten (10) years of experience preferred (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in implementing infrastructure projects in Nepal or similar environments (especially South Asia), with responsibilities including all phases of procurement (e.g., preparation of terms of reference, evaluation, award, etc.), contractor management, contract and budget management, and broad stakeholder engagement requirements; preference will be given to prior experience in transmission lines of at least 132 KV in capacity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ten (10) years of experience preferred (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in managing teams, especially in a project-based or matrixed organization such as a consulting firm, with demonstrated ability to ensure integration of multiple work streams to achieve project goals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred; completed projects references will be given additional advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical background in energy infrastructure, environmental management, resettlement and land acquisition, or other topical areas is preferred</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(35, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quality Assurance Manager (Social Inclusion &amp; Resettlement) </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Deputy Executive Director (DED) for Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;D</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India-helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Quality Assurance Manager (Social Inclusion &amp; Resettlement) monitors and strategically manages to achieve dual objectives: (i) gender and social inclusion into compact projects and activities&nbsp; in line with MCC Gender Policy and Operational Requirements and (ii) resettlement&nbsp; for all Compact funded activities to ensure compliance of all Program activities with relevant national environmental and social laws and regulations, MCC Environmental Guidelines, and the International Finance Corporation (IFC) Performance Standards on Environment and Social Sustainability. The Quality Assurance Manager (Social Inclusion) achieves these objectives by advising the Deputy Executive Director of Project Delivery on the performance of each Project Manager, coordinating with the Gender and Social Inclusion and Environment and Social Performance experts in each project teams and, where necessary, providing technical guidance for MCA-N team members to fulfill their respective role.&nbsp; The Quality Assurance Manager (Social Inclusion) will equally divide his/her between tasks necessary to fulfill all gender, social inclusion and resettlement responsibilities (i.e., 50 percent for each mentioned objective).<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Deputy Executive Director of Project Delivery on social and gender inclusion performance of each project through ongoing communication, coordination, reporting, oversight and, where necessary, providing recommended corrective actions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA-N Environmental Social Performance (ESP) and GSI staff through regular meetings and discussions to provide updates, monitor progress, identify challenges/opportunities and provided practical advice and solutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA-N/MCC Staff, and other government counterparts to effectively integrate social inclusion considerations into project planning, development, and implementation, including Terms of Reference, work plans, designs, supervision contracts, budgets, timelines, and monitoring mechanisms</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Serve as the main counterpart to MCA/MCC GSI and ESP (Environmental Social Performance) Staff, and other government counterparts and stakeholders on all (i) resettlement and (ii) gender and social inclusion in compact projects and activities issues on Compact activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Deputy Executive Director and Project Managers to build the Electricity Transmission Project (ETP) team through recruitment, training, development and mentoring, and performance management of staff to ensure a capacity to deliver the project&rsquo;s objectives</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review key resettlement documents including but not limited to, Resettlement Action Plans, Stakeholder Engagement Plans, etc., and ensure the dissemination and implementation of these tools to improve environmental and social performance on Compact activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review key GSI documents including but not limited to Social and Gender Integration Plan (SGIP) and its revision; Social and Gender Training modules and materials and other relevant tools for improving GSI performance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and implement a quality control framework to monitor and strategically manage the (i) resettlement and (ii) gender and social inclusion (GSI) performance of each Project</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide intellectual and technical leadership and support to MCA-N project staff in general and GSI staff in particular in strengthening their capacity in current GSI approaches, strategies and tools for effectively integrating gender and social into compact projects and activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate closely with all MCA-N Staff and government counterparts to ensure proper oversight of the implementation of all Compact-funded activities, including participating in field missions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Social Science, Sociology, Social Work, Gender Studies, Community Development, Development Economics, Political Science, Environmental Science, Environmental Studies, Environmental Engineering, Environmental Planning, Environmental Management, Engineering</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">10 years of cumulative experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in social inclusion and resettlement work with infrastructure focused projects preferably in power sector</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Managing projects of similar size, including preparing Terms of references for hiring consultants (designers, advisors, program managers), and construction contractors, preparing budgets for their hiring, managing budgets for social inclusion activities, evaluating the procurement processes, negotiating and awarding the contracts, and managing the hired consultants and contractors for a timely and quality implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred; completed projects references will be given additional advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in resettlement, and social impact assessment, especially where integrated with environmental or other social considerations in infrastructure projects, or projects of a similar nature</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in gender and social inclusion and social impact assessment of infrastructure projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability in working with multi-disciplinary team and perform in oversight capacity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with international resettlement, environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills (MS office, MS Project). HDM4 experience is advantageous</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(36, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quality Assurance Manager (Environmental, Health &amp; Safety)</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Deputy Executive Director for Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;D</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India-helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Quality Assurance Manager (Environmental, Health and Safety) monitors and strategically manages environmental, health and safety performance of all Compact funded activities to ensure compliance of all Program activities with relevant national environmental and social laws and regulations, MCC Environmental Guidelines, and the International Finance Corporation (IFC) Performance Standards on Environment and Social Sustainability. The EHS Quality Assurance Manager achieves this objective by advising the Deputy Executive Director of Project Delivery on the performance of each Project Manager and their respective teams and, where necessary, providing technical guidance for EHS team members to fulfill their respective role.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Deputy Executive Director of Project Delivery on environmental, health and safety performance on each project and Project Manager through ongoing communication, coordination, reporting and, where necessary, providing recommended corrective actions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Deputy Executive Director and Project Managers to build the Electrical Transmission Project (ETP) team through recruitment, training, development and mentoring, and performance management of staff to ensure a capacity to deliver the project&rsquo;s objectives</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Serve as the main counterpart to MCA-N Staff, MCC Staff, and other government counterparts and stakeholders on all Environmental and Social Performance issues on Compact activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and implement a quality control framework to monitor and strategically manage the environmental, health and safety performance of each Project Manager and their projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA-N Staff, MCC Staff, and other government counterparts to effectively integrate environmental, health and safety considerations into project planning, development, and implementation, including Terms of Reference, work plans, designs, supervision contracts, budgets, timelines, and monitoring mechanisms</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate closely with all MCA-N Staff and government counterparts to ensure proper oversight of the implementation of all Compact-funded activities, including participating in field missions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review key Environmental Social Performance (ESP) documents including, but not limited to, Environmental and Social Management System, Environmental and Social Impact Assessments and Management Plans, Resettlement Action Plans, Stakeholder Engagement Plans, etc., and ensure the dissemination and implementation of these tools to improve environmental and social performance on Compact activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social Science, Sociology, Social Work, Community Development, Development Economics, Political Science, Environmental Science, Environmental Studies, Environmental Engineering, Environmental Planning, Environmental Management, Public Health, Public Policy, International Development, Development Economics</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">10 years of experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in environmental, safety or health initiatives</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in environmental and social impact assessment and in leading efforts to integrate environmental and social considerations into infrastructure projects, or projects of a similar nature</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Managing projects of similar size, including preparing Terms of reference for hiring consultants (designers, advisors, program managers), and construction contractors, preparing budgets for their hiring, managing budgets for environmental and social impact activities, evaluating the procurement processes, negotiating and awarding the contracts, and managing the hired consultants and contractors for a timely and quality implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred; completed projects references will be given additional advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with international environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(39, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manager - Program Procurement&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Management</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Deputy Executive Director/Deputy Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO) for Management</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;D</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></em></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Position Objective</u></em></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Manager - Program Procurement, under the supervision of the Deputy Executive Director/Deputy Chief Executive Officer (DED/ DCEO) for Management, is responsible for overseeing the delivery and implementation of procurement-related services that include resource acquisition, inventory management, and stock quality control of goods and services relevant to wider organization programs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations </u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manages and oversees all procurement operations and the performance of the Procurement Agent(s). Manages the flow of procurement activity to implement the Compact</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensures that all procurement transactions are implemented in accordance with the MCC Program Procurement Guidelines</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Works closely with the management and the ED/CEO of MCA-N to maintain the integrity and confidentiality of the procurement process</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Works closely with the Procurement Agent(s) and serves as the primary liaison between the Procurement Agent(s), MCC, and outside entities from a variety of specialized sectors on all procurement activities and facilitates the smooth interplay between and among all elements of the procurement process</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Translates program requirements into actionable procurement packages and requisitions, in coordination with the Project Managers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Plans, organizes, and guides the PA in conducting market/industry outreach activities and analyzes market conditions in order to inform the packaging of project objectives into procurable requirements, promote competition, and optimize the likelihood of success of the resulting procurement activity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinates the functions of MCA-N and the Procurement Agent(s) in implementing the Compact program, including identifying initial procurement needs and organizing procurement operations</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Facilitates the preparation and submission to the Procurement Agent(s) of necessary procurement documents (requisition, Terms of Reference, estimated budgets etc.) provided by the technical staff of MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensures that the solicitation documents, Procurement Plans, Procurement Implementation Plans, and all other required documents prepared by the Procurement Agent(s) and comply with the MCC Program Procurement Guidelines and Standard Bidding Documents, and they meet the procurement needs of MCA-N and follow the Procurement Operations Manual and other relevant templates of MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establishes and communicates procurement priorities to Procurement Agent(s), in consultation with the MCA-N management and Project Managers</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensures that the Procurement Agent acts consistently with the approved Procurement Operations Manual;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Actively monitors and manages the progress of procurements against the applicable Procurement Implementation Plan. Coordinates with MCA-N management and project staff to ensure everyone understands their respective roles and responsibilities in the execution of procurements, appreciates the critical nature of their responsibilities and are aware of the serious consequences of missed deadlines and unacceptable inputs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Regularly reviews MCA-N&rsquo;s Procurement Operations Manual(s) and Contract Administration Manual(s) prepared by the Procurement Agent(s) and recommends any necessary changes or improvements to ensure it responds to the operational reality of MCA</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Leads, guides, and manages the members of the MCA-N procurement team. Manages and reviews the work of the MCA-N procurement team to ensure quality of outputs, and provides day-to-day supervision of MCA-N procurement unit staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approves procurement decisions in accordance with Attachment 1 to the MCC Program Procurement Guidelines within the approval thresholds and reviews those that require MCC and the MCA-N Governing Body approval prior to submission to these entities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists Project Managers, and Legal Counsel in interpreting and applying various contractual provisions, in particular with respect to claims from contractors for time extensions or extra payments, and in general with respect to the contractors&rsquo; and consultants&rsquo; conformance and compliance with contractual obligations</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversees, in coordination with Project Directors and Project Managers, the contract amendment/modification process and ensures that the approval authorities in Attachment 1 of the MCC Program Procurement Guidelines are adhered to in this regard</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develops and applies fraud and corruption awareness and anti-fraud and corruption measures, with emphasis on the procurement and contract execution processes, in collaboration with the Procurement Officers, Procurement Agent(s), Project Directors, Project Managers, the fiscal team, and the MCA-N legal team</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In consultation with the MCA-N Management and legal Counsel ensures the development of the MCA-N specific Bid Challenge System in accordance with the appropriate MCC guidelines</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Participates in the review of the Bid Challenges received from aggrieved bidders in accordance with the MCC approved Bid Challenge System (BCS)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In consultation with the MCA-N Project Managers, ensures that the Contract Administration and Management Manual (CAMM) is generated and agreed in good time before the contract administration process and management period begins</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Reviews reports submitted by the Procurement Agent(s)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensures that the Procurement Agent keeps records of all procurement activities during the procurement phase and also during the Contract Administration phase</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Mandatory requirements:</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Procurement, Business Administration, Business Management, Law, Contract Law, Contract Management, Supply Chain Management, Logistics, Economics, Engineering</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum seven (7) years of cumulative experience (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in senior position(s) or in senior advisory role(s) in the management of project(s) that required procurement of goods, works and services (a written test to gauge procurement knowledge may be given to short-listed candidates)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience drafting, reviewing, and approving procurement documents</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge of or experience with procurement policies of World Bank, Asian Development Bank, MCC (or other international donor institutions)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated abilities to coordinate teams; prioritize tasks; and monitor performance against schedule and KPIs for own team and for contractors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated track record of delivering high quality outcomes/projects on time and within budget</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven capacity to work with a minimum of supervision and make independent assessments and decisions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in English</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills with office productivity applications (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, MS Project)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Preferred requirements:</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in management of similar projects preferably at the enterprise or organization level</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Dynamic, solution-driven, proactive personality (reference checks required)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with the energy sector</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Working in or managing multidisciplinary teams across different departments or functional areas</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience with planning and organizing market outreach events, speaking to audiences</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Supervision of construction and/or consulting contracts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(40, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Manager- Road Maintenance &amp; Technical Assistance</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Deputy Executive Director/Deputy Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO) for Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo ensure the timely and efficient implementation of the Road Maintenance Project (the Project), the Manager&nbsp; &ndash; Road Maintenance will oversee the project&rsquo;s activities involving (i) Technical Assistance and (ii) Strategic Road Maintenance Works as set forth in the Compact and manage communications around their development, implementation and completion.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe sub-activities of the Road Maintenance Project, for which the Project Manager is expected to be responsible include the following:</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Technical Assistance Activity:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Improved data collection and techniques</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Preparation of appropriate road maintenance plans driven by economic justification</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Improved prioritization of periodic maintenance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Improved contracting and contracting management, including improved road safety features</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Improved project management</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Strategic Road Maintenance Works:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Pavement Recycling Pilot Program</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Matching Fund to finance periodic maintenance works</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Road Maintenance Manager Responsibilities:</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage and deliver all activities related to the Road Project as described above</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate and provide needed information in a timely manner with the MCA-N team, relevant Implementing Entities, and other cooperating partners, to execute the activities for the Project under the Program Implementation Agreement</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure stakeholder participation in Project implementation and represent MCA-N in public forums with respect to the Project</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure and Approve all relevant project management tools, including but not limited to, are developed and updated in a timely manner: work plans (schedules), procurement plans, detailed financial plans (budgets), risk management plans and scoping documents (activity descriptions, terms of references, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Development of a pilot pavement recycling program for potential integration into the works projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure annual data collection of IRI, SDI and Deflections on the SRN per the Compact and provide necessary remediation measures if needed to ensure GoN compliance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Recruit and manage consultant services to support data collection efforts and integration into the HMIS database to provide for annual road maintenance and rehabilitation plans</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure the GoN road maintenance matching fund requirements are being budgeted and allocated per the Compact and PIA requirements</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Collection of all necessary documentation from the GoN to satisfy GoN requirements under the Compact and PIA</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Identify additional MCA consulting resources to manage the road maintenance civil works in the field/office</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure contractual performance, including all aspects of contract performance management, of all road maintenance civil works contracts</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Act as the focal point for communications between DOR and the MCA-N, as well as the Ministry of Physical Infrastructure and Transport (MOPIT) and Roads Board Nepal (RBN)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist MCA-N Procurement team with technical inputs in any procurement activities which may be undertaken for the selection of a firm</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure Coordination with the DOR and other stakeholders for the formal review of design studies and drawings done by design consultants</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure coordination for approvals and permits during civil works, including but not limited to design modifications, variation orders and contract modifications</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review and submit quarterly progress reports in a timely manner</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approve reports from any Consultant/Contractor or Implementing Entities, and address any implementation problems and delays and recommend actions to keep Project progress on track</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In accordance with MCA-N fiscal procedures, approve disbursement requests or payment vouchers submitted by consultants or contractors funded under the project</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with the Environmental and Social Performance Director of MCA-Nepal to ensure the correct application of MCC and Government of Nepal environmental guidelines, policies and regulations in the execution of all Project Activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Interface with MCC field staff based in Nepal and technical staff based out of Washington DC.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Determine additional experts input requirements, identifying possible sources for these inputs, and assist Procurement Agent/staff on their procurement</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide regular progress information and reports to DOR, MOPIT, and RBN as needed</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other tasks and responsibilities as requested by the CEO of MCA-N</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Civil Engineering, Engineering, Structural Engineering, Transport Engineering or equivalent field</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Preferred: Professional license or accreditation in Civil Engineering or equivalent field</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">10 (ten) years&rsquo; or more experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in roads construction/rehabilitation projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least 5 years&rsquo; cumulative experience with HDM4 and its application in practice with managing a road network is preferred</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Managing projects of similar size, including preparing Terms of references for hiring consultants (designers, advisors, program managers), and construction contractors, preparing budgets for their hiring, managing budgets for social inclusion activities, evaluating the procurement processes, negotiating and awarding the contracts, and managing the hired consultants and contractors for a timely and quality implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred; completed projects references will be given additional advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Previous experience in field data collection</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills (MS office, MS Project). HDM4 experience is advantageous</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good written and verbal communication skills in English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(41, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Manager &ndash; Substations </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Deputy Executive Director/Deputy Chief Executive Office (DED/DCEO) for Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;D</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description </u></strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Substations Manager is responsible for achieving the delivery of the Substations Activity of the Electricity Transmission Project (ETP) through management of an integrated team of technical experts. The Manager will employ rigorous contract and project management techniques to ensure implementation of the Substations Activity on time and within budget while complying with all relevant policies and standards.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the ETP Substations Activity team to implementing the Activity across all project requirements and ensure that these are aligned to the established strategies, frameworks, budgets and resources defined by the Compact</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the Substations Activity team in securing and overseeing high-quality contractors by developing comprehensive scoping documents; preparing tender documents; conducting high-quality procurements; and implementing robust contract management procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Guide ETP Substations Activity team to ensure the use of resources and the implementation of project activities are aligned to the overall project plan</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide MCA-N leadership with consistent progress updates and risk analysis to ensure timely and effective organizational action to advance the goals of the Substations Activity</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Build the ETP Substations Activity team through recruitment, training and development, and performance management of staff to ensure a capacity to deliver the project&rsquo;s objectives</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure integration of all relevant technical requirements in implementing through Substations Activity through management of multidisciplinary team of experts including engineers and environmental, social, health &amp; safety, and resettlement experts</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Secure and integrate support from other MCA-N departments including procurement, fiscal management, monitoring &amp; evaluation, and communications, to ensure timely and effective contracting, management, and monitoring processes for the Substations Activity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the ETP Substations Activity as an integrated component of the Country MCA-N program to project stakeholders (e.g., with national/local government counterparts, civil society, project beneficiaries, etc.) ensuring that collaborative relationships are built and maintained to facilitate the delivery of the program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Evaluate ETP Substations Activity components and activities as these are developed to ensure their relevance to the country context and ensure that these adapted to address requirements on the ground. Establish and implement framework to ensure successful management of the Activity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee development and application of critical project management tools to support the implementation of the Substations Activity including work plans for schedule control, Quality Assurance/Quality Control (QA/QC) and change management plans, risk management tools, contract administration tools, budget and contingency management tools, and others as required</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required), and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields:&nbsp; Electrical Engineering, Electrical Power Engineering, Electronics Engineering, Civil Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Formal training in Project Management preferred (e.g., certified Project Management Professional)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ten (10) years of experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in implementing similar projects in Nepal or similar environments (especially South Asia), with responsibilities including all phases of procurement (e.g., preparation of terms of reference, evaluation, award, etc.), contractor management, contract and budget management, and broad stakeholder engagement requirements;&nbsp; preference will be given to prior experience in substations of at least 132 KV in capacity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Multilateral donor funded projects in the directly relevant sectors will be preferred; completed projects references will be given additional advantage</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ten (10) years of experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) managing teams, especially in a project-based or matrixed organization such as a consulting firm, with demonstrated ability to ensure integration of multiple work streams to achieve project goals</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Technical background in energy infrastructure, environmental management, resettlement and land acquisition, or other topical areas is preferred</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred and</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(43, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ESP Specialist (Land Acquisition) </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines/Substations or Lead ESP Specialist/Coordinator</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Specialist, Environmental &amp; Social Performance (ESP), under the supervision of the Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines (or the Environmental Coordinator, as designated), is responsible for assisting in providing technical input to ensure the environmental and social performance of all Compact funded activities. This involves assisting the Project Manager in ensuring compliance of the Program activities with relevant national environmental and social laws and regulations, MCC Environmental Guidelines, and the International Finance Corporation (IFC) Performance Standards on Environment and Social Sustainability.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA-N Staff, MCC Staff, and other government counterparts to effectively integrate environmental and social considerations into project planning, development, and implementation, including Terms of Reference, work plans, designs, supervision contracts, budgets, timelines, and monitoring mechanisms&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate closely with all MCA-N Staff in the project team and government counterparts to ensure proper oversight of the implementation of all Compact-funded activities, including participating in field missions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and/or review, with guidance from the Quality Assurance Managers (EHS and Social) of ESP documents including, but not limited to, Environmental and Social Management System, Environmental and Social Impact Assessments and Management Plans, Resettlement Action Plans, Stakeholder Engagement Plans, etc., and under the guidance of the Project Manager, ensure the dissemination and implementation of these tools to improve environmental and social performance on Compact activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the adherence of the project team and implementing partners to ESP plans and schedules across different project stages, to ensure efficient implementation of ESP elements and strengthen quality of ESP outputs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains documentation and databases related to ESP information to support reporting and communications activities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social Science, Sociology, Social Work, Community Development, Development Economics, Political Science, Environmental Science, Environmental Studies, Environmental Engineering, Environmental Planning, Environmental Management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years of cumulative experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in environmental and social impact assessment on projects of a similar nature</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with international environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(44, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Specialist, Gender and Social Inclusion (GSI)</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Program </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; PM Power Sector TA (D) and Road Maintenance </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe position will report to the Project Manager Power Sector TA (D) and Road Maintenance Project and be valid for the life of the project, subject to a satisfactory performance review on an annual basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\nThe Specialist, Gender and Social Inclusion, under the supervision of the Project Managers for the Power Sector Technical Assistance and Road Maintenance, is responsible for the implementation of the gender and social inclusion interventions of the TA as described below.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the quality assurance (social) director and other MCA-N GSI specialists, support the development and implementation of the Social and Gender Integration Plan (SGIP)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the reform specialist, implement the institutionalization of a lifeline tariff in the Government policy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:80px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate and oversee studies for determining low-income and poor households&rsquo; ability to access electricity and examine affordability of electricity services</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate inclusive consultations among key government, civil society and the communities to better understand issues, barriers and challenges poor and marginalized women and men experience in accessing and using electricity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support the development of policy and other measures to address key barriers</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support strengthening the capacity of the Electricity Regulator Commission in its responsibility to promote and monitor social equity in the sector</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the transmission specialist, support the design and implementation of the program for strengthening the capacity of NEA&rsquo;s Environment and Social Studies Department&rsquo;s (ESTD) in conducting social impact assessment and inclusive stakeholder engagement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:80px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support institutional capacity assessment of ESTD vis-&agrave;-vis its responsibilities in social impact assessment of infrastructure projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support assessment of the adequacy of policy and regulatory framework, guidelines and tools for conducting effective social impact assessment of infrastructure projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support the assessment of staff and management perceptions of the performance of ESTD in social impact assessment- identify gaps, risks and opportunities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support field assessment and community consultations to understand challenges and gaps of past social impact assessments of projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate consultations with key international development partners such as USAID, World Bank, Asian Development Bank and others who support the ESTD</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Based on analysis and consultations, support the development of guidelines, tools and training programs relevant for improving the institutional capacity of ESTD</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the Road Maintenance Project Manager, integrate gender and social inclusion into the Road Maintenance Project implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support and implement other GSI responsibilities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate and support the implementation of the Environment and Social Management Plan</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support MCC Counter-Trafficking Policy requirement compliance in compact implementation</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with M&amp;E staff in supporting gender and social inclusion data collection and M&amp;E</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social science, Sociology,&nbsp; Social Work, Anthropology, Community Development, Gender Studies</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years or more of cumulative experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in policy and program development for social inclusion</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in socio-economic studies and data analysis to inform policy and program development</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in addressing social exclusion through policy and programs in electricity projects</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good written and oral communication skills, ability to work with wide range of stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in integrating social inclusiveness in project implementation</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Written and spoken fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working in the energy sector preferred</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(45, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BIKAS/Benefit Sharing Activity Specialist </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project Delivery</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe position will report to the Project Manager&mdash;Transmission Lines and be valid for the life of the project, subject to a satisfactory performance review on an annual basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe BIKAS Benefit-Sharing Activity Manager, under the supervision of the Project Manager, Transmission Line, with oversight from the Quality Assurance Advisor (EHS and Social Inclusion), is responsible for the design, management and day-to-day monitoring of BIKAS projects against established milestones and deliverables to support the disbursement of BIKAS activity funding and monitoring the full life cycle of BIKAS activities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Operations</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage consultants and contractors in the assessment and design of a benefit sharing program related to energy infrastructure and energy utilization</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute payments and BIKAS activity disbursements aligned to payment schedules and in response to the achievement of project milestones and deliverables, ensuring compliance with applicable requirements such as MCA finance and accounting policies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Planning</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines, of issues related to the administration of the BIKAS activity, anticipating issues affecting the payment schedule and/or achievement of milestones and deliverables by implementers which could impact the implementation of the Electricity Transmission Project</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with key MCA and MCC staff for effective gender and social inclusion into BIKAS activity development and implementation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the adherence of activity implementers against established project milestones</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate documentation and maintain a database of BIKAS partners and projects, for the full cycle of activity development and implementation, including design and consultant management, budget development, and internal and external audit processes</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Inform potential and current implementers of documentary/information and award processing requirements and award management activities, to build an informed partnership toward the efficient management of contracts and award</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social Science, Community Development, Sociology, Anthropology, International Development, Economics, Development Economics, Environmental Science, Environmental Planning, Environmental Resource Management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in accounting or program management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years or more cumulative work experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in benefit sharing and community development programs, inclusive community engagement and taking into account the concerns of marginalized groups into project design and implementation&nbsp; on projects of a similar nature</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with international environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(46, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Specialist, Human Resources </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Division:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Human Resources </strong><br />\r\n<strong>Report to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Manager, Human Resources and Administration</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Band:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;C</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe position will report to the Manager for Human Resource and Administration and be valid for the life of the project, subject to a satisfactory performance review on an annual basis.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Human Resources (HR) Specialist, under the supervision of the Human Resources and Administration Manager, is responsible for the execution of recruitments, tracking of attendance and maintenance of MCA-N personnel files, and the logistics support for Human Resources-related activities and meetings.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Human Resources Systems &amp; Management</em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute recruitment activities from posting job vacancies to scheduling of applicant interviews, and contracting, ensuring proper documentation and timely delivery against MCA-N programmatic and operational personnel needs</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Track attendance of staff and contracted personnel, and ensure that information are entered accurately for payroll and benefits administration, and contract compliance processes</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Inform staff and managers of Human Resources processes ensuring information is complete to build an informed interaction that facilitates the fulfillment of requests and strengthens compliance with Human Resources guidelines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Recruitment &amp; Staffing</em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain files for all MCA-N personnel ensuring the security, currency, and confidentiality of information</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible for providing smooth transition and on-boarding of new staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide training opportunities that will improve performance and also accountability and leadership qualities of staff</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Administration &amp; Compliance</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Document issues and best practices to help inform process improvement activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Be the custodian of key systems for accountability such as time-keeping, attendance, leave balance and others</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Safeguard confidentiality, privacy and integrity of HR related matters such as Grievance procedures</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure Administration support to staffs with a conductive environment for workplace that protects the staffs&rsquo; well-being, health, safety &amp; security</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Capacity Building &amp; Staff Development</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide training, support and advice on performance management and staff development plans</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize materials and logistics for internal and external MCA-N staff development and engagement activities, and Human Resources meetings</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In conjunction with line Project Managers, organize and lead workshops, retreats and continuing learning to boost morale, productivity and performance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Performance Management</u></em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure a transparent, fair and accountable performance management and evaluation plan is in place</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the evaluation processes at each and every staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide guidance and advise as they carry out evaluations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) from a recognized institution in Human Resources Management, Business Administration, Business Information Systems, Public Administration, Economics, Social Sciences, Humanities or equivalent fields</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) or more years of cumulative work experience preferred (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in a human resource function</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain confidential information and privacy of staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Must hold high degree of integrity, ethics, code of conduct and exercises good judgment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(47, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Manager, Monitoring, Evaluation, and Economic Analysis<br />\r\nDivision:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Program<br />\r\nReport to:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Deputy Executive Director/Deputy Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO) Management<br />\r\nBand:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; D</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\nThe position will report to the Deputy Executive Director/ Chief Executive Officer (DED/DCEO) Management and be valid for the life of the project, subject to a satisfactory performance review on an annual basis<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Manager, Monitoring, Evaluation, and Economic Analysis (MEE) leads the combined Monitoring &amp; Evaluation (M&amp;E) and Economic Analysis (EA) Unit, under the guidance of the Deputy Executive Director, Management.&nbsp; The goal of the MEE unit is to produce timely, relevant, and reliable data and assessments related to the progress and quality of project implementation and the achievement of targeted results by the Nepal Compact.&nbsp; The MEE Manager, is responsible for leading the monitoring and reporting of progress toward compact targets, supporting the independent evaluations of the compact program, updating the economic analysis activities of the compact program, and managing the Compact M&amp;E budget and MEE staff.&nbsp; The MCC counterparts to this position with whom the MEE Manager will liaise are the M&amp;E Lead(s), Results Reporting Analysts, and Economist(s).<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Summary of Duties and Responsibilities</u></em></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lead the development and periodic updates of the Nepal Compact M&amp;E Plan, in accordance with MCC Guidelines and in coordination with MCC and relevant stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li>Lead the implementation of the monitoring component of the Nepal M&amp;E Plan to provide timely and relevant input to project management and external reporting, including:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:80px\">\r\n	<li>Define the performance indicators to be monitored along with their baselines and targets in collaboration with project teams; ensure that monitoring indicators are relevant to project management needs and that risks and assumptions included in the M&amp;E Plan are appropriately tracked</li>\r\n	<li>Produce the quarterly monitoring report, including the M&amp;E Plan Indicator Tracking Table (ITT) and an associated analysis and narrative, to be reviewed by MCA-Nepal and MCC to inform project management. This should include reviewing all of the ITT data on a quarterly basis, checking inconsistent values with project leads and implementers, and storing supporting documentation for all data that is reported</li>\r\n	<li>Identify critical data gaps or data quality issues related to the M&amp;E Plan indicators early on and design and implement a plan to resolve these issues and build capacity with the party that produces the data (e.g. government entities or project implementers) or through independent data collection</li>\r\n	<li>Commission an independent Data Quality Review of monitoring or evaluation data reported by MCA-Nepal and implement a plan to address any identified weaknesses</li>\r\n	<li>Design and implement field assessments of project implementation and achievement of outputs and intermediate outcomes</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate good reporting protocols for field visits conducted by all MCA-Nepal staff, through use of standardized field checklists and review of trip reports</li>\r\n	<li>Disseminate information from M&amp;E systems to relevant stakeholders in Nepal and to MCC</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Support the design and implementation of the evaluation component of the Nepal M&amp;E Plan to promote accountability and learning, including:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ol style=\"margin-left:80px\">\r\n	<li>Advise on the data and evidence needs of Government of Nepal stakeholders so that, where possible, evaluations can be designed to meet those needs</li>\r\n	<li>Provide data and documentation required to inform the design and implementation of evaluations to MCC and independent evaluators</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor adherence to the project design and implementation plans and report any deviations to the independent evaluator</li>\r\n	<li>Review evaluation reports, survey instruments, and other materials produced by each of the evaluators hired by MCC to conduct independent evaluations of the Compact projects</li>\r\n	<li>Manage local stakeholder reviews of evaluation reports and materials</li>\r\n	<li>Contract survey firms to undertake baseline and interim data collection for independent evaluations and supervise work in coordination with the independent evaluator</li>\r\n	<li>Organize meetings/events for the dissemination of evaluation findings for each evaluation report</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ensure that the Cost-Benefit Analyses and Beneficiary Analyses, including estimates of the Economic Rate of Return (ERR), are modified and updated in accordance with MCC Guidelines as improved information becomes available (updating key parameters and variables upon the receipt of new or higher quality data)</li>\r\n	<li>Provide recommendations on project scope or detailed design to MCA-Nepal project directors, including on policy and institutional reforms, as necessary to ensure the projects achieve their intended economic impacts</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain close collaboration and integration between MEE and project teams to ensure that MEE&rsquo;s data and analysis is accurate, up-to-date, and supports evidence-based project design and management</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain regular communication with MCA-Nepal leadership, MCC M&amp;E and Economic Analysis staff to provide updates on the status of MEE activities and to communicate risks related to the progress of implementation or the achievement of results and offer potential solutions</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the MEE staff and supervise their activities</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the Compact M&amp;E budget and provide updates to MCC on commitments and disbursements on a quarterly basis</li>\r\n	<li>Manage the procurements and contracts funded by the M&amp;E budget and report progress to MCC on a quarterly basis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Requirements (Education, Experience, Technical Competencies)</u></em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Economics, Statistics, Monitoring &amp; Evaluations, Mathematics, Engineering, Finance or equivalent field</li>\r\n	<li>Ten (10) or more years&rsquo; cumulative experience, (accumulated after acquisition of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) seven (7) of which is in managing teams that conducted quantitative and qualitative analyses of programs, including a minimum of five (5) years of experience in Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</li>\r\n	<li>Previous managerial experience with demonstrated ability to balance a variety of tasks and demands and to meet deadlines in a responsible and flexible manner. Must demonstrate history of delivering high quality projects on time and within budget</li>\r\n	<li>Previous supervisory experience managing at least 2 subordinate staff</li>\r\n	<li>Experience applying economic concepts to real-world problems, using data and analysis to reach conclusions and provide recommendations. Experience conducting this type of work in Nepal is desired but not required. Demonstrated competency in cost-benefit analysis of projects is desired but not required. Demonstrated experience designing and implementing monitoring systems, including collecting, analyzing, and reporting performance data</li>\r\n	<li>Demonstrated experience designing and implementing program evaluations; experience implementing rigorous, quantitative evaluations involving household or business surveys preferred</li>\r\n	<li>Strong and demonstrable skills in contract management</li>\r\n	<li>Willingness to undertake regular field visits and interact with the different stakeholders. Occasional international travel may also be required</li>\r\n	<li>Strong analytical and report writing skills</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to work with national government counterparts</li>\r\n	<li>Experience working with international donor organizations preferred</li>\r\n	<li>Good written and oral communication skills, ability to work with wide range of stakeholders</li>\r\n	<li>Written and spoken fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n	<li>Demonstrated experience in one or more of the following statistical analysis software and databases, such as STATA, SPSS, SAS, CSPRO, Access, Excel and strong proficiency with MS Word and PowerPoint</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent organizational skills related to data and document management</li>\r\n	<li>Experience working in Energy and/or Roads sectors preferred</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(29, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Chief Legal Officer/General Counsel<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> Legal<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Chief Executive Officer (CEO) / Executive Director (ED)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> D<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Chief&nbsp; Legal Officer/ General Counsel will serve as a critical member of the senior management team of the Accountable Entity (the MCA-N) identified in the compact (Compact) between the Government of Nepal and the United States of America, acting through the Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC).&nbsp; The Chief Legal Officer/General Counsel will serve as the principal legal officer and senior policy advisor on legal matters, as well as a technical resource, to the MCA-N governing board (Board) and management team and other staff of the MCA-N.&nbsp; The Chief Legal Officer/General Counsel may have responsibility for managing and supervising subordinate staff and other legal resources as may be necessary for proper functioning of the MCA-N.&nbsp; The Chief Legal Officer/General Counsel will be expected to carry out the following among his or her primary responsibilities.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Legal Advice &amp; Analysis</em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide or coordinate the provision of legal advice on all issues affecting the internal operations of the MCA-N, including government contracts and other agreements, third party commercial contracts and other agreements, procurement and fiscal law, and corporate governance and records management</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Help to identify, and advise on, situations that may involve elements of fraud and corruption and/or conflicts of interest in the implementation of the Compact.&nbsp; Coordinate training and advice on MCC policies and applicable laws, regulations and other policies relevant to the prevention, detection, and correction of fraud and corruption. Coordinate training and advice on matters of ethical behavior, including the avoidance of conflicts of interest and policies governing confidentiality and transparency.&nbsp; This training will include the Board, the management team, other staff of the MCA-N, and, where appropriate, implementing entities of the Government of Nepal (Government) designated in accordance with the terms of the Compact and of MCA-N contractors</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Board, the management team, and the staff of the MCA-N on legal issues and address legal matters as they arise.&nbsp; This may include preparing and submitting reports and other documents on a periodic basis to the Board and the management team that identify any problems (and recommended solutions) encountered in MCA-N compliance with its obligations or other legal matters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Legal Compliance &amp; Due Diligence </em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure that MCA-N activities comply with: (i) the obligations of the MCA-N contained in the Compact and all related agreements or otherwise delegated to the MCA-N by the Government; (ii)&nbsp;all agreements entered into under or in furtherance of the Compact; (iii) all applicable laws and regulations of Nepal; (iv) all of the MCA-N&rsquo;s organizational and governance documents, including any law or decree related to the creation or operation of the MCA-N and the MCA-N&rsquo;s bylaws or other governing documents; and (v)&nbsp;any other applicable laws, regulations, policies, and agreements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><em><u>Assistant Corporate Secretary &amp; Legal Counsel</u> </em></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist the ED in his/her role as the corporate secretary of the Board.&nbsp; This includes developing and implementing procedures for the meetings of the Board and ensuring that Board meetings and actions comply with the requirements of the Compact, all related agreements, and the relevant governing documents of the MCA-N (including any law or decree related to the creation or operation of the MCA-N and the MCA-N&rsquo;s bylaws or other governing documents).&nbsp; This function also includes responsibility for ensuring all necessary and appropriate records are produced and maintained by the MCA-N</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Contract Management </em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Participate in negotiations, and draft, review, and advise on all types of contracts and other documents to be executed by the MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Participate in the drafting and review of deliverables required by the terms of the Compact and related agreements to ensure legal sufficiency and the proper and timely delivery of such deliverables</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Employment &amp; Labor Law</em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Board and MCA-N regarding employment matters, including drafting and negotiating employment agreements</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide guidance on legal implications of procurement and financial activities that may be undertaken by the MCA-N</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Recruit, supervise, and manage junior legal officers and other staff within the MCA-N;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Determine the need for additional legal experts (including outside counsel), identify possible sources for such experts, assist the Procurement Manager in the procurement of such experts, provide recommendations on particular legal tasks that should be outsourced to an outside counsel, and manage such outside counsel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>Government Relations &amp; Public Policy </em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Cooperate with and advise Government bodies, including ministries, the legislature, and other public agencies, regarding the Government&rsquo;s responsibilities under the Compact and all related agreements</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong><em>General Counsel </em></strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent, or manage the representation of, the MCA-N before courts, regulatory, and administrative bodies, and in arbitration and other proceedings;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Act as the main liaison between the MCA-N and MCC on legal matters relating to the implementation of the Compact</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Perform such other responsibilities that are commonly exercised or incidental to the position of General Counsel or as may be delegated or requested from time to time by the Board or the management team</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>):</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Must hold Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (minimum) and Master&rsquo;s Degree preferred from a recognized institution in Law or an equivalent degree in Law. Also, must be qualified and certified in good standing to practice law in Nepal.&nbsp; Desired to hold specialty in Energy Law, Environmental Law, Corporate Law, or International Law</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Seven (7) or more years of cumulative experience preferred (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) working at a law firm or as legal counsel, preferably with some experience serving as in-house counsel and some experience working in a law firm or as legal counsel in Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge of, and experience with, both international law and the laws of Nepal encompassing a diverse range of legal issues, including contract, corporate, construction, employment, and procurement laws and regulations, especially in transactions or situations involving foreign investors/foreign governments, or experience representing foreign investors in transactions or situations involving the Government. Experience in international commercial transactions and project and structured financing is a plus</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience advising entities in negotiating, executing, and implementing international agreements with foreign governments&nbsp; Experience in US Government funded projects is a plus</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working as or with a corporate secretary on governing board and corporate governance, compliance, and record keeping matters</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in administering or providing advice regarding tax exemptions under Nepali law</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven ability to work in a national and international context</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to coordinate with Government to ensure implementation of MCA-N activities</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to work with multidisciplinary teams and institutions</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with people of different backgrounds</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to collaborate effectively with peers as well as work across departments</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven supervisory or management experience of attorneys and other staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A responsible and flexible attitude and capacity to simultaneously manage a variety of tasks, responsibilities, and shifting priorities and deadlines without supervision</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated history of delivering high quality projects on time and within budget</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The ability to work under pressure and against tight deadlines</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated professionalism, good judgment, and flexibility to meet the needs of the position;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills (e.g., MS Office, Internet)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.</div>\r\n'),
(96, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Infrastructure Assistant Engineer (Substations) #1</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Report to Instructure Lead Engineer (Substations); official supervisor is Project Manager (Substations)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C (low)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:23px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:69px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The &nbsp;Infrastructure Assistant Engineer (Substations) under the supervision of the Lead Senior Engineer for Substation, is responsible for the execution of project support activities, organizing logistical and administrative support for project activities, gathering and inputting information, and monitoring and reporting on project activities including project preparation, design, works, commissioning and closeout of Substations Activity.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Project Management </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute project activities as defined by project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize logistics and administrative requirements for project activities (e.g. travel, venue management, etc.) and ensure that these are delivered and that costs are controlled in line with established budgets;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Collect and input information for use in project monitoring, evaluation, and reporting activities, ensuring the accuracy of data and adherence to established formats for reporting;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under direction of the SR Engineer for Substations, ensure project implementation plans are updated regularly to account for changes in project scopes;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and implement robust document management processes to ensure adequate records keeping for all Substation Activities in coordination with the Project Preparation &amp; Technical Supervision Consultant;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support contract management through processing of invoices and maintenance of MCA-Nepal management information systems; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain a calendar of project activities and ensure that staff and project stakeholders are informed of upcoming deadlines and project progress against milestones to support overall project management.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Oversight </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under oversight of SR Engineer, Substations, conduct reviews of technical deliverables (e.g., design reports), work plans and physical work progress through desk reviews, site visits, progress meetings, etc., and provide guidance and direction to contractors; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Address queries from staff and external stakeholders (e.g. partner organizations, government offices) related to the implementation of project activities to build an informed basis for interaction and increased efficiency in the execution of activities.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s University degree in Engineering, Electrical Engineering or any related field;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other qualifications (e.g., Project Management Professional) preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years professional experience in managing engineering works projects at a variety of stages, including pre-feasibility, feasibility, design construction, supervision and close out;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Two (2) years of project management experience in the construction of energy sector projects, particularly electricity sector construction projects, especially transmission/distribution;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated understanding/experience with safeguards issues linked to infrastructure development including resettlement and environmental, health &amp; safety issue;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(108, '<strong>Job Description for Accountant </strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Summary of the position</u></strong><br />\r\nSupport to Finance officer for day to day financial activities, prepare monthly reporting and visit different projects to support book keeping and financial monitoring.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Line Manager&nbsp;</span></strong></u><br />\r\nResponsible to the Finance office<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Support to raise vouchers according to the accounting software (FAMAS) &nbsp;with adequate supporting documents</li>\r\n	<li>Support to pay all authorized bills received</li>\r\n	<li>Support to pay all staff salaries and expense and keep the staff salaries record up to date</li>\r\n	<li>Issue advance payment to partners as and when authorized and to check their account details regularly</li>\r\n	<li>Deal with the bank regarding fund transfer draft for partners&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Calculate the cost of material sent to and received from the project and charge to the project&rsquo;s accounts</li>\r\n	<li>Make regularly visit to check, support and reconcile the accounts between NEWAH regional office and project accounts</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure account book keeping system of partners according to provided guide line</li>\r\n	<li>Reconcile the inventory record between NEWAH Provence office and project record</li>\r\n	<li>Update the audit queries for adequate supporting documents with the committees / project staffs (signed by responsible persons, official stamp, tax deduction, expenditure update and approved from WSUC&#39;s meetings, return copy of inventory books to NEWAH at the end of the project period etc)</li>\r\n	<li>Support to update accounts at the end of the project in all project sites to satisfy all the concerned stakeholders.</li>\r\n	<li>Support other financial work as instruction by line manager.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><u><strong>Working Condition</strong></u></span></h1>\r\nSindhuli office based with regular visits to project sites<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12px\"><u><strong>Person&rsquo;s specification&nbsp;</strong></u></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIntermediate in commerce with at list 2 years of experience in similar works<br />\r\nGood communication skills in both English and Nepali (both written and Verbal)<br />\r\nVery good time management skills<br />\r\nComputer skill.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Conditions</u></strong>&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Especially women and candidates from under privileged castes and ethnic groups are encouraged to apply.</li>\r\n	<li>Six-month probationary period extendable to one-year contract with satisfactory performance and thereafter renewable on a yearly basis</li>\r\n	<li>Salary and other conditions will be as per the rules of the organization</li>\r\n	<li>The post will be decided on the basis of a written test followed by an interview</li>\r\n	<li>Only short-listed candidates will be contacted</li>\r\n	<li>Telephone and personal contact will not be entertained&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><u>Salary and Benefits</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;Starting&nbsp;&nbsp; Salary NRS 27000.00 per Month<br />\r\n&nbsp;Dearness Allowance NRS 13550.00<br />\r\n&nbsp;Dashain Bonus as per rules<br />\r\nPF as per rules.<br />\r\nTotal 33 annual leave and 15 days public holiday<br />\r\nOthers: AS per the rules of the organization<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(98, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Assistant Engineer &ndash; Transmission Line</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Report to Lead Engineer-Transmission; official supervisor is Project Manager -Transmission</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C (low)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:23px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:69px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:7px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Assistant Junior (JR) Engineer (Transmission &nbsp;Lines ) under the supervision of the Lead Senior Engineer for Transmission Lines, is responsible for the execution of project support activities, organizing logistical and administrative support for project activities, gathering and inputting information, and monitoring and reporting on project activities including project preparation, design, works, commissioning and closeout of transmission lines Activity.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:10px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Project Management </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute project activities as defined by project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize logistics and administrative requirements for project activities (e.g. travel, venue management, etc.) and ensure that these are delivered and that costs are controlled in line with established budgets;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Collect and input information for use in project monitoring, evaluation, and reporting activities, ensuring the accuracy of data and adherence to established formats for reporting;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under direction of the SR Engineer for Transmission Lines, ensure project implementation plans are updated regularly to account for changes in project scopes;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and implement robust document management processes to ensure adequate records keeping for all Substation Activities in coordination with the Project Preparation &amp; Technical Supervision Consultant;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support contract management through processing of invoices and maintenance of MCA-Nepal management information systems; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain a calendar of project activities and ensure that staff and project stakeholders are informed of upcoming deadlines and project progress against milestones to support overall project management.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Oversight </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under oversight of SR Engineer, Transmission Lines, conduct reviews of technical deliverables (e.g., design reports), work plans and physical work progress through desk reviews, site visits, progress meetings, etc., and provide guidance and direction to contractors; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Address queries from staff and external stakeholders (e.g. partner organizations, government offices) related to the implementation of project activities to build an informed basis for interaction and increased efficiency in the execution of activities.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s University degree in Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Civil Engineering or any related field;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other qualifications (e.g., Project Management Professional) preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years professional experience in managing engineering works projects at a variety of stages, including pre-feasibility, feasibility, design construction, supervision and close out;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Two (2) years of project management experience in the construction of energy sector projects, particularly electricity sector construction projects, especially transmission/distribution;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated understanding/experience with safeguards issues linked to infrastructure development including resettlement and environmental, health &amp; safety issue;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><a name=\"_Hlk535582164\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(48, '<strong>Job purpose</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe purpose of this position is to provide quality and training assistance for the successful implementation of quality service with more knowledge and skills on leading a service &amp; product knowledge, communication and skill development and team work to perform a professional duties and state management functions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Develop a need assessment process and create an instructional design process with appropriate delivery methods and post-training evaluation</li>\r\n	<li>Recommend solutions for performance issues and potential areas of training</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct training need assessments and oversee the training function</li>\r\n	<li>Manage, lead, motivate and develop training team members</li>\r\n	<li>Resolve and respond to training issues and questions from management team and employees on the application and interpretation of processes, company policies and current legislation</li>\r\n	<li>Continuously seek and support new approaches, practices and processes to improve the efficiency of training services offered</li>\r\n	<li>Producing training material for in-house programs</li>\r\n	<li>Monitoring and reviewing the progress of trainees through questionnaires and discussions with immediate supervisors</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and maintain up to date training and development plans for contact center</li>\r\n	<li>Creating time line and work plan for each training event</li>\r\n	<li>Document performance report and worksheet of the all personnel</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure compliance of corporate standards and procedures in training sessions</li>\r\n	<li>Conduct a series of training sessions as assigned by the management team</li>\r\n	<li>Research, write, organize and present a variety of training sessions</li>\r\n	<li>Constantly study, revise and re-write any material related to the area of responsibility outlined</li>\r\n	<li>Design and apply assessment tools to measure training effectiveness</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate and make recommendations on training material and methodology</li>\r\n	<li>Listen to calls in three ways: Recorded, live and side by side while communicating feedback to encourage good ones and discourage the bad ones</li>\r\n	<li>Work in a continuous process of evaluating calls and providing feedbacks enhancing the quality of the calls</li>\r\n	<li>Identify calls failing to meet predefined standards and get the root cause of why</li>\r\n	<li>Make informed decisions to make the process better, faster and quicker, implement or refine agent training and coaching initiatives to bridge skills gaps, correct broken internal process, improve workforce, scheduling or perhaps alert other areas of organization that are having an impact</li>\r\n	<li>Measure compliance against established expectations of agent behavior</li>\r\n	<li>To assess agent performance/ behavior in call center and to coach and counsel agents to modify their performance/ behavior to facilitate a high level of customer service</li>\r\n	<li>Check in agent attrition rate</li>\r\n	<li>Perform raw data collection and analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Measure and evaluate the effectiveness of corporate processes, procedures and outcomes as they relate to customer service in a complete accurate and timely manner</li>\r\n	<li>Contribute to continuous improvement activities</li>\r\n	<li>Escalate issues as appropriate</li>\r\n	<li>Look after agent performance and their motivation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Job Specification </strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or running from reputed university</li>\r\n	<li>Should be hardworking, respectful and tactful with all stakeholders, superiors and peers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>High levels of computer literacy including quantitative/analytical skills and advanced proficiency with MS Excel</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to do data analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Able to do multi-tasking, maintain confidentiality and finish the assigned work within the deadline</li>\r\n	<li>Needs to have pleasant personality and should be able to communicate things properly</li>\r\n	<li>2 year of experience in the similar field</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(111, 'Requirements:<br />\r\n1. Qualification: minimum +2 pass or pursuing bachelors<br />\r\n2. Experience: Preferably experienced candidates in customer support role but we encourage freshers to apply as well.<br />\r\n3.Skills:Decent spoken/written English, basic computer skills<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBrief Job description:<br />\r\nHandling Inbound and Outbound calls on timely manner,response to customer queries.<br />\r\nDuty hours: Morning shift(6am-2pm),Day shift(10am-6pm), Night Shift(10am-6pm)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', ''),
(112, '<a name=\"_Hlk7689444\"><strong><u>Territory Manager &ndash; Neurosurgery<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWork location: Kathmandu, Nepal</u></strong></a><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Careers that Change Lives</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To achieve sales revenue and market share targets for the territory of Orissa &amp; Chattisgarh, by promoting Neurosurgery products to doctors/ specialists and patients/end users.</li>\r\n	<li>Develop and maintain long-term relationships with customers.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand market sales opportunities and close orders to meet sales targets. Seek opportunities to open new accounts and start new programs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<a name=\"_Hlk7689489\"><strong>A Day in the Life</strong></a><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Secondary AOP Responsibility</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Responsible for achieving Secondary AOP/Targets in terms of product units and revenue and increase total company market share in assigned territory.</li>\r\n	<li>Support in creating and implementing an annual business plan with quarterly updates.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure coverage of all accounts on the basis of customer segmentation within territory in agreement with the manager to maintain optimum level of exposure.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and expand existing business and develop new business opportunities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Increase Coverage</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek new customers and formulate and follow up plans for such action as directed by the Regional Sales Manager.</li>\r\n	<li>Aggressively solicits orders from present and prospective customers for the products assigned.</li>\r\n	<li>Expand the customer base and sales by establishing regular contact with key specialists, technical staff and administration personnel.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Marketing Intelligence &amp; Reporting</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize and understand competitive products, features, strengths in relation to the company&rsquo;s products.</li>\r\n	<li>Gather market intelligence as an audit on hospital usage, competitor products and pricing, also continual updates on general competitive activities.</li>\r\n	<li>Communicate marketing plans / intelligence/competitor activity promptly, including potential sales leads, and information regarding product price or account activity to Regional Sales Manager and other appropriate company personnel.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide timely information to management regarding customer concerns, issues and market opportunities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Must Have &ndash; Minimum Requirements</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:615px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:65px; width:307px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li><strong>4&ndash; 8 years&rsquo; sales experience &ndash; TSM</strong></li>\r\n				<li>Bachelor in Science /B Pharma/BE/ BTech in Biomedical Engineering / Bio-instrumentation, Electronics</li>\r\n				<li>PG degree in Business Management (preferred)</li>\r\n				<li>Must have Indian bank account, Adhar Card &amp; PAN Card.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:65px; width:307px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Selling of capital equipment product from MNC/Company of repute</li>\r\n				<li>Familiar with the physics of <strong>medical imaging technologies </strong>(For Navigation)</li>\r\n				<li>Good verbal communicator and presenter &ndash; Good command over English and Regional language</li>\r\n				<li>Willing to travel extensively</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Nice to Have</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Professional presentation and &quot;Presence&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Professional standard of written and verbal communication to sales team and customers</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to quickly establish credibility with all levels of customer base</li>\r\n	<li>Strategic mindset in planning and driving marketing strategies and managing customers</li>\r\n	<li>People and Relationship building Skills including Networking Skills</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>PHYSICAL&nbsp;REQUIREMENTS:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe physical demands described within the Responsibilities section of this job description are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job.&nbsp; Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. While performing the duties of this job, the employee is regularly required to be independently mobile. The employee is also required to interact with a computer, and communicate with peers and co-workers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', ''),
(113, '<div><strong>Position Description</strong></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:668px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:139px\"><strong>Position Title:</strong></td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:529px\"><strong>Sales Representative II / Territory Manager</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:139px\"><strong>Reports To:</strong></td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:529px\"><strong>Regional Manager</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:139px\"><strong>Division:</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:528px\"><strong>Spinal &amp; Biologics</strong></td>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Main Purpose:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u></strong><strong><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To over achieve sales revenue and market share targets for a specified regional territory, by promoting Spinal &amp; Biologic products to doctors/ specialists and patients/end users.</li>\r\n	<li>To practice good territory management in terms of organization, administration and expense planning and control.</li>\r\n	<li>To ensure that the company&rsquo;s agreed quality standards are maintained with regard to its products, procedures, policies, operations and customer contact.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Key Accountabilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n	<li>Meets or exceeds sales quota and increases total company market share in assigned territory.</li>\r\n	<li>Partner with the application specialist when and where applicable.</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for being a spinal &amp; biologics &ldquo;expert&rdquo; in the market place.</li>\r\n	<li>Aggressively solicits orders from present and prospective customers for the products assigned.</li>\r\n	<li>Aggressively seeks new customers and formulates and follow plans for such action as directed by the Regional Sales Manager.</li>\r\n	<li>Satisfy customer complaints in accordance with Company policy and to advise Regional Sales Manager and company promptly of any situation beyond scope of authority.</li>\r\n	<li>Comply with all Company policies.</li>\r\n	<li>Stay attentive to competitor&rsquo;s product and merchandizing practices and to keep the Regional Sales Manager and company informed concerning them.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain and expand existing business and develop new business opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Represent company at industry conferences and maximize potential by targeting specific customers to gain sales leads, and pursue opportunities to promote the company&rsquo;s product range</li>\r\n	<li>Follow the principles and adhere to the SFE practices.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintains Consignments and Loaner inventory in line with company guidelines..</li>\r\n	<li>Prepares and submits call reports as required by Regional Sales Manager.</li>\r\n	<li>Recommends the additions of new products and the modification or deletions of present products to the line as appropriate.</li>\r\n	<li>Attends and participates in sales meetings, training programs, conventions, and trade shows as directed.</li>\r\n	<li>Cooperates with all personnel on the execution of Company programs.</li>\r\n	<li>Creates and implements an annual business plan with quarterly updates.</li>\r\n	<li>Provides service to customers per their individual needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Submits reports and provides information as directed.</li>\r\n	<li>Adheres to company policies and conducts all business in an ethical manner.</li>\r\n	<li>Manages business with company profitability in mind.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>KEY BEHAVIOURAL ATTRIBUTES REQUIRED.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills: Good verbal communicator and presenter.</li>\r\n	<li>Self Starter &amp; High on Initiative.</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneurial Drive.</li>\r\n	<li>Innovative &amp; Ideating nature.</li>\r\n	<li>Logical approach &amp; reasoning skills while analyzing competition &amp; market trends.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to deal with ambiguity &amp; persevere to resolve situation at hand.</li>\r\n	<li>Strong Analytical ability during customer/patient call.</li>\r\n	<li>Effective Time Management.</li>\r\n	<li>Execution Excellence.</li>\r\n	<li>High on energy &amp; positive outlook.</li>\r\n	<li>Highly adaptable &amp; flexible in action.</li>\r\n	<li>Customer focused:Understands and delivers customer service</li>\r\n	<li>Self motivated and positive.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to quickly establish credibility with all levels of customer base</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>KEY TRAITS:</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:679px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:121px\"><strong>TRAITS</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:558px\"><strong>STRONG INDICATORS</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:121px\"><strong>Execute </strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:558px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Consistently delivers results on time and exceeds expectations;</li>\r\n				<li>Clarifies and aligns resources for faster execution;</li>\r\n				<li>Looks at different ways to align resources for better outcomes,</li>\r\n				<li>Continually monitors progress and makes adjustments.</li>\r\n				<li>Seeks continuous improvement.</li>\r\n				<li>Takes accountability to produce agreed upon results.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:121px\"><strong>Driven to WIN</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:558px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Consistently achieves high outcomes under varied circumstances.</li>\r\n				<li>Doesn&rsquo;t allow degree of difficulty to stand in the way &ndash; finishes what he/she started.</li>\r\n				<li>Demonstrates high capacity for work.</li>\r\n				<li>Taking on significant challenging responsibilities.</li>\r\n				<li>Pursues work with passion and drive.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:121px\"><strong>External Focus</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:558px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Operates with customer interests clearly in mind.</li>\r\n				<li>Interacts regularly with customers and seeks inputs.</li>\r\n				<li>Well informed regarding market and industry / competitors operating in territory.</li>\r\n				<li>Brings best practices from other region colleagues or outside and implements them within territory.</li>\r\n				<li>Initiates or champions changes from the outside in.</li>\r\n				<li>Explores new opportunities and asks informed questions.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:121px\"><strong>Clear Thinking</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:558px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li>Problem solver:Resolves issues of patient / distributor /KOL in territory.</li>\r\n				<li>Data Analysis: Territory, Doctors, Leads, Patients.</li>\r\n				<li>Judgment about activity /investments in Territory.</li>\r\n				<li>Making sound decision in absence of full data.</li>\r\n				<li>Design Short- &amp; Long-term territory &amp; KOL plan. Helping and Guiding distributors reps.</li>\r\n				<li>Communicates complex matters to Internal (Company people) and other external stakeholders with appropriate clarity and simplicity<strong>.</strong></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Experience and Knowledge:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A minimum 4 to 8 years sales experience and Concept Selling background</li>\r\n	<li>Experience of Distribution Management</li>\r\n	<li>Exceptional interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>QUALIFICATIONS.</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nB Sc (Any Sciences)/BE . MBA would be preferred.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nMust have Indian Bank Account, Adhar Card &amp; PAN Card<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWork Location: kathmandu, Nepal', '', '', '', ''),
(100, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Gender and Social Inclusion (GSI) Specialist</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Program</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">PM Power Sector TA (D) and Road Maintenance</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp;<br />\r\n			The position will report to the Project Manager Power Sector TA (D) and Road Maintenance Project and be valid for the life of the project, subject to a satisfactory performance review on an annual basis.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Specialist, Gender and Social Inclusion, under the supervision of the Project Managers for the Power Sector Technical Assistance and Road Maintenance, is responsible for the implementation of the gender and social inclusion interventions of the TA as described below.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Operations</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the quality assurance (social) director and other MCA-N GSI specialists, support the development and implementation of the Social and Gender Integration Plan (SGIP).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the reform specialist, implement the institutionalization of a lifeline tariff in the Government policy.\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li>Coordinate and oversee studies for determining low-income and poor households&rsquo; ability to access electricity and examine affordability of electricity services.</li>\r\n					<li>Coordinate inclusive consultations among key government, civil society and the communities to better understand issues, barriers and challenges poor and marginalized women and men experience in accessing and using electricity.</li>\r\n					<li>Support the development of policy and other measures to address key barriers.</li>\r\n					<li>Support strengthening the capacity of the Electricity Regulator Commission in its responsibility to promote and monitor social equity in the sector.</li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the transmission specialist, support the design and implementation of the program for strengthening the capacity of NEA&rsquo;s Environment and Social Studies Department&rsquo;s (ESTD) in conducting social impact assessment and inclusive stakeholder engagement.\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li>Support institutional capacity assessment of ESTD vis-&agrave;-vis its responsibilities in social impact assessment of infrastructure projects.</li>\r\n					<li>Support assessment of the adequacy of policy and regulatory framework, guidelines and tools for conducting effective social impact assessment of infrastructure projects.</li>\r\n					<li>Support the assessment of staff and management perceptions of the performance of ESTD in social impact assessment- identify gaps, risks and opportunities.</li>\r\n					<li>Support field assessment and community consultations to understand challenges and gaps of past social impact assessments of projects.</li>\r\n					<li>Coordinate consultations with key international development partners such as USAID, World Bank, Asian Development Bank and others who support the ESTD.</li>\r\n					<li>Based on analysis and consultations, support the development of guidelines, tools and training programs relevant for improving the institutional capacity of ESTD.</li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the Road Maintenance Project Manager, integrate gender and social inclusion into the Road Maintenance Project implementation.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support and implement other GSI responsibilities\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li>Coordinate and support the implementation of the Environment and Social Management Plan</li>\r\n					<li>Support MCC Counter-Trafficking Policy requirement compliance in compact implementation.</li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with M&amp;E staff in supporting gender and social inclusion data collection and M&amp;E</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:19px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:23px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Advanced (Master&rsquo;s Degree or higher preferred) from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social science, Sociology,&nbsp; Social Work, Anthropology, Community Development, Gender Studies;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least five (5) years of cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification) in policy and program development for social inclusion</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in socio-economic studies and data analysis to inform policy and program development.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in addressing social exclusion through policy and programs in electricity projects</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good written and oral communication skills, ability to work with wide range of stakeholders</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in integrating social inclusiveness in project implementation</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Written and spoken fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working in the energy sector preferred.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(92, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:23px; text-align:justify; width:149px\"><a name=\"_Hlk535410570\">Position:</a></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:23px; text-align:justify; width:474px\">Power Sector Reform Specialist (Transmission)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:22px; text-align:justify; width:149px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:22px; text-align:justify; width:474px\">Project Manager &ndash; Power Sector Technical Assistance</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Band</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Position Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Power Sector Technical Assistance Specialist (Transmission) under the supervision of the Power Sector TA Project Manager, Technical Assistance, is responsible is responsible for the daily execution, monitoring, and supervision of a range of activities supporting the Electricity Transmission Project&rsquo;s (ETP) Technical Assistance Activity related to strengthening operations at the Nepal Electricity Authority (NEA) ensuring consistency with established work plans and implementation guidelines.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Management </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under the direction of the Project Manager, prepare, update and monitor all relevant project management tools including but not limited to: work plans (schedules), procurement plans, detailed financial plans (budgets), risk management plans and scoping documents (activity descriptions, terms of reference, etc.);</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure the delivery of effective technical assistance activities by securing and overseeing high-quality contractors through development of comprehensive scoping documents; preparing tender documents; conducting high-quality procurements; and implementing robust contract management procedures;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate project statistics from multiple sources and review these for accuracy and compliance with established formats to support implementation, monitoring, and analytics;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise Project Manager, Technical Assistance, of issues related to the implementation of the project in order ensure the continuity of project delivery;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor project budget, procurement activities, and contracts, ensuring that these are consistent with established MCA guidelines and that issues and discrepancies are resolved and reported. On quarterly basis, support preparation of disbursement request packages to ensure consistent flow of funding;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor project timelines and milestones, anticipate delivery issues, and ensure that staff and external stakeholders are kept informed of project status to support overall project management and delivery; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain project documentation and Operations Manuals ensuring that these are current and reflecting lessons learned to support the improvement of projects/processes.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Implementation </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute and/or oversee a range of project implementation and support activities as defined by the project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives, and ensure consistency of quality;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and sustain relationships with critical stakeholders at ETP partners to facilitate implementation of the Technical Assistance Activity through delivery of effective technical assistance, stakeholder engagement and dialogue, and other requirements to advance ETP goals;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor implementation of activities and recommendations delivered under the ETP and identify options to address gaps in implementation or follow through on recommendations;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the Technical Assistance Activity team as an integrated component of the MCA-Nepal ETP to project stakeholders (e.g., with national/local government counterparts, civil society, project beneficiaries, etc.) ensuring that collaborative relationships are built and maintained to facilitate the delivery of the program;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with relevant MCA-Nepal staff the effective gender and social inclusion into the development and implementation of the TA (transmission); and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and maintain an understanding of all ongoing activities linked to strengthening the power sector to include other technical assistance activities, institutional changes at ETP partners, sector investments, legal or regulatory changes, etc., as required to ensure the Technical Assistance Activity reflects current context.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:15px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:19px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Economics, Business, Management, Engineering, or other relevant field of study; Advanced Degree is preferred. Project Management Professional certification (PMP) is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least five (5) years of cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification) professionallyin institutional reform and organizational development processes, particularly in public sector organizations.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least two (2) years of experience managing complex projects on time/on budget (&gt;$1 million) including procurement, implementation and closeout phases</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency with written and oral communication in Nepali and English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Intimate knowledge of, and experience with, Nepal&rsquo;s energy sector, preferably including an understanding of electric utility operations challenges and related development strategies.&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience as a leader and in consensus building; strong capability to multi-task and manage multiple work streams simultaneously.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively with multi-disciplinary and multi-cultural local and international stakeholders and counterparts.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills (MS office, MS Project, Management Information Systems).&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:31px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(107, '<strong>TITLE: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Field Support Officers</strong><br />\r\n<strong>PROJECT: &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Global Health Supply Chain &ndash; Procurement and Supply Management Project in Nepal</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>General Summary and Background:</strong> The purpose of GHSC-PSM is to ensure uninterrupted supplies of health commodities in support of USG-funded public health initiatives around the world. The project provides direct procurement and supply chain management support to the President&rsquo;s Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR), the President&rsquo;s Malaria Initiative (PMI), Population and Reproductive Health (PRH) Maternal and Child Health and Zika (MCH). GHSC-PSM supports health programs through the supply of a wide range of health commodities, including contraceptives and condoms, essential drugs; and select commodities for HIV/AIDS, malaria, maternal and child health, and infectious diseases.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Principal Duties and Responsibilities (Essential Functions)</strong><br />\r\n&bull; Assist in developing and implementing activities and tools(checklist, job aids, guides) to improve warehousing, inventory management, transportation and distribution at regional, district/palikas and health facilities levels.<br />\r\n&bull; Support the gathering of monitoring and evaluation data<br />\r\n&bull; Maintain good relations with counterparts in regional and district stores and health facilities and provide project with feedback<br />\r\n&bull; Provide inputs to project reporting and assist the supply chain logistics team to fulfil contract deliverables<br />\r\n&bull; Monitor stock situation and provide support to prevent a stock out at facilities<br />\r\n&bull; Ensure that USAID regulations, Chemonics&rsquo; policies, and best practices are consistently enforced<br />\r\n&bull; With the Ministry of Health and other partners, develop and implement a plan to de-clutter and maintain selected warehouses<br />\r\n&bull; Oversee reporting and the re-supply of commodities from district/palika level by checking facilities&rsquo; LMIS forms, stock book updates, use of authorized stock levels and emergency order plans; by reviewing LMIS feedback reports for supplies to health facility; and by supporting web-based logistic information<br />\r\n&bull; Support health facility inventory management by: i) assisting completion of quantities to order on LMIS forms, ii) overseeing essential drugs in pull system-implemented districts and program commodities in other districts, thereby sending a requisition form along with LMIS forms to districts, iii) overseeing district re-supply of health facilities as per LMIS form data; and iv) checking that facilities maintain needed stock levels<br />\r\n&bull; Oversee stock balances of key family planning and MNCH commodities in district health facilities and communicate for re-ordering when stocks are low<br />\r\n&bull; Oversee the cleanliness of storage areas and the practicing of the first expiry-first out system<br />\r\n&bull; Assist in the district level quarterly distribution of health commodities to health facilities<br />\r\n&bull; Coordinate district and regional level logistics capacity building programs<br />\r\n&bull; Assist the auctioning and disposal of expired and unneeded commodities in district stores and health facilities<br />\r\n&bull; Oversee on the job training of district staff and ensure new staff are orientated on basic health logistics<br />\r\n&bull; Keep track of important district-level information and work with DHOs and DPHOs to avoid double entry system at health facilities and oversee keeping of district and health facility equipment status lists and communicate status to LMD<br />\r\n&bull; Support provincial MOH staff in use of data for decision making;<br />\r\n&bull; Other tasks as may be assigned.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Qualifications and Requirements</strong><br />\r\n&bull; Minimum 3 years&rsquo; experience of supply chain management or warehousing, and inventory management, procurement, forecasting, and planning or other relevant experience<br />\r\n&bull; Bachelor in pharmacy, commerce, arts, science or relevant field (advance degree preferred)<br />\r\n&bull; Self-starter, outgoing and results oriented with proven problem solving and decision-making skills<br />\r\n&bull; Experience organizing and delivering capacity-building interventions such as training and mentorship programs<br />\r\n&bull; Ability to work on complex assignments where considerable judgment and initiative is needed to resolve problems<br />\r\n&bull; Experience working with GoN staff at district and region level<br />\r\n&bull; Experience with USAID funded projects<br />\r\n&bull; Excellent interpersonal, written and oral communications skills in English and Nepali<br />\r\n&bull; Expert user of Microsoft Office, especially Excel and PowerPoint<br />\r\n&bull; Province-based candidates who own a motorcycle will be preferred.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Supervision and Evaluation</strong><br />\r\nThe Field Support Officers will be managed and supervised by the selected subcontractor under the technical supervision of the GHSC-PSM project in Nepal<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(116, 'Rolling Plans Private Limited (RPPL) is a specialized service outsourcing firm having intensity of its services in various functions of human resource management and development (HRM/D), research and innovation, and institutional development since 2004. Our vision is to be an internationally acclaimed service provider in HR solutions and research and innovation. For this, we have a mission to support organizations by providing them with strategic as well as operational solutions, and at the same time, we help organizations maintain highest level of socio-ethical standards. For more info, please check our website <a href=\"http://www.rollingplans.com.np\">www.rollingplans.com.np</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nRPPL entered the contract with UNOPS for Human Resource services for implementation of various project of UNOPs in different districts of Nepal.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Job purpose</strong><br />\r\nThe main responsibility of this position is to provide logistic and admin support to officer-HR &amp; Admin for HR and logistics function, which include recruitment, staffing, training and development, performance monitoring, field visit, inventory management and be an assistant focal person for the employees and perform tasks such as communication, system record-keeping, Reporting, Recruiting, Training and assisting in the establishment project documentation.<br />\r\n<strong>Duties and responsibilities</strong><br />\r\nThe primary job duties and responsibilities:&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Assess and organize logistics in terms of transport and its required logistics.</li>\r\n	<li>Establish a detailed procurement program plan to determine appropriate specifications of required items, according to established procedure.</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in field-level planning formulation in the area of logistics for various functional HR activities.</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in program planning and advising on logistics considerations.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide technical and operational support to the field visits and visitors, as well as advice on application of logistics management best practice, systems and procedures.</li>\r\n	<li>Handle and maintain candidate database to generate report on application status.</li>\r\n	<li>Communicate with candidates for various HR related purpose.</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for information flow as assigned by team members to the candidates/staffs.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform and handle printing activities as required in staff management.</li>\r\n	<li>Preparation of contract in coordination with team members.</li>\r\n	<li>Collect Time sheet on monthly basis and prepare the details for payroll management</li>\r\n	<li>Overview deadlines and suggest to team members.</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate on recruitment and selection of staffs and its components.</li>\r\n	<li>Assist the Officer and Project Coordinator and in overall process.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide support on report preparation of all activities, maintenance of assignment status and administrative support.</li>\r\n	<li>Review the logistics component of travel and logistics budget proposals for consideration during budget review.</li>\r\n	<li>Record and file all documents of service performance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<strong>Competencies</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Communication</strong>:&nbsp; Speaks and writes clearly and effectively; listens to others, correctly interprets messages from others and responds appropriately; asks questions to clarify, and exhibits interest in having two-way communication; tailors language, tone, style and format to match audience; demonstrates openness in sharing information and keeping people informed.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Teamwork: </strong>Works collaboratively with colleagues to achieve organizational goals. Solicits input by genuinely valuing others&rsquo; ideas and expertise; is willing to learn from others. Places team agenda before personal agenda. Supports and acts in accordance with final group decision, even when such decisions may not entirely reflect own position. Shares credit for team accomplishments and accepts joint responsibility for team shortcomings.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Planning &amp; Organizing: </strong>Develops clear goals that are consistent with agreed strategies. Identifies priority activities and assignments; adjusts priorities as required. Allocates appropriate amount of time and resources for completing work. Foresees risks and allows for contingencies when planning. Monitors and adjusts plans and actions as necessary. Uses time efficiently.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Client Orientation</strong>: Considers all those to whom services are provided to be &ldquo;clients&rdquo; and seeks to see things from clients&rsquo; point of view; establishes and maintains productive partnerships with clients by gaining their trust and respect; identifies clients&rsquo; needs and matches them to appropriate solutions; monitors ongoing developments inside and outside the clients&rsquo; environment to keep informed and anticipate problems; keeps clients informed of progress or setbacks in projects; meets timeline for delivery of products or services to client.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Technological Awareness</strong>: Keeps abreast of available technology; understands applicability and limitation of technology to the work of the office; actively seeks to apply technology to appropriate tasks; shows willingness to learn new technology.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Qualifications</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\nQualifications include:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Preferably Master&rsquo;s degree in management or social sciences or related field or Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in management or social sciences.</li>\r\n	<li>At least two years of professional experience in human resource administration for Master&rsquo;s degree and three years of experience in HRM for Bachelor&rsquo;s degree.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>High degree of proficiency in office procedures and use of computers including Microsoft Word and Excel programs.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work independently and make decisions in accordance with established policies and regulations.</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to maintain confidential information with good health, high moral character and good attendance record.</li>\r\n	<li>Should be hardworking, respectful and tactful with all stakeholders, superiors and peers.</li>\r\n	<li>Should be detail oriented, organized and able to meet tight deadlines.</li>\r\n	<li>Fluency in Nepali and English language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Working conditions</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\nAssisting work in office environment from Sunday- Friday (9:30am- 5:30pm) with frequent requirement to work beyond office hours based upon project requirements and deadlines.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Direct reports</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\nProject Coordinator\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(105, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Driver</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Administration</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Manager-Administration and Human Resources</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">A</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:23px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:69px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:10px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Office Driver, under the supervision of the Office Manager, is responsible for driving office vehicles for official functions and maintaining cleanliness and functionality of vehicles in order to support the office in its overall functioning.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:11px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Drive MCA-Nepal office staff and guests ensuring safety and security of passengers in support of daily operational requirements of the office and its programs;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain the cleanliness and functionality of vehicles, reporting any damage or needs for repair and maintenance and ensure that the vehicles are ready for use;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Log vehicle use, gasoline consumption, and mileage to ensure that vehicles &ndash; considered organizational resources &ndash; are responsibly used and to support monitoring and audit activities;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Keep aware of schedules and work plans and general traffic conditions to ensure effective and efficient driving support is provided to office staff.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide administrative assistance where required to ensure smooth functioning of MCA-Nepal</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Professional Driver&rsquo;s License&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proficiency in English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Attention to detail.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Problem-solving attitude and skilled in taking initiative.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience of providing office assistance support.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to process documents independently is preferred.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience of driving 4WD in remote areas of Nepal.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><a name=\"_Hlk535582164\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(87, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Internal Control/Compliance Specialist</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Financial Management</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Chief Financial Officer (CFO)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Internal Control/Compliance (ICC) Specialist supports the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) who leads the Financial Management Directorate and has overall responsibility for MCA-Nepal financial management activities.&nbsp; &nbsp;The ICC Specialist will be expected to carry out the following among his or her primary responsibilities.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Internal Compliance&nbsp; </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support CFO in adherence to all financial management provisions of the Compact and related documents;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversees the Fiscal Agent contract to ensure that the Fiscal Agent is providing all the financial management services, such as funds control and payment processing, required in its contract and in the Fiscal Agent Agreement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Internal Control</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Reviews and updates a financial management operation manual, known as the Fiscal Accountability Plan (FAP), which outlines all procedures necessary for financial management operations, documents sound internal controls, and designates the officials that have the authority to approve obligations, verify receipt of goods and services, and execute payments.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Plans and oversees audit requirements and ensures audit findings are resolved timely;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support the Financial Management division in developing program accounting reports, including special reports required by the MCA-Nepal or the Board of Directors and the Government of Nepal.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Risk Management </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitors and ensures compliance with all aspects of the FAP;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensures that MCC funds are exempt from all taxes and refunds for taxes are paid as detailed in the Compact Agreement, Program Implementation Plan, and/or any other associated agreements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Supports preparation of MCA-Nepal&rsquo;s annual Program budget for the entire Compact period, as well as detailed budgets with the Projects/Unit and any Implementing Entities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Serves as liaison with the Project/Unit Managers, other personnel, and any Implementing Agencies on internal control and compliance matters and issues;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitors expenses against budgets to ensure adequate resources and control of funds.&nbsp; Provides quarterly contract disbursements and other necessary information to the Monitoring, Evaluation &amp; Economic Analysis team in order to track process milestones for the Compact on internal control and compliance matters and issues.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Administration &amp; Operations</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manages and reviews the work of related personnel and ensure quality of outputs and provide day-to-day supervision;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists in matters related to office insurances, which includes assets insurance, public liability insurance, directors&rsquo; and officers&rsquo; liability insurance on internal control and compliance matters and issues;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Reviews and provides advices to contracts related to the day to day operations of MCA-Nepal;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Performs other tasks and special projects as assigned.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Must hold Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (minimum) from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Accounting, Banking &amp; Finance, Commerce, Finance, Financial Control, Chartered Accountancy Business Administration, Business Management, General Management, Economics, or in equivalent field.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least five (5) or more years of progressive professional experience, (notwithstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification) in managing the corporate finance or finance function, preferably in international development, governmental organizations, or donor agencies.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Chartered Accountant, Certified Public Accountant holding a Certified Accountancy or equivalent Financial Management certification is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in developing and managing financial management processes.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in managing balance sheets, managing costs and containing risks.&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in instilling a financial discipline within the organization, while dealing complex internal and external regulations.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in the development, implementation and maintenance of automated accounting and financial management systems. Advantage for specific experience in SAP-based systems.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledgeable about taxation issues especially relevant to project development organization.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent command of English and Nepali languages, both written and spoken.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communication, coordination skills, management and supervisory skills; demonstrated ability to interact and collaborate with people across departments, divisions and institutions.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(104, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Outreach Communication Assistant&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Manager - Transmission Lines; or Environmental Coordinator</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">B</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:29px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:12px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:21px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:26px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Outreach Communication Assistant, under the supervision of the Project Manager - Transmission Lines, or Environmental Coordinator, as designated, is responsible for the execution of project stakeholder engagement and consultation support activities, organizing logistical and administrative support for project communications at the local level (District, Municipality), gathering and inputting information, monitoring and reporting on communication activities.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Implementation</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support the execution of communications activities as defined by the stakeholder engagement plan or other plan, ensuring that these activities are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain coordination with the Communications team to ensure all field-level consultation and communication activities are consistent with MCA-wide communication strategies;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong>Planning</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize logistics and administrative requirements for communications and stakeholder engagement activities (e.g. travel, venue management, etc.) and ensure that these are delivered and that costs are controlled in line with established budgets;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Reporting</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Collect and input information for use in project monitoring, evaluation, and reporting activities, ensuring the accuracy of data and adherence to established formats for reporting;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Address queries from staff and external stakeholders (e.g. partner organizations, government offices) related to the implementation of project activities to build an informed basis for interaction and increased efficiency in the execution of activities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain a calendar of project activities and ensure that staff and project stakeholders are informed of upcoming deadlines and project progress against milestones to support overall project management.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Completion of Secondary School</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Some prior experience in communications, stakeholder engagement and consultation</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prior experience in outreach in relevant district preferred.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to converse local language and knowledge of local language and customs preferred</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><a name=\"_Hlk535582164\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</a></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(80, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Chief Financial Officer (CFO)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Division:</strong> Financial Management<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Reports to:</strong> Executive Director(ED)<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Band:</strong> D<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Background &amp; Project Description:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nIn September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India - helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nPursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Position Objective:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Chief Financial Officer (CFO) leads the Financial Management Directorate and has overall responsibility for MCA-N financial management activities.&nbsp; The CFO reports directly to the ED of MCA-N.&nbsp; He/she manages up to 4 full-time financial management staff, oversees the external Fiscal Agent, as well as short-term consultants as required.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table align=\"left\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><u>Financial Management</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Ensures adherence to all financial management provisions of the Compact and related documents;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Oversees the Fiscal Agent contract to ensure that the Fiscal Agent is providing all the financial management services, such as funds control and payment processing, required in its contract and in the Fiscal Agent Agreement;&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Reviews and updates a financial management operation manual, known as the Fiscal Accountability Plan (FAP), which outlines all procedures necessary for financial management operations, documents sound internal controls, and designates the officials that have the authority to approve obligations, verify receipt of goods and services, and execute payments;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><u>Planning </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">In coordination with the Project/Unit Managers, estimate the future period cash flow requirements for each Project/Unit, and ensures that all accompanying reports are delivered according to the required schedule;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Oversee automated accounting and financial management system. As necessary, manages system updates and improvements in coordination with external consultants;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Plans and oversees audit requirements and ensures audit findings are resolved timely;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Develops and manages all program accounting reports, including special reports required by the MCA-N or the Board of Directors and the Government of Nepal;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><u>Risk Management </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Monitors and ensures compliance with all aspects of the Financial Accountability Plan (FAP);</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Ensures that MCC funds are exempt from all taxes and refunds for taxes are paid as detailed in the Compact Agreement, Program Implementation Plan, and/or any other associated agreements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Works with others in senior management to ensure that GoN has met all required Conditions Precedent (CPs), prior to any future disbursements of new funds from MCC</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Supports preparation of MCA-N&rsquo;s annual Program budget for the entire Compact period, as well as detailed budgets with the Projects/Unit and any Implementing Entities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Coordinates the development of quarterly disbursement requests for funding from MCC;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Serves as liaison with the Project/Unit Managers, other personnel, and any Implementing Agencies on financial matters and issues;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Monitors expenses against budgets to ensure adequate resources and control of funds.&nbsp; Provides quarterly contract disbursements and other necessary information to the M&amp;E Directorate in order to track process milestones for the Compact;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Supervises the processing and analysis of project-related expenses and ensures that they are in accordance with approved budget, MCC policies, and government procedures;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><u>Administration &amp; Operations</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Manages and reviews the work of related personnel and ensure quality of outputs and provide day-to-day supervision;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Assists in matters related to office insurances, which includes assets insurance, public liability insurance, directors&rsquo; and officers&rsquo; liability insurance;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Reviews and provides advices to contracts related to the day to day operations of MCA-N;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Performs other tasks and special projects as assigned.&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear: both; text-align: left;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><u>Requirements (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"left\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Must hold Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (minimum) from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Accounting, Banking &amp; Finance,&nbsp; Commerce,&nbsp; Finance, Financial Control, Chartered Accountancy Business Administration, Business Management, General Management, Economics, or in equivalent field;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Chartered Accountant, Certified Public Accountant holding a Certified Accountancy or equivalent Financial Management certification is a plus;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Seven (7) or more years of progressive professional experience preferred, (accumulated after acquiring Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree) in managing the corporate finance or finance function, preferably in international development, governmental organizations, or donor agencies;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Proven ability to oversee and manage daily operations of a financial management unit;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Ability to develop complex budgets and manage related financial transactions;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Experience in developing and managing financial management processes.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Experience in managing balance sheets, managing costs and containing risks.&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Experience in instilling a financial discipline within the organization, while dealing complex internal and external regulations</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Experience in the development, implementation and maintenance of automated accounting and financial management systems. Advantage for specific experience in SAP-based systems;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Experience in dealing with taxation issues in Nepal is a plus;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Excellent command of English and Nepali languages, both written and spoken;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Excellent communication, coordination skills, management and supervisory skills; demonstrated ability to interact and collaborate with people across departments, divisions and institutions</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by a specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the confidential classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only. The staff of Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.'),
(118, '&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 366px; text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n			<strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 366px; text-align: justify;\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>६</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 366px; text-align: justify;\"><strong>१. पद</strong>: उत्पादन अधिकृत&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>२.</strong> <strong>तलव</strong>: कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३</strong><strong>. काम गर्ने समयः</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४</strong><strong>. </strong><strong>कार्य क्षेत्रः</strong> काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५</strong><strong>. </strong><strong>जवाफदेहिताः</strong> उत्पादन प्रमुख&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 366px; text-align: justify;\"><strong>उत्पादन व्यापार इकार्इ</strong> -Manufacturing<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">&nbsp;\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">कम्पनीको हर्वल केयर तथा अन्य उत्पादनको उद्देश्य अनुरूप आफ्नो शाखावाट उत्पादन गर्ने वस्तुहरूको मासिक,चौमासिक,अर्ध बार्षिक तथा बार्षिक उत्पादन कार्य योजना वनार्इ सो अनुसार छिटो,छरितो ढंगले स्वच्छ,सफा र गुणस्तरिय वस्तु उत्पादन गर्न आफ्नो शाखाको काम कारवाहीलार्इ नियमित, व्यवस्थित,चुस्त, दुरूस्त वनाउने काम, कर्तव्य तथा जिम्मेवारी उत्पादन अधिकृतको हुनेछ ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;कम्पनीको वार्षिक उत्पादन कार्यक्रम अनुसार जडीबुटी तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरूको सार तथा तेल लगायत आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थहरूको प्रयोग गरी स्वीकृत फर्मुलेशन अनुसार वस्तु उत्पादन गर्ने,गराउने।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उत्पादन प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष सम्पर्कमा रही कम्पनीको लक्ष्य अनुरूप उत्पादन गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">आवश्यक्ता अनुसार आफ्नो शाखाबाट उत्पादन गरिने उत्पादनहरूको उत्पादन कार्य योजना तयार पार्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उत्पादन शाखाका कर्चमारीहरूको कार्यतालीका तयार गरी सो अनुसार काममा लगाउने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">आफु मातहतका कर्चारीहरूले तोके वमोजिम काम गरे नगरेको सम्वन्धमा कामको नियमित मूल्यांकन गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">आफ्नो शाखावाट उत्पादन भएको विभिन्न उत्पादनहरूको गुणस्तर परिक्षणको लागि सम्वन्धित शाखामा पठार्इ चेक जाँच गर्ने गराउने र प्राप्त जाँच रिपोर्ट सुरक्षित राख्ने राख्न लगाउने।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">आफ्नो शाखाको वार्षिक उत्पादन योजना तथा कार्यक्रम अनुसारको उत्पादनका लागि आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थको खरिदको लागी सम्वन्धित शाखासंग समन्वय गरी खरिद सम्वन्धि आवश्यक कार्य गर्ने।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">आफ्नो शाखावाट उत्पादित वस्तुहरू नियमानुसार भण्डारण दाखिला गर्ने गराउने र सो नभएसम्म समुचित संरक्षणको व्यवस्था मिलाउने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उत्पादनका लागी आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थ तथा&nbsp; प्याकिङ सामाग्री समयमा माग गरी उत्पादन कार्यको लागी सहजिकरण गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उत्पादन शाखामा उत्पादन हुने वस्तु तथा सो संग सम्वन्धित कार्यहरूको विवरण&nbsp; तयार गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">बजार माग अनुसारका उपयोगी उत्पादनको खोज तथा अनुसन्धान गरी गुणस्तर निर्धारण शाखा र उत्पादन इकार्इ&nbsp; प्रमुखसंग समन्वय तथा सहकार्य गरी नयाँ उत्पादनका लागि फर्मुलेशनहरू तयार गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उत्पादन व्यापार युनिटमा उत्पादन गरिने वस्तुहरूको उत्पादनका लागि आवश्यक विभिन्न Manufacturing Process (Mixing, Filling, Sealing, Packaging) कार्यहरू गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;महाप्रवन्धक वा कम्पनीले तोके वमोजिमका अन्य आवश्यक कार्य गर्ने गराउने ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">मान्यता प्राप्त विश्वविद्यालयबाट फार्मेसि विषयमा कम्तीमा स्नातक तह उत्तिर्ण गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">औषधिजन्य उत्पादन क्षेत्रमा कम्तीमा २ वर्ष कार्य गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको,नयाँ नयाँ खोज अनुसन्धान गर्न तत्पर रहने&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको र नेपाली तथा अंग्रेजी भाषामा टार्इष गर्न सक्ने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(117, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\nकोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ<br />\r\n&nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>सेवा-प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			तह-६</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>१. पदको नाम</strong> ;- खेती बिस्तार अधिकृत<br />\r\n			<strong>२. तलब(मासिक)</strong>;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३. काम गर्ने समय</strong> ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४. कार्य क्षेत्र</strong> &nbsp;: तोकिएको खेती सम्बन्धी ब्यापारीक र्इकार्इ अन्य जिल्लाहरू<br />\r\n			<strong>५. जवाफदेहिताः</strong> महाप्रवन्धक तथा केन्द्रीय कार्यालयको खेतिविस्तार प्रमुख समक्ष।</div>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>शाखा</strong> :-व्यापारिक र्इकार्इ ,तामागढी</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षा</strong>-फार्म तथा नीजि क्षेत्रममा ब्यबसायीक&nbsp; रूपले खेति हुने बालीहरूको अधिकतम उत्पादकत्वका लागी खेति कार्य एवम अन्य निर्देशित कम्पनीका कार्यहरू व्यबस्थित तरिकाले गर्ने गराउने ।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्वः</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>१ </strong>केन्द्रीय कार्यालयको खेती विस्तार प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन , नियन्त्रण र समन्वयमा&nbsp; रहीआफ्नो फारम भित्र तथा निजि क्षेत्रमा खेतीका कर्यहरू जिम्वेवार भर्इ र्इमानदारीका साथ सम्पादन गर्ने ,र गराउनु पर्ने छ।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n२.बजारमा माग भएका आर्थिक दृष्टिकोणले नाफामुलुक बालीहरूको आफ्नो फारम तथा स्थानीयन निजि स्तरका कृषकहरूद्वारा समेत खेतिको कार्य गर्ने गराउने तथा बालिको विमा गर्नु पर्ने भए केन्द्रीय कार्यालयमा समन्बय गरी&nbsp; वीमा कार्य&nbsp; समपन्न् गर्ने गराउने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n३.जडिबुटी खेतिका लागि प्रबिधी परिक्षण,उन्नतजात तथा उत्पादकतवको परिक्षण गरि उत्कृष्ट नतिजाको व्यबसायिक उत्पादनमा समाबेश गर्ने गराउने कार्यका लागि प्रतिबेदन तयार गरि पेश गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n४.आफ्नो कार्य क्षेत्रमा खेति भैरहेका बालीहरूको आवश्यकता अनुसार गुणस्तरिय विउ बिजनको&nbsp; उत्पादन गरी राख्नु पर्ने बिउ बिजनका लागी उपयुक्त जग्गाको छनौ गरि गुणस्तरीय बिउ बिजन उत्पादनको कार्य गर्ने गराउने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n५.निजि स्तरमा खेति गरिएका बालिहरूका सम्बन्धीत कृषकहरूलार्इ समयमा आश्ककता अनुसारखेति प्रविधि, रोग किरा र संकलन समय बारे आवश्यक तालिम प्रदान गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n६. फार्ममा प्रयोग हुने टेक्टर,हार्बेस्टर, पम्पसेटजस्ता मेशिन,मेशिनरि एवम कुटो कोदालो , जस्ता अौजारहरूको मर्मत संभार,भण्डारण र आवश्यक परिमाणको लेखा जोखा गरि आवश्यक ब्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n७.बार्षिक कार्य योजनाअनुसार सम्पूर्ण कार्य संपादन गर्न दैनिक र मासिक रूपमा&nbsp; कार्य बिभाजन&nbsp; र आफ्नो क्षेत्रमा आवहश्यक जनशक्ती स्रोतसाधन परिचालन गरी परिमाण मुखि कार्य गर्ने गराउने।साथै माग अनुसार प्रगति प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n८.खेति कार्य गर्दा भौतिकपुर्बाधार,उत्पादन लागत ,कार्य क्षेत्रहरू लगायत कार्यको दैनिक ढाचामा&nbsp; रेकर्डहरू अध्यावधीक&nbsp; गरार्इ राख्ने राख्न लगाउने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n९.खेती भैराखेका बालिहरूको छुट्टा छुट्टै कूल उत्पादन लागत र उत्पादन परिमाणको दैनिक र मासिक रूपमा रेकर्ढ बनाइ राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।साथै सोही आधारमा बार्षिक प्रतिबेदन तथार गरि&nbsp; पेश गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n१०.आफ्नो मातहतका सम्पुर्ण कर्मचारीहरूलार्इ&nbsp; निर्देशन र परिचालन गरी निजहरूको कार्य संपादन समेत निष्पक्ष&nbsp; तरिकाले मूल्याङकन गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n११कम्पनीको बार्षिक योजना एवम कार्य योजना बनाउदा आफ्नो क्ष्रेत्रको कार्य संपादनका लागि गरिने सम्पुर्ण कामकारवाही तथा गतिविधीहरूका वारेमा आवश्यक छलफल गरी तयार गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n१२.कम्पनिले समय समयमा आवश्यक्ता अनुसार तोकेका अन्य कार्यहरू गर्ने गराउने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n१३.आफु र मातहतका कर्मचारीहरूको बृति विकासका लगि तालिम ,अबलोकन भ्रमण तथा उच्च् शिक्षाका लागि पहल गर्ने।<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\nमान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा बाली बिज्ञान बिषयममास स्नातक भर्इ सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा कम्तिमा दुर्इ बर्षको अनुभब भएको।एवम कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी (MS Word MS .Excel , PowerPoint ) ज्ञान भएको साथै हुनुपर्ने छ।<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(119, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>६</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>१. पदको नामः</strong> गुणस्तर निर्धारण अधिकृत&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>२.</strong> <strong>तलव </strong><strong>(मासिक</strong>): कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३</strong><strong>. काम गर्ने समयः</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४</strong><strong>. </strong><strong>कार्य क्षेत्रः</strong> काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५</strong><strong>. </strong><strong>जवाफदेहिताः</strong> महाप्रवन्धक</div>\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><strong>शाखाः</strong> गुणास्तर एवम अनुसन्धान तथा विकास शाखा<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\"><strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">कम्पनीमा खेती, प्रशोधन,संकलन तथा उत्पादन भएका वस्तुहरूको गुणस्तर मापदण्ड तयार गरी राख्ने राख्न लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उत्पादित वस्तुहरू निर्धारित मापदण्ड अनुसार उत्पादन भए नभएको सम्वन्धमा गुणास्तर नांप जाच गरी गरार्इ गुणस्तरीय वस्तु उत्पादन गर्न भुमिका निर्वाह गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">नियमित कार्य तालिका वनाई हरेक ४ महिनामा कम्पनीमा रहेका सम्पूर्ण जडिबूटीहरु तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरुको गुणस्तर परीक्षण गरी&nbsp; रेकर्ड&nbsp; राख्ने ,राख्न लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">कम्पनीद्धारा खरिद गरिने विभिन्न जडिबूटी,वनस्पति तथा सुगन्धित घांसहरुको गुणस्तर तथा जलांश आदिका वारेमा जाँच विश्लेषण गर्ने गराउने र आवश्यक्ता अनुसार सम्वन्धित शाखामा सो को रिपोर्ट पेश गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">जडिवुटीजन्य अौषधिय गुण भएका वस्तु उत्पादनका लागि नयाँ नयाँ फर्मुलेशनहरूको अनुसन्धान तथा विकास गरी कम्पनीवाट त्यस्ता वस्तु उत्पादनमा आवश्यक सहयोग तथा समन्वय गर्ने एवम सो वस्तुहरुको&nbsp; गुणस्तर मापदण्ड&nbsp; तयार पार्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">गुणस्तर परीक्षणका लागि अध्ययन अनुसन्धान गरी नयां प्रविधिहरुको विकास गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">गुणस्तर जांचका लागि अन्य निकाय वा व्यक्तिवाट मग भइ आए वमोजिम जडीबुटी तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरुको गुण्स्तर परिक्षण कार्य गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">प्रयोगशालामा रहेका सम्पूर्ण उपरकणको जिम्मेवारी लिने, संचालन गर्ने गराउने, मर्मत संभारको आवश्यकता परेमा सम्विन्धत शाखासंग आवश्यक समन्वय राखी लागत स्टिमेट तयार गरी गराई मर्मत संभार गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">आवश्यक परेको समयमा अन्य निकायहरुसंग सम्पर्क र समन्वय गरी गुणस्तर परिक्षण सम्वन्धी कार्यहरु गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">१० प्रत्येक आर्थिक वर्षको कार्यक्रम र बजेट तर्जुमा हुनु पूर्व चालु आ.ब.को अन्त्य हुनु ३ महिना &nbsp;अगाडि नै आफ्न</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">उपरोक्त कार्यहरुसंग सम्वन्धित आगामी आ.ब.को कार्य योजना तयार गरी गराई पेश गर्ने &nbsp;गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">११ आफ्नो मातहतमा कार्यरत कर्मचारीहरुलाई गुणस्तर निर्धारण सम्वन्धी कार्य योजना वनाई काममा लगाउने, जिम्मेवारी</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">तोक्ने सोही आधारमा कार्य सम्पादन मूल्यांकन गरी गराई राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">१२ कम्पनीलार्इ आवश्यक पर्ने कच्चा पदार्थहरूर्को गुणस्तर Parameters तयार गरी Specification तयार पार्ने .</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">१३ आफ्नो शाखासंग सम्वन्धित नयां खोज तथा अनुसन्धानहरू गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">१४. महाप्रवन्धक वा कम्पनीले तोकेको अन्य आवश्यक काम काज गर्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">मान्यता प्राप्त विश्वविद्यालयबाट रसायन शास्त्रमा स्नातक वा सो सरह उत्तिर्ण</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">सुगन्धित तेल वा औषधिजन्य वस्तु उत्पादन गर्ने सस्थाको गुणस्तर निर्धारण( Quality Control)&nbsp; क्षेत्रमा कम्तीमा २ वर्ष कार्य गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको,नयाँ खोज,अनुसन्धान गर्न तत्पर ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको र नेपाली तथा अंग्रेजी भाषामा टार्इप गर्न सक्ने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(121, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\n			&nbsp;कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n			<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n						<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>सेवा</strong><strong>-</strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong><br />\r\n						<strong>तह</strong><strong>-</strong><strong> ५</strong></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">१<strong>.पदको नाम</strong> ;-जुनियर प्राविधिक सहायक<br />\r\n						२<strong>.तलब(मासिक)</strong><strong>;-</strong><strong>.</strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n						<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय</strong> ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n						४<strong>.कार्य क्षेत्र</strong> &nbsp;:- काठमाण्डौ बाहिर खटाएको क्षेत्रमा<br />\r\n						५.<strong>जवाफदेहिता</strong> :- खेती विस्तार अधिकृत<br />\r\n						&nbsp;<br />\r\n						&nbsp;</td>\r\n						<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>शाखा</strong> :-जडिबुटी खेति</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:638px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु खटिएको व्यापारीक र्इकार्इमा जडिबुटी खेती प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्षा सम्पर्क र निर्देशनमा रही कम्पनीले खेति गर्ने गरेका जडिवुटी खेती वालीहरूको खेती देखि वाली भित्र्याउने सम्ममा गर्नु पर्ने जे जति कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फार्म भित्र तथा निजि क्षेत्रमा खेती कार्य गराउदा वालीहरूको विमा गर्नु पर्ने भए सो का लागी पहल गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बिभिन्न वालीहरूको खेति ,जात तथा प्रबिधीवारे अनुसन्धान कार्य गर्नु पर्दा अनुसन्धान प्लटहरूको वैज्ञानीक तरीकाको व्यबस्थापन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तरिय बिउ बिजन उत्पादन र भण्डारणको समुचित कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">दैनिक ,मासिक र बार्षिक रूपमा फार्म तथा निजिक्षेत्रका खेतिको कार्य संचालन&nbsp; गर्दा आवश्यक जनशक्ती&nbsp; परिचालन गरी सो कार्यको अभिलेख राख्ने एवम कृषकलार्इ&nbsp; समय सापेक्ष&nbsp; खेति ,रोग ,किरा ,जात बारे राय परामर्श&nbsp; र तालिम दिने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फार्म तथा निजि क्षेत्रमा खेति कार्य संचालन गर्दा आवश्यक पर्ने साधनस्रोत, औजाहरूको व्यबस्थापन गरी आवश्यक परेकोवेला मर्मत संभारको कार्य समयमै गरी गरार्इ राख्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फार्म र निजि क्षेत्रमा लक्ष्यित बार्षिक कार्य योजना अनुसार बिभिन्न वालिको नर्सरी व्यबस्थापन ,रोपार्इ र कटनी&nbsp; कार्य तदारूकताका साथ गर्न गराउन आवश्यक निर्देशन लिने र मातहतका सम्पुर्ण जनशक्तीलार्इ परिचालन गर्ने ,दैनिक रेकर्ड राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फारममा प्रगति प्रतिबेदन तयार गर्दा आवश्यक सहयोग गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रत्येक वालीको छुट्टा छुट्टै खेतिको लागत खर्च उत्पादनको रेकर्ड बनार्इ प्रतिबेदनको रूपमा तयार गरि पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनिले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागि भइ राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले समय समयमा आवश्यक्ता अनुसार सुम्पिएको कार्य गर्ने गराउने<strong>।</strong></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\n			मान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्था बाट न्युनतम कृषि बिषयमा प्रविणता प्रमाणपत्र तह वा सो सरह उतिर्ण गरि सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा दुर्इ बर्षको अनुभव भएको एवम कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी MS Word , Excel, PowerPoint सम्बन्धि ज्ञान हासिल गरेको हुनु पर्ने छ।</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(120, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><br />\r\n			<strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong> <strong>सहायक</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>५</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\"><strong>१. पदको नामः</strong> टेक्निकल अपरेटर<br />\r\n			<strong>२.</strong> <strong>तलव </strong><strong>(मासिक)</strong><strong>:</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३</strong><strong>. काम गर्ने समयः</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४</strong><strong>. </strong><strong>कार्य क्षेत्रः</strong> काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५</strong><strong>. </strong><strong>जवाफदेहिताः</strong> उत्पादन अधिकृत</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>शाखाः</strong> उत्पादन व्यापार इकार्इ</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\"><strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जिम्मेवारी दिएका उत्पादन शाखामा प्रयोग हुने मेशिन मेशिनरीहरूलार्इ सूचारू रूपमा संचालन गर्ने, संरक्षाण गर्ने, यथाशक्य मर्मत गरी गराइ वस्तु उत्पादन लक्ष्य अनुसारको प्रगति हासिल गर्ने प्रमुख भुमिका निर्वाह गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन व्यापार इकार्इमा उत्पादन अधिकृतको प्रत्यक्ष निगरानीमा रही काम गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिलिङ्ग तथा मिक्सिङ्क मेसिनमा उत्पादनका लागि हरेक व्याचमा आवश्यक कच्चा पर्दाथको सहि परिमाणा चेकजांच गरी&nbsp; उत्पादन अधिकृतसंग समन्वय गरी मेसिन संचालन गर्ने गराउने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिलिङ्ग तथा सिलिङ्ग भर्इ सकेको सामाग्रीको रेकर्ड राख्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा रहेका मेशिन मेशिनरीको Manual follow गरी मेशिन सन्चालन गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा प्रयोग भएका मेशिनहरू विग्रिन गएमा यथाशक्य सम्भव भएसम्म आफै गर्ने र नभएमा सम्वन्धित निकायसंग समन्वय गरी मर्मत गर्ने पहल गरी मेशिन सूचारू गराउने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा भएको उत्पादनका लागी प्रयोग गरिने मेसिनको संरक्षण गर्ने, उपयोग गर्ने, मर्मत&nbsp; गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिलिङ्क तथा मिक्सिङ्क मेसिनबाट उत्पादन भर्इ निस्केको बस्तुहरूको भौतिक चेकजांच, शिल भए नभएको र परिमाणा जांच गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मेसिनममा आर्इपर्ने खराबिका बारेमा उत्पादन अधिकृत मार्फत सम्वन्धित शाखालार्इ तुरून्त रिर्पोट गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मेसिन सञ्चालनमा आर्इपर्ने साना तिना कठिनार्इलार्इ सकेसम्म छिटो सुधार गरी सुचारू&nbsp; गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">विज्ञान विषयमा कम्तीमा Plus two&nbsp; गरी &nbsp;Machine सम्वन्धी ज्ञान शिप भएको&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडीबुटी जन्य वा अन्य औषधि वनाउने कम्पनीमा मेशिन चलाउने अनुभव भएको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्तीमा २ वर्ष सोही क्षेत्रमा काम गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको तथा नेपाली र अंग्रेजी भाषामा टार्इप गर्न सक्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(122, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\nकोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>सेवा</strong><strong>-</strong><strong>प्रशासनिक</strong><br />\r\n			तह-५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>१.पदको नाम</strong> ;-योजना र अनुगमन&nbsp; सहायक<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक)</strong><strong>;-</strong><strong>.</strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय</strong> ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र:</strong> काठमाण्डौ र आवश्यकता अनुसार&nbsp; अन्य बाह्रय&nbsp; जिल्लाहरू<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता:</strong> योजना र अनुगमन मुल्याङकन शाखा प्रमुख समक्ष।</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>शाखा</strong> :-काठमाण्डौ रआवश्यकता अनुसार बाह्रय जिल्लाहरू</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षाः</strong>- तामागढी व्यापारिक इकाइको प्रशोधन शाखामा सुगन्धीत घास एवम कोरा जडीबुट प्रशोधन कार्य सुचारू रूपले संचालन भै कम्पनीकत्र उतपादन कार्यमा सहयोग पुग्ने छ।</div>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">तामागढी व्यापरीक इकाइमा प्रशोधन युनिट प्रमुखको निर्देशन,नियनत्रण मा&nbsp; रही सम्पूर्ण प्रशोधनका कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य गर्दा गराउदा तहा अवस्थित अौजार मेशिनरिको नियमित सरचारू रूपले संचालन गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यकता अनुसार अौजार ,मेशिनरीहरूको मर्मत संभार कार्यको जिम्मा लिइ मर्मत&nbsp; गरि गरार्इ संचालनमा ल्याउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">ब्वाइलर सेटमा जडित बिभिन्न प्रकारका मोटर लगायत वाइरिङ को दैनिक संचालन हुनु पुर्ब चेक जाच गरी संचालन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बस्तु प्रशोधन गर्दा कम्पनी बाट उपलब्ध मापदण्ड अनुसार प्रशोधन अवधि सम्म र प्रशोधन कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधित बस्तु भण्डारण पुर्ब राख्ने कन्टेनर बस्तु अनुसार व्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तिलाइ कार्य योजना अनुसार स्वस्थ वातावरणमा काम गर्नका लागि अभिप्रेरित तालिम दिने कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्राबिधिक कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तीलार्इ कार्य योजना अनुसार कार्य योजना बनार्इ संचालन गरी दैनिक एवम मासिक रेकर्ड राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।एवम सो को प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कमपनिले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागि भर्इ आफ्नो राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">१० कम्पनीले समय सापेक्ष सुम्पेको कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा प्रविणता प्रमाणपत्र तह व सो सरह उतिर्ण भै सम्बन्धीत विषयमा&nbsp;&nbsp; तालिम प्राप्त गरेको एवम सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा कम्तिमा ५ बर्षको अनुभव भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(123, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली</strong><strong>,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कोटेश्वर</strong><strong>,</strong><strong>काठमाडौ</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:304px\"><strong>सेवा</strong>-प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			<strong>तह</strong>-५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>१.पदको नामः</strong>- टेक्निकल अपरेटर<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक)</strong><strong>:</strong><strong>-</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समयः-</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र</strong><strong>:</strong><strong>-</strong>तामागढी बारा<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिताः</strong>- प्रशोधन इकार्इ समक्ष<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:304px\"><strong>शाखा </strong>&ndash;व्यापारिक इकार्इ तामागढी</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षाः</strong>- तामागढी व्यापारिक इकाइको प्रशोधन शाखामा सुगन्धीत घास एवम कोरा जडीबुट प्रशोधन कार्य सुचारू रूपले संचालन भै कम्पनीकत्र उतपादन कार्यमा सहयोग पुग्ने छ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">तामागढी व्यापरीक इकाइमा प्रशोधन युनिट प्रमुखको निर्देशन,नियनत्रण मा&nbsp; रही सम्पूर्ण प्रशोधनका कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य गर्दा गराउदा तहा अवस्थित अौजार मेशिनरिको नियमित सरचारू रूपले संचालन गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यकता अनुसार अौजार ,मेशिनरीहरूको मर्मत संभार कार्यको जिम्मा लिइ मर्मत&nbsp; गरि गरार्इ संचालनमा ल्याउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">ब्वाइलर सेटमा जडित बिभिन्न प्रकारका मोटर लगायत वाइरिङ को दैनिक संचालन हुनु पुर्ब चेक जाच गरी संचालन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बस्तु प्रशोधन गर्दा कम्पनी बाट उपलब्ध मापदण्ड अनुसार प्रशोधन अवधि सम्म र प्रशोधन कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधित बस्तु भण्डारण पुर्ब राख्ने कन्टेनर बस्तु अनुसार व्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तिलाइ कार्य योजना अनुसार स्वस्थ वातावरणमा काम गर्नका लागि अभिप्रेरित तालिम दिने कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्राबिधिक कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तीलार्इ कार्य योजना अनुसार कार्य योजना बनार्इ संचालन गरी दैनिक एवम मासिक रेकर्ड राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।एवम सो को प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कमपनिले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागि भर्इ आफ्नो राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">१० कम्पनीले समय सापेक्ष सुम्पेको कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\n			मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा प्रविणता प्रमाणपत्र तह व सो सरह उतिर्ण भै सम्बन्धीत विषयमा&nbsp;&nbsp; तालिम प्राप्त गरेको एवम सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा कम्तिमा ५ बर्षको अनुभव भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(129, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Herbs Productions and Processing Co. Ltd.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Jadibuti, Koteshwor, Kathmandu</strong></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>Job Description Form</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\"><strong>Level: 5</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\">\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position:</strong> Marketing/Sales Assistant</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Salary (Monthly):</strong> As per company policy</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Working Time</strong>: As per company policy</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Job Location</strong>: Head Office, Kathmandu</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Reports to</strong>: Divison Head</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 319px; text-align: justify;\"><strong>Department:</strong> Marketing</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Job Duties and Responsibilities</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Identify prospective buyers by following leads of national and international customers</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Identify the product that will best fit the customer&rsquo;s needs and arrange delivery schedules.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Make daily sales calls on existing and prospective customers.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Enter and process purchase orders from our customers, entering all orders on the day they are received.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Assist in preparing, planning and project managing the publication of all publicity material to maximize company&rsquo;s promotion.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Assist in creating marketing campaigns and working with the company&#39;s external PR agency to see them executed.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Assist in creating and developing new innovative ways to communicate the company message to their existing customers.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Manage online e-commerce site of the company</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Contributing to the annual sales and marketing plan.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n.<br />\r\n<strong>Minimum Requirements (Education &amp; Experience)</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Minimum +2 level or certificate level in Management, Marketing, Communications or other relevant fields from a recognized university by Government of Nepal</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Minimum 2 years of proven experience as marketing officer or similar role</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Excellent knowledge of MS Office (MS Word MS. Excel, PowerPoint).</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">A team player with a customer-oriented approach</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(109, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:gill sans mt,sans-serif; font-size:10.0pt\">Our Vision:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:gill sans mt,sans-serif; font-size:10.0pt\"> &ldquo; Our commitment to all children, to have opportunity for quality education&rdquo;</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>WORK CONTEXT/ BACKGROUND: </strong>\r\n<p>In 2000, Rural Education and Environment Development Centre (REED-Nepal) was established with the goal of ensuring quality education for Nepali children. &nbsp;The&nbsp;Education Program Manager (EPM)&nbsp;is responsible for delivering the Teachers Training Quality Education (TTQE) program funded by the Australian Himalayan Foundation in accordance with the Monitoring &amp; Evaluation plan of the program. The TTQE program is an innovative approach to deliver quality, inclusive education to the children of lower Solukhumbu through key program outcomes. The EPL will be responsible to implement the program following the program design; review the implementation through participatory approaches and upgrade the program continuously to ensure adaptability and innovation. S/he will supervise the education program team with coordination MEAL manager to deliver programmatic results as per the annual plan. To ensure a strong evidence based program development, the EPM will manage and deliver on&nbsp;a rigorous M&amp;E plan that includes data collection, analysis and reporting as agreed with AHF. The EPM will be responsible to report to the major donor AHF as per their requirements.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Key Position Information </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Job Title</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Education Program Manager (EPM)</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Reports To</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Programme Director (PD)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Location</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">50% Kathmandu and 50 % Solukhumbu</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Purpose</strong></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The&nbsp;Education Program Manager is responsible for&nbsp;positioning&nbsp;REED-Nepal to devise our organizational strategy, oversee its implementation and assess its outcomes. Incumbent will identify educational needs and drive initiatives that build quality education in community schools of lower Solukhumbhu. &nbsp;<br />\r\n			The purpose of the post is to contribute to the REED in the area of education in general and particularly develop the capacity of Schools.</div>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Expected Results:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Model Schools are demonstrating quality, inclusive education practice.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">EGRP Children read and write competently in Nepali by class 3 under the CLIPS program.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Children meet prescribed government competency and benchmark standards in English, Math and Science (EMS)-100 Schools.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Going to School Support.</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>No. Direct Report:</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">07</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:12px; text-align:justify\"><strong>Decision&nbsp;Making Authority</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:12px; text-align:justify\">With REED policy and procedure.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Important Functional Relationships </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:216px\"><strong>External</strong><br />\r\n			Government related Agencies, Civil Society Organizations, Relevant Institutes<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:205px\"><strong>Internal</strong><br />\r\n			CEO, Programme Director, Finance/ Admin/ HR Manager, Training Manager, MEAL Manager</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:251px\"><strong>Committees/Groups</strong><br />\r\n			School Management Committees, Parents Teachers Associations, Child Clubs<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Key Objectives of the Position </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Major Responsibilities:</div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To deliver the TTQE program following the program design and M &amp; E plan through innovative, adaptive and participatory approaches.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To lead, manage and deliver on the Education Programme agreed with the AHF that includes data collection, analysis and reporting.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To supervise, coach and lead the field education development officers and to deliver programmatic results as per the annual plan (carrying out regular review workshops, brainstorming and interactions with field staff and stakeholders including REED Head Office and AHF for this purpose).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To review the implementation through participatory approaches and upgrade the program continuously to ensure adaptability and innovation to deliver on the identified programmatic outcomes.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To work closely with technical experts and researchers as required for program and Develop training manual cooperation with Training and research department.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To carry out capacity assessments of the programmatic team and advise their professional development to deliver on results.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To liase and network with local HTs, teachers, school management committees, NGOs/CBOs, and other stakeholders in Solukhumbhu as and when required.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To motivate school management committees, HTs, teachers and local communities for their active participation in the project planning, implementation and monitoring and evaluation, as and when required.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To provide technical inputs to local schools and field staffs in the TTQE project area to ensure program delivery.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To monitor and ensure practice of: gender and disability inclusion, child protection and environmental responsibility across the TTQE program.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To liaise with all government line agencies at rural municipality and district level.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To assist the development and documentation of learning materials such as training manuals and appropriate educational materials.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To ensure all activities are implemented as per REED policy and guidelines and project activities are timely completed as defined in the annual implementation plan.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;Receive community proposals, scrutinize, check and verify and develop and submit them to concerned authorities for necessary actions.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Check properly financial status and recommended to payment timely in field office</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To assist different intervention of TTQE Project on model schools, EGRP, EMS and school going initiatives&nbsp; for basic school in coordination with&nbsp; Village Education Committee, Rural Municipality,&nbsp; District Education Coordination committee and schools</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To ensure that appropriate monitoring and data collection are ongoing</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To report to the major donor partner AHF as per their requirements</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">To regularly complete and submit required project management</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Carry out other relevant tasks requested by Programme Director</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h5 style=\"text-align:justify\">Person Specification</h5>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree, Master&rsquo;s Degree (preferred) in Education /Sociology/ Management or other relevant field.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Master&rsquo;s Degree with minimum of 5 years working experience or Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree with Minimum of 7 years working experience (preferably in I/NGO sector)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Clear understanding of issues project has to work on</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge on Education</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good conceptual and practical skill to write project concept paper, design documents and report of the project.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prior experience of conducting Baseline survey and aware of Evaluation and Monitoring process and tools.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to facilitate Training, Seminar and Advocacy programs.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Proven management and leadership ability</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good communication and networking skill</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good proficiency in English &amp; Nepali, both written and verbal</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good time management skills</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Decision making and problem solving skills</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Competent in using MS Word, MS Excel and PowerPoint presentation</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good report writing and documentation ability</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">50 % field visit in the working area is expected</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good working relationship between Education project and other projects including special projects in the working area.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>Core Capabilities</strong></td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Achieving Capabilities:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Achieving quality results and service</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Practicing accountability and integrity</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Communicating information effectively</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Self-Managing Capabilities:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Learning for growth and development</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintaining work/life balance and effectiveness</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<h6 style=\"text-align:justify\">Thinking Capabilities</h6>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Thinking clearly, deeply and broadly</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Understanding the Education sector</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Understanding REED mission andoperations</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Practicing innovation and creativity</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Relational Capabilities:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Building collaborative relationships</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Practicing gender, disability and cultural diversity</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Influencing individuals and groups</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(125, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<h1><strong>TERMS OF REFERENCE </strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:648px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; text-align:left; width:132px\"><strong>Position Title</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; text-align:left; width:516px\">Community Mobilizer</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:29px; text-align:left; width:132px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:29px; text-align:justify; width:516px\">Community mobilization and training support for construction of 23,088 houses for earthquake affected &nbsp;families in the 31 District in Nepal</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:left; width:132px\"><strong>Position Duration </strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:left; width:516px\">1 month to 12 Months renewable</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>General Background:</strong>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">UNOPS is implementing, on behalf of the GoI, a homeowner driven reconstruction project supporting 23,088 earthquake affected households in 2 municipalities and 8 rural-municipalities of Nuwakot district.&nbsp; The project operates offices across the district and provides socio-technical assistance to the identified beneficiaries.&nbsp; The offices monitor construction sites, provide technical packages (drawings + BOQ, etc) and assist the beneficiaries in retrieving their reconstruction grant from the government.</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">In parallel to this homeowner driven project in Nuwakot, UNOPS is also implementing, in the 31 earthquake affected districts, a homeowner driven retrofitting project in which homeowners modify their houses to make earthquake-resilient structures without having to reconstruct their entire houses.&nbsp; This structural reinforcement method allows the beneficiaries to preserve heritage architecture and allows homeowners to keep their traditional houses at a lower cost.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Roles, Deliverables &amp; Expected Outputs</strong>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:25px; text-align:center; width:209px\"><strong>Description of Role</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:25px; text-align:center; width:221px\"><strong>Deliverable</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:25px; text-align:center; width:192px\"><strong>Expected Output</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90px; width:209px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will reach out to the population to which they are assigned to in order to promote each projects&rsquo; objectives.&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will follow up with government agencies to ensure that grants are paid out to the beneficiaries.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will hand hold beneficiaries to ensure that requests to government are complete and eligible.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will educate the beneficiaries on the government processes regarding all grants, grievances, reconstruction, retrofitting, etc.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will serve as liaison between the field, the central UNOPS office, and the local government offices.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will update data on tablet based UNOPS application.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Motivate and ensure beneficiaries participate in the process of housing construction</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate and work collaterally with Technical Assistant in implementing housing construction.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare and submit progress report of housing construction under his/her purview.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90px; width:221px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Conduct at least 600&nbsp; monitoring individual visits each per quarter.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure that positive messaging is provided to beneficiaries and area population.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Face to face discussion with beneficiaries regarding the housing construction .Provide documental proof to UNOPS.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Face to face discussion in between Social Mobilizer and Technical Assistant with regard to the challenges in housing construction minimum once a week. Provide recodes of discussion to UNOPS. Report progress to UNOPS once in a month</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90px; width:192px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Enrol all project beneficiaries to each project on monitoring system.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Beneficiaries take ownership of housing units right from the beginning</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Joint efforts to overcome challenges in the field level</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Project team is updated with progress of construction</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Qualification:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree with One year or 10+ 2 (Intermediate) with 2 Years&rsquo; experience in the field of Community mobilization, capacity building and development.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Work Experience, Language &amp; other Mandatary Requirements</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">At least 2 years of experience in working closely with communities for 10+2 ( intermediate)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">At least 1 year of experience in working closely with communities for Bachelor degree.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Working knowledge in Microsoft Office 2010 and internet. Ability to maintain various types of documentation in English is required.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Working knowledge of English and fluency in Nepali is mandatory.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Planning and reporting; identification of field level issues</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Meeting/ Training management and facilitation skills.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Liasion and communications; awareness raising.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:left\">Fair knowledge in operating smart phone and sharing the project informations such as project pictures, geo-references etc. via mobile messaging Apps <strong>is mandatary. </strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(124, '<h1 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>TERMS OF REFERENCE </strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Position</strong> <strong>opening</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Civil Engineer &ndash; Field Monitoring &amp; Site Supervision</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Industry</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Non-profit/International Development<br />\r\n<strong>Function&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Technical<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Organization Description</strong><br />\r\nA non‐profit social enterprise whose mission is to save lives in earthquakes and hurricanes that designs disaster-resistant houses and schools, trains homeowners, builders, engineers and government officials to build them, works with governments to develop and implement building standards, partners with the private sector to improve building materials quality and create jobs, and facilitates access to incentive-based capital for reconstruction and retrofitting by partnering with financing institutions and government subsidy programs. The enterprise has trained more than 39,380 people on earthquake-resistant design and construction techniques, guided 74&nbsp;organizations in using homeowner-driven design, created over&nbsp;16,768 jobs and provided technical assistance for almost 58,328&nbsp;safer buildings, impacting an estimated 304,440 people.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Position Description:</strong><br />\r\nFor the position of Civil Engineer, we are seeking a competent engineer for its projects. This position reports to the Lead Structural Engineer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Conduct field monitoring of owner-driven housing reconstruction (including of house retrofits).</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Use mobile construction monitoring checklists and collect corroborative pictures through each phase of house construction.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Help compile weekly construction monitoring reports.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Liaising and coordinating with local government bodies on technical issues.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide engineering advise and safe construction and advise to local homeowners, builders and partner organizations&rsquo; staffs.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist in trainings for engineers, architects, drafters and other technical staff including development of training materials and presentations.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist in solving problems and generating solutions in the field for special cases.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist in controlling quality of information and implementation for projects in Nepal.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Communicate and report to the management about the progress/issues of projects implemented by Build Change.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare field reports and assist in other reporting as requested.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Qualifications:</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Civil Engineering with minimum 1 year professional experience in earthquake resistant design and construction of buildings.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work experience private sector engineering firms an advantage. Self-employed / entrepreneurial spirit a plus.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work experience based in remote field locations a plus. Work experience with owner-driven or community driven construction a plus.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge of AutoCAD and/or other Autodesk engineering software is a must.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge of structural analysis and design software will be an advantage.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">No ego, drama, or pessimism; the successful candidate will be flexible, humble, patient, and have a good sense of humor.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluent English and Nepali.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(91, '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Financial Management Specialist (2)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Financial Management</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Chief Financial Officer (CFO)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description&nbsp; </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCANepal. &nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Financial Management Specialist, under the supervision of the Chief Financial Officer, is responsible for examining the daily execution of accounting and finance transactions, monitoring the banking relationship, communicate with the fiscal agent, and serve a facilitating role in budget management and as focal point for the preparations for budgeting and auditing activities.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Financial Management</u>&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor budgets and daily cash flow ensuring that issues of overspend/underspend are anticipated and that remedial measures are raised to management;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the preparation and organization of finance and accounting documentation for budgeting, reporting, and audit activities, ensuring that information is accurate and traceable.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Risk Management</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review and verify a range of transactions (including disbursements, transfers, etc.) and ensure MCANepal/MCC finance and accounting guidelines are properly observed, and documentation is current and accurate to support reporting and audit activities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Examine bank records/reports to determine if any inconsistencies exist and advise the CFO and MCANepal management of issues related to the banking relationships of the MCA-Nepal.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Train MCA-Nepal staff on the proper use of accounting forms and accomplishment of finance and accounting transactions to ensure consistent compliance with MCA-Nepal guidelines and strengthen the transparency of the accounting function.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Administration &amp; Operation</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate and maintain documentation on issues and best practices to support process improvement activities.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors Degree in Accounting, Finance, Banking &amp; Finance, Commerce, Financial Control, or Business Administration, Business Management, General Management, or in equivalent field.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least five (5) or more years of cumulative experience (not withstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience managing financial management processes;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communication, coordination skills; demonstrated ability to interact and collaborate with people across departments, divisions and institutions;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good command of English and Nepali languages, both written and spoken.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 5.65pt; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(114, '<strong><u>Summary of Position</u></strong><br />\r\nTo be responsible for raising funds for NEWAH in line with its fund-raising strategy<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Line Manager</u></strong><br />\r\nReports to the Director<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Job Responsibilities</u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To develop a year wise fundraising plan and activities in line with NEWAH&#39;s fund raising strategy</li>\r\n	<li>To assess donor landscape</li>\r\n	<li>To raise at least USD 100,000.00 by the end of 2019 and as stated in the strategy for the following years</li>\r\n	<li>To develop wining proposals and submit to potential donors for funding</li>\r\n	<li>To prepare report to donors as per their requirements and maintain a good empathy of a partner organization</li>\r\n	<li>To develop fundraising materials as required</li>\r\n	<li>To remain updated on any fundraising opportunities in country &amp; globally</li>\r\n	<li>To remain prepared with ready project proposals for submission to donors on demand at a very short notice</li>\r\n	<li>To network and establish link and communication with major donors in country &amp; with possible collaborative partners</li>\r\n	<li>To work in coordination and harmony with every staff at all levels</li>\r\n	<li>To carry out any other reasonable duties as assigned by the line manager</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><u>Person Specification</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>At least Bachelor&#39;s degree from recognized university with two years of experience preferably in the related field</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication and presentation skills in both English &amp; Nepali</li>\r\n	<li>Computer skill in Word, Excel &amp; Power Point for windows</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to plan and execute a wide range of activities on time</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work hard under pressure to meet deadlines</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to initiate and complete task to a high standard with minimum supervision</li>\r\n	<li>A genuine interest in development and empathy with NEWAH&#39;s work and ethos</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><u>Working Condition </u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This position is based in NEWAH Headquarters, Kathmandu with occasional visits to the field to understand NEWAH&rsquo;s work on ground and to prepare proposals based on the ground reality.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Salary and Benefits (F Level)</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Starting&nbsp;&nbsp; Salary NRS 42,000.00 per Month</li>\r\n	<li>Dearness Allowance NRS 18,300.00</li>\r\n	<li>One-month Dashain Bonus of Basic salary</li>\r\n	<li>PF as per rules.</li>\r\n	<li>Accidental &amp; Medical insurance as per rules.</li>\r\n	<li>Total 33 annual leave and 15 days public holiday.</li>\r\n	<li>Others: As per the rules of the organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(63, 'We are looking for a PHP Developer responsible for managing back-end services and the interchange of data between the server and the users. Your primary focus will be the development of all server-side logic, definition and maintenance of the central database, and ensuring high performance and responsiveness to requests from the front-end. You will also be responsible for integrating the front-end elements built by your co-workers into the application. Therefore, a basic understanding of front-end technologies is necessary as well.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Jobs and Responsibilities</u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Integration of user-facing elements developed by front-end developers</li>\r\n	<li>Build efficient, testable, and reusable PHP modules</li>\r\n	<li>Solve complex performance problems and architectural challenges</li>\r\n	<li>Integration of data storage solutions {{may include databases, key-value stores, blob stores, etc.}}</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><u>Skills and Qualifications</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Strong knowledge of PHP web frameworks Laravel</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding the fully synchronous behavior of PHP</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding of MVC design patterns</li>\r\n	<li>Basic understanding of front-end technologies, such as JavaScript, HTML5, and CSS3</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge of object oriented PHP programming</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding accessibility and security compliance&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Strong knowledge of the common PHP or web server exploits and their solutions</li>\r\n	<li>Understanding fundamental design principles behind a scalable application</li>\r\n	<li>User authentication and authorization between multiple systems, servers, and environments</li>\r\n	<li>Integration of multiple data sources and databases into one system</li>\r\n	<li>Familiarity with limitations of PHP as a platform and its workarounds</li>\r\n	<li>Creating database schemas that represent and support business processes</li>\r\n	<li>Familiarity with SQL/NoSQL databases and their declarative query languages</li>\r\n	<li>Proficient understanding of code versioning tools, such as Git</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(85, '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Communications &amp; Public Affairs Manager</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Communications and Outreach</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Executive Director (ED)&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">D</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background&nbsp; &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-Nepal) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp; &nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Reporting to the Executive Director (ED), the Communications and Public Affairs Manager will manage broadbased strategic communications strategies and plans to effectively promote and publicize MCA-Nepal projects and activities and to strengthen stakeholder participation in the Compact.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Outreach &amp; Public Affairs</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Launch a communications strategy and plan with clearly defined objectives, messages, and an outreach plan with timeline of outreach activities to targeted stakeholders and liaise with MCC counterparts during the development and refinement of these plans;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee all outreach and public relations activities and ensure that the US Embassy Public Affairs Office and relevant implementing entities communications personnel are aware of these activities.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee relationship with stakeholders, focusing primarily on the political parties, Government and the media;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage all MCA-Nepal public events such as forums, press events, workshops and seminars;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee public consultation sessions, in coordination and collaboration with the ESP/GSI teams;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare speeches for ED and other executives public speaking engagements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Write press releases, answer press enquiries.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Plan the annual and monthly work plans for all communications and outreach activities, clearly detailing roles/responsibilities, deadlines and budgets for each activity;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the Finance office, develop and manage of annual and quarterly budgets for communications and outreach activities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the consultative process plan, in compliance with MCC&rsquo;s requirements, in collaboration with the Environmental Social Performance/Gender &amp; Social Inclusion (ESP/GSI) teams.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Reporting</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work in coordination with Monitoring, Evaluation and Economic Analysis team to accurately promote MCA-Nepal results and success stories;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Commission where appropriate photographers, journalists, columnists or film crews to cover issues linked to project activities or special events;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor political developments and develop strategies on behalf of the Executive Director and the MCA-Nepal to deal with a dynamic political environment.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Communications &amp; Productions</u>&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In collaboration with the Information Technology (IT) department, co-manage and co-direct the development of the MCA-Nepal website;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In collaboration with other MCA-Nepal offices/departments, ensure that minutes of meetings of the BoDs are properly recorded and made public in both English and Nepali, within one week of the meeting date, via the MCA-Nepal website;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop MCA-Nepal Branding Guidelines that will adhere to the mandatory MCC Branding Guidelines and manage the MCA-Nepal brand;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure quality output in MCA-Nepal social media plan, brochure and other promotional materials;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Solicit media partners in electronic, printed and social media for the MCA-Nepal to disseminate information about Compact project opportunities and achievements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the engagement with the media to ensure that accurate information about the program reach the public domain;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Act as the conduit for all of MCA-Nepal&rsquo;s, and its employees interactions with the media;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take direction from the Executive Director in serving as the spokesperson of MCA-Nepal;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Perform other tasks and special projects as assigned by the ED.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Communications, Development Communications, Mass Communications, Journalism, Community Development, Business Administration or equivalent field;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Certification on creative writing, photography, film-making is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approximately five (5) or more years of cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after, or during pursuit of required academic qualification) in corporate communications community and public outreach. Experience in development communications is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge and expertise in crafting and delivering messages to diverse stakeholders;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in managing development of print, audio/visual, advertising and promotional communication products;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge in the development of communications strategy, marketing and advertising plans will be an advantage;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both English and Nepali;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good Information and Technology skills, e.g. word processing, power point and other communications and publishing applications;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and demonstrated the ability to effectively interact and collaborate with people in multidisciplinary teams as well as work across departments, divisions and institutions;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge and expertise in group and public facilitation;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated high degree of courtesy, tact and discretion;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have creativity and capability to be flexible to respond to changing requirements.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 5.65pt; text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(89, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Procurement &amp; Contracting Specialist (2 positions)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Management</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px; text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:20px; text-align:justify\">Procurement Manager</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:145px; text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Procurement &amp; Contract (PC) Specialist, under the supervision of the Procurement Manager (PM), is responsible for the delivery and implementation of procurement-related services that include resource acquisition, inventory management, and stock quality control of goods and services relevant to wider organization programs. The PC&nbsp; Specialist shall provide a broad range of contract management services support. The PC shall ensure that contract administration and procurement activities are conducted in compliance with the principles, rules and procedures set out in MCC Procurement Guidelines, Nepal Compact Agreement, and any Supplemental Agreements with respect to Compact funded activities.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong><br />\r\n			<strong><u>Contract Management </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Upon receiving a signed contract from the PA, the PC Specialist will distribute copy of the signed contract including a checklist to the relevant Project Team/Personnel responsible for the management of the contract.&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;The checklist shall provide:</div>\r\n\r\n			<ol style=\"margin-left:40px\">\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">details of all parties involved in the implementation of the contract, their role, title, position, and contact information;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">mobilization activities and timeframe/dates for mobilization;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">list of all contract deliverables, due dates and related sums/percentages due against each contract deliverable or completion point (Contract monitoring tool);</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">details of meetings and other similar events referenced in the contract and their dates;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">identification of contractual responsibilities within MCA-Nepal, e.g. who will be responsible for reviewing/accepting contractual deliverables, approving invoices, etc.;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">timeframe for reviewing/accepting deliverables; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">any other information relevant to the concerned contract.</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Draft and processes contracts for signature for administrative purchases or procurements handled by the PM&rsquo;s office;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists Sector Managers in the implementation and management of contracts;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the PM in contract administration;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Facilitates contract closure plan and implementation.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepares and regularly updates MCA-Nepal Procurement Plans for administrative purchases or procurements handled by the PM&rsquo;s office.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>Procurement Operations</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the PM in the review of TORs submitted by Sectors;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepares and coordinates submission of Procurement Requisitions;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists in the receipt and opening of quotations, bids, proposals and offers;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepares public procurement documents (bidding documents, evaluation reports, purchase orders, contracts, procurement meeting minutes, etc.) for administrative purchases or procurements handled by the PM&rsquo;s office;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists in the facilitation of evaluation of quotations, bids, proposals and offers;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In consultation with the PM, establishes and communicates procurement priorities to Procurement Agent(s).</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the PM in regular reviews of MCA-Nepal&rsquo;s Procurement Operations Manual(s) and Contract Administration Manual(s) prepared by the Procurement Agent(s) and recommend any necessary changes or improvements to ensure it responds to the operational reality of MCA-Nepal;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the PM to ensure that the Non PPG Procurement Procedures are developed in line with MCC Guidance and that it is fully implemented;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the PM to actively monitor the progress of procurements against the applicable Procurement Implementation Plan;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assists the PM in coordinating with MCA-Nepal management and project staff to ensure responsibilities of all involved actors in the execution of a procurement are understood and acknowledged;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Renders overall assistance to the PM as required;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Undertakes all responsibilities delegated by the PM.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Procurement, Business Administration, Business Management, Project Management, Law, Contract Law, Contract Management, Supply Chain Management, Logistics, Economics, Engineering or equivalent field; or commensurate practical experience in one or more of these disciplines.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Must have a familiarity with procurement and contract management in the public sector, demonstrated through work experience and interview.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience drafting, reviewing, ad approving procurement documents.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge of or experience with procurement policies of World Bank, Asian Development Bank, MCC (or other international donor institutions).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated track record of delivering high quality outcomes/projects on time and within budget.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good skills in project management and communications, both written and oral, demonstrated in previous jobs.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in English.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills with office productivity applications (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, MS Project)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in supporting large projects preferably at the enterprise or organization level.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Dynamic, solution-driven, proactive personality (reference checks required).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with the energy sector.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working in multidisciplinary teams across different departments or functional areas.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience with planning and organizing market outreach events for procurement and vendors, speaking to large audiences.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(103, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Assistant to the DED - Management</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Administration</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Deputy Executive Director -Management</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">B</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal (MCA-N) entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-N.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position&nbsp; Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Assistant, reporting directly to the Deputy ED for Management, provides support in a range of administrative services including organization of event logistics, travel arrangements, and maintenance of office inventories and filing systems related to the Deputy ED for Management.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Office Management</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains an inventory of office supplies and equipment ensuring that stocks are replenished on a regular basis and faulty equipment are repaired as needed facilitating workplace efficiency;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains filing systems and databases of all division and project documentation to ensure that activities are well-documented in support of planning and auditing processes;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Administration </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Submit and reconcile expense reports.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take accurate minutes of meetings.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Produce and distribute correspondences, memos, letters, faxes and other forms of communications.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Handle sensitive communication with highest degree of confidentiality and integrity.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Initiates communication within MCA-N and with external service providers, to ensure that logistical preparations for workshops, meetings, and events are in place allowing sufficient leeway in case of changes in schedule or venue;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize and schedule meetings and appointments;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Logistics</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organizes logistics and materials for workshops, meetings, and events to support smooth-running activities for the Deputy ED-Management;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Processes visa applications and travel arrangements, travel disbursements, and other travel-related requirements in accordance with MCA-N&rsquo;s&nbsp;&nbsp; travel policy in order to support leadership activities for &nbsp;the Deputy ED Management;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Completion of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree; and/or Executive Assistant Certification or equivalent Diploma, Degree or Certification.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Three (3) to five (5) years of cumulative experience in General Office Administration &amp; Management (not withstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent time management skills and ability to multi-task and prioritize work.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communications skills in speaking and writing and note-taking.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Attention to detail.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A self-starter who is proactive, takes ownership and initiative.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(84, '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Project Manager &ndash; Power Sector Technical Assistance</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Deputy Executive Director for Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">D</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Project Manager, Power Sector Technical Assistance (TA) is accountable for the successful implementation of the Electricity Transmission Project&rsquo;s (ETP) Technical Assistance Activity, including i) supporting the start of operations at the Nepal Electricity Regulatory Commission (ERC) and (ii) support to the Nepal Electricity Authority (NEA) in transmission planning and operations. Under the guidance of the Deputy Executive Director, Program, lead a team to achieve the goals of the TA Activity from initiation and execution, building collaborative relationships with project stakeholders, and oversight of project budgets. The Project Manager, Power Sector TA, ensures the alignment of Activity execution with the overall objectives of the ETP and the Compact and the judicious management of its resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Management </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the ETP Technical Assistance Activity across all project activities and ensure that these are aligned to the established strategies, frameworks, budgets and resources defined by the Compact;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the Technical Assistance Activity team to ensure the delivery of effective programming by securing high-quality contractors (including development of comprehensive scoping documents; preparing tender documents; conducting high-quality procurements); and overseeing work of contractors by implementing robust contract management procedures;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop tools to support the implementation of project activities, including work plans for schedule control, QA/QC and change management plans, risk management tools, contract administration tools, budget and contingency management tools, and others as required; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage in meetings and other communications on regular basis with project partners in government and other organizations to ensure effective project implementation, promote progress on the program, update understanding of events affecting power sector context, and adapt to new risks or opportunities.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Assistance&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Apply sector and technical expertise to develop clear goals and approaches to implement Technical Assistance Activities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Build the ETP Technical Assistance Activity team through recruitment, training and development, and performance management of staff to ensure a capacity to deliver the project&rsquo;s objectives;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Guide ETP Technical Assistance team to ensure the use of resources and the implementation of project activities are aligned to the overall project plan; Build and sustain authority and support from critical Activity partners such as the Ministry of Energy, the Energy Regulatory Commission and Nepal Electricity Authority (NEA) to achieve the goals of the ETP. This includes developing and implementation of technical assistance activities and achieving planned milestones;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the Technical Assistance Activity team and other MCA-Nepal teams to develop and implement stakeholder engagement and communications activities necessary to support achievement of the ETP goals for Nepal&rsquo;s power sector; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the Technical Assistance Activity team as an integrated component of the MCA-Nepal ETP to project stakeholders (e.g., with national/local government counterparts, civil society, project beneficiaries, etc.) ensuring that collaborative relationships are built and maintained to facilitate the delivery of the programs.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp;Reporting</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Evaluate progress of project components and activities against established goals and ensure these arealigned to compact goals and country context; and Provide MCA leadership and other stakeholders with consistent progress updates and risk analysis to ensure timely and effective organizational action to advance the goals of the Technical Assistance Activity.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Economics, Business, Management, Engineering (Civil, Mechanical or Electrical), Economics, Public Policy, Public Administration or relevant field; Project Management Professional certification (PMP) is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least seven (7) years of cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after, or during pursuit of required academic qualification) of professional experience in institutional reform and organizational development processes, particularly in public sector organizations.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least five (5) years of experience managing complex projects on time/on budget (&gt;$10 million) including procurement, implementation and closeout phases</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience managing other staff</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency with written and oral communication in Nepali and English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Intimate knowledge of, and experience with, Nepal&rsquo;s energy sector, preferably including an understanding of the electric utility operations challenges and related development strategies.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Intimate knowledge of the regulatory and institutional framework that impact the Project as well as the potential role of the private sector in meeting the investment needs of electric utility operations.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience as a leader and in consensus building; strong capability to multi-task and manage multiple work streams simultaneously.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to work collaboratively with multi-disciplinary and multi-cultural local and international stakeholders and counterparts.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 5.65pt; text-align: justify;\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(99, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">ESP Specialist -Environment</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines/Substations or Lead ESP Specialist/Coordinator</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Environmental &amp; Social Performance (ESP) Specialist- Environment , under the supervision of the Project Manager &ndash; Transmission Lines (or the Environmental Coordinator, as designated), is responsible for assisting in providing technical input to ensure the environmental and social performance of all Compact funded activities. This involves assisting the Project Manager in ensuring compliance of the Program activities with relevant national environmental and social laws and regulations, MCC Environmental Guidelines, and the International Finance Corporation (IFC) Performance Standards on Environment and Social Sustainability.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Operations</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA-N Staff, MCC Staff, and other government counterparts to effectively integrate environmental and social considerations into project planning, development, and implementation, including Terms of Reference, work plans, designs, supervision contracts, budgets, timelines, and monitoring mechanisms;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate closely with all MCA-N Staff in the project team and government counterparts to ensure proper oversight of the implementation of all Compact-funded activities, including participating in field missions.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and/or review, with guidance from the Quality Assurance Managers (EHS and Social) of ESP documents including, but not limited to, Environmental and Social Management System, Environmental and Social Impact Assessments and Management Plans, Resettlement Action Plans, Stakeholder Engagement Plans, etc., and under the guidance of the Project Manager, ensure the dissemination and implementation of these tools to improve environmental and social performance on Compact activities;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the adherence of the project team and implementing partners to ESP plans and schedules across different project stages, to ensure efficient implementation of ESP elements and strengthen quality of ESP outputs;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains documentation and databases related to ESP information to support reporting and communications activities.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:29px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelors&rsquo; Degree (Required) and Advanced (Master&rsquo;s Degree or higher preferred) from a recognized institution in the following or equivalent fields: Natural or Social Science, Sociology, Social Work, Community Development, Development Economics, Political Science, Environmental Science, Environmental Studies, Environmental Engineering, Environmental Planning, Environmental Management;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated five (5) years cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification) in environmental and social impact assessment on projects of a similar nature;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with national and international environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(102, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Assistant to the DED for Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Administration</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Deputy Executive Director-Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">B</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position&nbsp; Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Assistant, reporting directly to the Deputy ED for Project Delivery provides support in a range of administrative services including organization of event logistics, travel arrangements, and maintenance of office inventories and filing systems related to the Deputy ED for Project Delivery.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Office Management</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains an inventory of office supplies and equipment ensuring that stocks are replenished on a regular basis and faulty equipment are repaired as needed facilitating workplace efficiency;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains filing systems and databases of all division and project documentation to ensure that activities are well-documented in support of planning and auditing processes;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Administration </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Submit and reconcile expense reports.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take accurate minutes of meetings.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Produce and distribute correspondences, memos, letters, faxes and other forms of communications.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Handle sensitive communication with highest degree of confidentiality and integrity.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Initiates communication within MCA-N and with external service providers, to ensure that logistical preparations for workshops, meetings, and events are in place allowing sufficient leeway in case of changes in schedule or venue;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize and schedule meetings and appointments;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Logistics</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organizes logistics and materials for workshops, meetings, and events to support smooth-running activities for the Deputy ED-Project Delivery;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Processes visa applications and travel arrangements, travel disbursements, and other travel-related requirements in accordance with MCA-N&rsquo;s&nbsp;&nbsp; travel policy in order to support leadership activities for&nbsp; the Deputy ED -Project Delivery;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:17px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Completion of Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree; and/or Executive Assistant Certification or equivalent Diploma, Degree or Certification.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Three (3) years of cumulative experience in General Office Administration &amp; Management (not withstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent time management skills and ability to multi-task and prioritize work.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communications skills in speaking and writing and note-taking.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Attention to detail.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Problem-solving skills.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A self-starter who is proactive, takes ownership and initiative.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(90, '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Communications Specialist&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Communications and Outreach</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Communications and Public Affairs Manager</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCANepal.&nbsp; &nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Reporting to the Communications and Public Affairs Manager, the Communications Specialist will execute broadbased strategic communications strategies and plans to effectively promote and publicize MCA-Nepal projects and activities and to strengthen stakeholder participation in the Compact.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Outreach</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Implement a communications strategy and plan with clearly defined objectives, messages, and an outreach plan with timeline of outreach activities to targeted stakeholders and liaise with MCC counterparts during the development and refinement of these plans;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain and strengthen relationship with stakeholders, focusing primarily on the political parties, Government and the media;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage all MCA-Nepal public events such as forums, press events, workshops and seminars;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee public consultation sessions, in coordination and collaboration with the ESP/GSI teams.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Planning</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and execute of annual and monthly work plans for all communications and outreach activities, clearly detailing roles/responsibilities, deadlines and budgets for each activity;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with the Finance office, develop and manage of annual and quarterly budgets for communications and outreach activities;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop the consultative process plan, in compliance with MCC&rsquo;s requirements, in collaboration with the Environmental Social Performance/Gender &amp; Social Inclusion (ESP/GSI) teams.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Reporting</u> </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Work in coordination with Monitoring, Evaluation &amp; Economic Analysis team to accurately promote MCA-Nepal results and success stories;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Commission where appropriate photographers, journalists, columnists or film crews to cover issues linked to project activities or special events;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor political developments and develop strategies on behalf of the Executive Director and the MCA-Nepal to deal with a dynamic political environment.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Communications &amp; Productions</u>&nbsp; </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In collaboration with the Information Technology (IT) department, co-manage and co-direct the development of the MCA-Nepal website;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In collaboration with other MCA-Nepal offices/departments, ensure that minutes of meetings of the BoDs are properly recorded and made public in both English and Nepali, within one week of the meeting date, via the MCA-Nepal website;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure quality output in MCA-Nepal social media plan, brochure and other promotional materials;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Solicit media partners in electronic, printed and social media for the MCA-Nepal to disseminate information about Compact project opportunities and achievements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the engagement with the media to ensure that accurate information about the program reach the public domain;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Act as the conduit for all of MCA Nepal&rsquo;s, and its employees interactions with the media.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelors&#39; Degree in Communications, Development, Communications, Mass Communications, Journalism, Community Development, Business Administration or equivalent field;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Certification on creative writing, photography, film-making is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approximately five (5) or more years of cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after, or during pursuit of required academic qualification) in corporate communications community and public outreach. Experience in development communications is a plus;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge and expertise in crafting and delivering messages to diverse stakeholders;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in managing development of print, audio/visual, advertising and promotional communication products;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Knowledge in the development of proposals, such as grant proposals, financing proposals or business plans will be an advantage;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent written and verbal communication skills in both English and Nepali;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good Information and Technology skills, e.g. word processing, power point and other communications and publishing applications;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent interpersonal and communication skills and demonstrated the ability to effectively interact and collaborate with people in multidisciplinary teams as well as work across departments, divisions and institutions;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated knowledge and expertise in group and public facilitation;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated high degree of courtesy, tact and discretion;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have creativity and capability to be flexible to respond to changing requirements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop MCA-Nepal Branding Guidelines that will adhere to the mandatory MCC Branding Guidelines and manage the MCA-Nepal brand;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take direction from the Executive Director in serving as the spokesperson of MCA-Nepal;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare speeches for ED and other executives public speaking engagements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Write press releases, answer press enquiries;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Perform other tasks and special projects as assigned by the ED.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"margin-left: 5.65pt; text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nThis Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(101, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Information Technology (IT) Specialist - Hardware</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">IT</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Manager- Administration and Human Resources</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The IT Specialist, under the supervision of the Manager, Administration and Human Resources, is responsible for the delivery and implementation of Information Technology (IT)-related services to include network management and data infrastructure oversight, ensuring that services rendered support the work of the MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee delivery of various IT services (e.g. infrastructure maintenance, database management, etc.) across the MCA-Nepal, ensuring that the quality of execution meets organization needs and established IT standards;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise management on overall issues regarding day-to-day IT operations and provide inputs to improve delivery and efficiency of services rendered;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide recommendations on hardware developments or upgrades for organization use in support of increased efficiency and productivity of wider program deliverables;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop regular testing, update, and maintenance schedule for IT infrastructure to ensure continuity of functionality and capacity to service the needs of the MCA-Nepal;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assess existing procedures/protocols to incorporate improvements based on user feedback to facilitate seamless delivery of services.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fulfill the following tasks (some of them being covered and added in the future IT Scope of Work):</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ol>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide new starters with IT equipment set up to their needs.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage the networks across all sites.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage network prioritization due to limited bandwidth</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and put in place sound back-up systems.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and enforce various IT policies (setting up e-mails, use of internet, accounts delection, etc)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide resolution to IT issues (repairs and maintenance)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain confidentiality, privacy and integrity of IT infrastructure through cybersecurity.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support procurement in gaining new hardware and also provide maintenance and updates to ensure smooth running of IT systems.</li>\r\n			</ol>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree (Required) from a recognized institution in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Electronic &amp; Communications Engineering, Mathematics, Computational Mathematics, and Business Information System or equivalent fields</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum three (3) years of experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification), managing IT infrastructure, systems and solutions in an environment with 10 or more staff.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Significant prior experience in the provision of IT services including vendor relationship management.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:6px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(94, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Road Maintenance Specialist</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:22px; text-align:justify; width:149px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:22px; text-align:justify; width:474px\">Project Manager-Road Maintenance &amp; Technical Assistance</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Band</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Position Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">To assist the Project Manager-Road Maintenance &amp; Technical Assistance, the Road Maintenance Specialist will ensure the timely and efficient implementation of the Road Maintenance Project (the Project). the Road Maintenance Specialist will assist in the implementation of the Project&rsquo;s activities involving (i) Technical Assistance and (ii) Strategic Road Maintenance Works as set forth in the Compact.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Technical Assistance</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist in the coordination with the MCA-Nepal team, relevant Implementing Entities, and other cooperating partners, to execute the activities for the Project under the Program Implementation Agreement;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical support and assistance for the pilot pavement recycling program for potential integration into the works projects;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide technical assistance for the recruitment of consultant services to support data collection efforts and integration into the HMIS database to provide for annual road maintenance and rehabilitation plans;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Reporting</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">As Road Maintenance Specialist, prepare, update and monitor all relevant project management tools including but not limited to: work plans (schedules), procurement plans, detailed financial plans (budgets), risk management plans and scoping documents (activity descriptions, terms of references, etc.);</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Follow up on annual data collection of IRI, SDI and Deflections on the SRN per the Compact and develop necessary remediation measures for consideration by the Road Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Routinely provide updates to the Road Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager on the GoN road maintenance matching fund requirements and their budgeting and allocation per the Compact and PIA requirements;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review and provide technical feedback to the Road Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager of any technical document/deliverable;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Provide routine technical audits of field work and consultant work and suggest remedial action steps for the Road Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager;&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Implementation </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist the Road Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager in the administration of road maintenance civil works contracts;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">As directed by the Road Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager provide coordination with the DOR and other stakeholders for the formal review of design studies and drawings done by design consultants;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Deliver on a timely basis all needed approvals and permits during civil works, including but not limited to design modifications, variation orders and contract modifications.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other tasks and responsibilities as requested by the Roads Maintenance &amp; TA Project Manager of MCA-Nepal.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:15px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:19px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Engineering, Highway Transport, Civil Engineering, or related field; (an additional 5 years of experience can be substituted for a Master&rsquo;s degree.)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Professional license or accreditation in Civil Engineering;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least 5 years or more of &rsquo;experience in roads construction/rehabilitation projects;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least 2 years&rsquo; experience with HDM4 and its application in practice with managing a road network is preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Previous experience in field data collection;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills (MS office, MS Project). HDM4 experience is advantageous.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good written and verbal communication skills in English.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills (MS office, MS Project). HDM4 experience is advantageous.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:11px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(97, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">ESP Specialist -Substation &amp; RMP</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Manager &ndash;Substations or Road Maintenance &amp; Technical Assistance (TA)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:29px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:10px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:23px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:29px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Specialist, Environmental &amp; Social Performance (ESP), under the supervision of the Project Manager &ndash; Substation (or the Road Maintenance &amp; Technical Assistance (TA), as designated), is responsible for assisting in providing technical input to ensure the environmental and social performance of all Compact funded activities. This involves assisting the Project Manager in ensuring compliance of the Program activities with relevant national environmental and social laws and regulations, MCC Environmental Guidelines, and the International Finance Corporation (IFC) Performance Standards on Environment and Social Sustainability.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Planning</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and/or review, with guidance from the Quality Assurance Managers (EHS and Social) of ESP documents including, but not limited to, Environmental and Social Management System, Environmental and Social Impact Assessments and Management Plans, Resettlement Action Plans, Stakeholder Engagement Plans, etc., and under the guidance of the Project Manager, ensure the dissemination and implementation of these tools to improve environmental and social performance on Compact activities;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Assistance</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Engage MCA Staff, MCC Staff, and other government counterparts to effectively integrate environmental and social considerations into project planning, development, and implementation, including Terms of Reference, work plans, designs, supervision contracts, budgets, timelines, and monitoring mechanisms;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate closely with all MCA Staff in the project team and government counterparts to ensure proper oversight of the implementation of all Compact-funded activities, including participating in field missions.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Monitoring &amp; Evaluation </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor the adherence of the project team and implementing partners to ESP plans and schedules across different project stages, to ensure efficient implementation of ESP elements and strengthen quality of ESP outputs;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintains documentation and databases related to ESP information to support reporting and communications activities.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:6px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:101px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Natural Science, Environmental Planning, Engineering, or a similar discipline.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in environmental and social impact assessment on projects of a similar nature.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Familiarity with international environmental and social guidelines and policies, including IFC Performance Standards on Environmental and Social Sustainability.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Exposure to Nepali Environment Protection Act &amp; Environment Protection Regulations derived from working on projects of similar nature.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(93, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\"><a name=\"_Hlk535410570\">Position:</a></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Power Sector Reform Specialist (Regulatory)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:22px; text-align:justify; width:149px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:22px; text-align:justify; width:474px\">Project Manager - Power Sector Technical Assistance</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:149px\">Band</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:474px\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Power Sector Technical Assistance Specialist (Regulatory) under the supervision of the Project Manager, Technical Assistance, is responsible is responsible for the daily execution, monitoring, and supervision of a range of activities supporting the Electricity Transmission Project&rsquo;s (ETP) Technical Assistance Activity related to establishing operations at the Nepal Electricity Regulatory Commission (ERC) ensuring consistency with established work plans and implementation guidelines.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under the direction of the Project Manager, prepare, update and monitor all relevant project management tools including but not limited to: work plans (schedules), procurement plans, detailed financial plans (budgets), risk management plans and scoping documents (activity descriptions, terms of reference, etc.);</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure the delivery of effective technical assistance activities by securing and overseeing high-quality contractors through development of comprehensive scoping documents; preparing tender documents; conducting high-quality procurements; and implementing robust contract management procedures;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate project statistics from multiple sources and review these for accuracy and compliance with established formats to support implementation, monitoring, and analytics;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise Project Manager, Technical Assistance, of issues related to the implementation of the project in order ensure the continuity of project delivery;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor project budget, procurement activities, and contracts, ensuring that these are consistent with established MCA guidelines and that issues and discrepancies are resolved and reported. On quarterly basis, support preparation of disbursement request packages to ensure consistent flow of funding;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor project timelines and milestones, anticipate delivery issues, and ensure that staff and external stakeholders are kept informed of project status to support overall project management and delivery; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain project documentation and Operations Manuals ensuring that these are current and reflecting lessons learned to support the improvement of projects/processes.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>Implementation </u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Execute and/or oversee a range of project implementation and support activities as defined by the project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives, and ensure consistency of quality;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and sustain relationships with critical stakeholders at ETP partners to facilitate implementation of the Technical Assistance Activity through delivery of effective technical assistance, stakeholder engagement and dialogue, and other requirements to advance ETP goals;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor implementation of activities and recommendations delivered under the ETP and identify options to address gaps in implementation or follow through on recommendations;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the Technical Assistance Activity team as an integrated component of the MCA-Nepal ETP to project stakeholders (e.g., with national/local government counterparts, civil society, project beneficiaries, etc.) ensuring that collaborative relationships are built and maintained to facilitate the delivery of the program;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate with relevant MCA-Nepal staff the effective gender and social inclusion into the development and implementation of the TA (transmission); and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and maintain an understanding of all ongoing activities linked to strengthening the power sector to include other technical assistance activities, institutional changes at ETP partners, sector investments, legal or regulatory changes, etc., as required to ensure the Technical Assistance Activity reflects current context</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:15px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:19px; width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelors University degree in Economics, Business, Management, Engineering, or other relevant field of study; Advanced Degree is preferred. Project Management Professional certification (PMP) is a plus.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least five (5) years of professional experience of cumulative experience (notwithstanding whether earned before, after or during pursuit of required academic qualification) institutional reform and organizational development processes, particularly in public sector organizations.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least two (2) years of experience managing complex projects on time/on budget (&gt;$1 million) including procurement, implementation and closeout phases</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency with written and oral communication in Nepali and English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Intimate knowledge of, and experience with, Nepal&rsquo;s energy sector, preferably including an understanding of sector reform initiatives related to the regulatory framework.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Intimate knowledge of the regulatory and institutional framework that impact the Sub-Activity as well as the potential role of the private sector in meeting the investment needs of electric utility operations.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills (MS office, MS Project, Management Information Systems).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:31px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(88, '<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitoring &amp; Evaluation Specialist (2 Positions)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Program</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Manager- Monitoring, Evaluation &amp; Economic Analysis (MEE)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Specialist, Monitoring and Evaluation (M&amp;E), under the supervision of the Manager, Monitoring,<br />\r\n			Evaluation, and Economic Analysis (MEE), is responsible for implementation of the monitoring and evaluation activities of the compact, with the goal of producing timely, relevant, and reliable data and assessments related to the progress and quality of project implementation and the achievement of targeted results by the Nepal Compact.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support the development of and periodic updates to the Nepal Compact M&amp;E Plan</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Implement the monitoring component of the Nepal M&amp;E Plan to provide timely and relevant input to project management and external reporting, including:\r\n				<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n					<li>Define the performance indicators to be monitored along with their baselines and targets in collaboration with project teams; ensure that monitoring indicators are relevant to project management needs and that risks and assumptions included in the M&amp;E Plan are appropriately tracked</li>\r\n					<li>Collect and analyze data to be reported in the quarterly M&amp;E Plan Indicator Tracking Table (ITT), including checking inconsistent values with project leads and implementers, and storing supporting documentation for all data that is reported each quarter.Prepare narrative report to provide analysis of ITT data and provide contextual information drawn from other monitoring work.</li>\r\n					<li>Implement plan to resolve data gaps or quality issues related to M&amp;E Plan indicators and build capacity with the party that produces the data (e.g. government entities or project implementers) or through independent data collection</li>\r\n					<li>Implement field assessments of project implementation and achievement of outputs and intermediate outcomes</li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support the design and implementation of the evaluation component of the Nepal M&amp;E Plan to promote accountability and learning, including:\r\n				<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n					<li>Provide data and documentation required to inform the design and implementation of evaluations to MCC and independent evaluators</li>\r\n					<li>Monitor adherence to the project design and implementation plans and report any deviations to the independent evaluator</li>\r\n					<li>Review evaluation reports, survey instruments, and other materials produced by each of the evaluators hired by MCC to conduct independent evaluations of the Compact projects.</li>\r\n					<li>Manage and oversee baseline/interim data collection to ensure alignment with the approved evaluation design and ensure coordination with the independent evaluator</li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Integrate with MCA-Nepal project teams to ensure that MEE&rsquo;s data and analysis is accurate, up-to-date, and supports the needs of the project teams.Train and guide the project team and implementing partners on the use of MCA-Nepal M&amp;E tools and formats, to strengthen the quality of M&amp;E outputs.Produce reports that facilitate the use of monitoring data by project teams.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support and oversee the procurements and contracts funded by the M&amp;E budget</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\" style=\"width:100%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Must hold Bachelors Degree (minimum) in Economics, Statistics, Monitoring &amp; Evaluation or a related field</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Three (3)-five (5) years of experience in Monitoring and Evaluation, specifically: managing household surveys, drafting monitoring and evaluation plans, assessing data quality, extracting and assessing the quality of administrative data</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience conducting program evaluation</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience conducting qualitative data collection (ex: key informant interviews, focus groups)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience conducting quantitative data collection (ex: household surveys, business surveys)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience extracting and assessing the quality of secondary/administrative data</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willingness to undertake regular field visits and interact with the different stakeholders. Occasional international travel may also be required.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good written and oral communication skills, ability to work with wide range of stakeholders</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Written and spoken fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience in one or more of the following statistical analysis software and databases, such as STATA, SPSS, SAS, CSPRO, Access, Excel and strong knowledge of MS Word and PowerPoint.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent organizational skills related to data and document management</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to manage a variety of tasks and demands to meet deadlines in a responsible and flexible manner.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated experience working successfully in a team</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working in the Energy and/or Roads sectors preferred.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience working with GIS data preferred</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(86, '<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"table table-bordered table-hover\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Legal Advisor</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Legal</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Chief Legal Officer (CLO)/General Counsel</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">C</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth.&nbsp; The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n			Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">The Legal Advisor under the guidance of the General Counsel, is responsible for the analysis of legal matters, drafting of legal documents, and advising MCA-Nepal staff and the MCA-Nepal board related to contracts/agreements/MOUs which may have legal implications for the MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Legal Advice &amp; Analysis</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Render sound analysis on legal issues to support decision-making by MCA-Nepal management and by the board;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise MCA-Nepal management on the preparation and interpretation of transactional documentation (e.g. related to procurement documents, project agreements and employment contracts).</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Legal Compliance &amp; Due Diligence</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Draft contracts/agreements/MOUs ensuring that proper these are consistent with MCA-Nepal standards for risk mitigation, legal documentations, and with country legal statutes;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Build networks within the local legal community and local regulatory agencies, to keep current with legal developments in the country and anticipate how these may affect the work of the MCA-Nepal;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee staff learning and development activities related to legal matters and ethics, to build an informed community and minimize the risks to the MCA-Nepal.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Contract Management</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop standardized contract/agreement/MOU formats for use across the MCA-Nepal, ensuring established practices are in place for the drafting of legal documents.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Support Corporate Secretary/ Chief Legal Officer</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Support&nbsp; the Chief Legal Officer of the MCA-Nepal Board.&nbsp; This includes developing and implementing procedures for the meetings of the Board and ensuring that Board meetings and actions comply with the requirements of the Compact, all related agreements, and the relevant governing documents of the MCA-Nepal (including any law or decree related to the creation or operation of the MCA-Nepal and the MCA-Nepal&rsquo;s bylaws or other governing documents).&nbsp; This function also includes responsibility for ensuring all necessary and appropriate records are produced and maintained by the MCA-Nepal.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Completion of Bachelor&#39;s Degree in Law (Juris Doctor); and must be qualified and certified in good standing to practice law in Nepal.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Specialized experience in the provision of legal advice with a particular emphasis on commercial contracting and labor law.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Approximately five (5) or more years of relevant experience working at a law firm or as legal counsel, preferably with some experience serving as in-house counsel and some experience working in a law firm or as legal counsel in Nepal.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated professionalism, good judgment, and flexibility to meet the needs of the position.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to collaborate effectively with peers as well as work across departments or divisions.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to establish and maintain effective working relationships with people of different backgrounds.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to work with multidisciplinary teams and institutions.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A responsible and flexible attitude and capacity to simultaneously manage a variety of tasks, responsibilities, and shifting priorities and deadlines without supervision.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated history of delivering high quality projects and work product on time and within budget;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">The ability to work under pressure and against tight deadlines.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills (e.g., MS Office, Internet).</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Written and verbal communication skills in English are beneficial but not necessary.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(95, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Infrastructure Lead Engineer -Substations (Senior)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">Project Manager (Substations)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:148px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:475px\">C (high)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n			<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"height:13px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description</strong></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"height:128px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n						&nbsp;Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The &nbsp;Infrastructure Lead Engineer -Substations (Senior), under the supervision of the Project Manager (PM), Substations, is responsible is responsible for the daily execution, monitoring, and supervision of a range of activities supporting the Electricity Transmission Project&rsquo;s (ETP) Substations Activity, including oversight of project preparation, design, works, commissioning and closeout of transmission lines or substations. The SR Engineer will apply consistent project management with established work plans and implementation guidelines to ensure completion of the compact program in the five-year timeline according to specifications and within budget.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Project Management </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under the direction of the PM, Substations, execute and/or oversee a range of project implementation and support activities as defined by the project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives, and ensure consistency of quality;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and implement effective contract and project management processes to support procurement and oversight of design, supervision and works contractors; consistent monitoring of Activity budgets;monitoring and updating of project timelines and milestones; quality assurance and quality control; and regular reporting processes;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under direction of the PM, Substations, leads Substations Activity staff working on specific contract or works package to ensure coordination of technical requirements for successful implementation of the contract and leads engagement with Project Preparatory &amp; Supervision Consultant for that package;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">As necessary, support junior engineering staff to execute work through technical guidance, quality control, and/or mentoring;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and maintain effective relationships with program partner staff (especially at NEA and Government institutions) to ensure coordination around design and construction of compact substations;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under direction of the PM, Substations, ensure adequate integration of environmental, health and safety and gender and social integration requirements during Activity implementation; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain project documentation and Operations Manuals ensuring that these are current and reflecting lessons learned to support the improvement of projects/processes.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Oversight</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review technical deliverables (e.g., design reports), work plans and physical work progress through desk reviews, site visits, progress meetings, etc., and provide guidance and direction to contractors;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate project statistics from multiple sources and review these for accuracy and compliance with established formats to support implementation, monitoring, and analytics; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">As required, interpret technical issues and progress for communication to internal and external audiences. Monitor, anticipate delivery issues, and ensure that staff and external stakeholders are kept informed of project status to support overall project management and delivery</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s University degree in Electrical Engineering or related field.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Seven (7) years professional experience in managing engineering works projects at a variety of stages, including pre-feasibility, feasibility, design construction, supervision and close out.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years of project management experience in the construction of energy sector projects, particularly electricity sector construction projects, especially transmission/distribution.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advanced degree in electrical or civil engineering preferred</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other qualifications (e.g., Project Management Professional) preferred</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience managing infrastructure contracts (&gt;$10 million)</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated understanding/experience with safeguards issues linked to infrastructure development including resettlement and environmental, health &amp; safety issue.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(106, '<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:170px\">Position:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:453px\">Lead Engineer- Transmission Lines&nbsp; (Senior)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:170px\">Division:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:453px\">Project Delivery</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:170px\">Report to:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:453px\">Project Manager -Transmission Lines</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:170px\">Band:</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:453px\">C (high)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"height:13px; text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Background &amp; Project Description </strong></td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"height:128px; text-align:justify; width:623px\">In September 2017, the U.S. Government&rsquo;s Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) signed a $500 million compact agreement with the Government of Nepal. The Compact aims to increase the availability and reliability of electricity, maintain road quality, and facilitate power trade between Nepal and India&mdash;helping to spur investments, and accelerate economic growth. The compact agreement is valid for a period of five years, and is currently in implementation stage, prior to Entry-Into-Force (EIF) at which time the five-year time period begins.<br />\r\n						Pursuant to the aforementioned agreement, the entity charged with implementing the project has been established as the Millennium Challenge Account Nepal entity. This position will assume a critical role in the success of MCA-Nepal.</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">The Lead Engineer -Transmission Lines, under the supervision of the Project Manager (PM) -Transmission Lines, is responsible is responsible for the daily execution, monitoring, and supervision of a range of activities supporting the Electricity Transmission Project&rsquo;s (ETP) Transmission Lines Activity, including project preparation, design, works, commissioning and closeout of transmission lines or substations. The Lead Engineer-Transmission Lines will apply consistent project management with established work plans and implementation guidelines to ensure completion of the compact program in the five-year timeline according to specifications and within budget.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Duties and Responsibilities</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Project Management </strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under the direction of the PM, Transmission Lines, execute and/or oversee a range of project implementation and support activities as defined by the project plan ensuring that these are delivered on a timely basis to support broader project initiatives and objectives, and ensure consistency of quality;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and implement effective contract and project management processes to support procurement and oversight of design, supervision and works contractors; consistent monitoring of activity budgets;monitoring and updating of project timelines and milestones; quality assurance and quality control; and regular reporting processes;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under direction of the PM-Transmission Lines, leads Transmission Lines activity staff working on specific contract or works package to ensure coordination of technical requirements for successful implementation of the contract and leads engagement with Project Preparatory &amp; Supervision Consultant for that package;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">As necessary, support junior engineering staff to execute work through technical guidance, quality control, and/or mentoring;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Establish and maintain effective relationships with program partner staff (especially at NEA and Government institutions) to ensure coordination around design and construction of compact substations;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Under direction of the PM, Transmission Lines, ensure adequate integration of environmental, health and safety and gender and social integration requirements during Activity implementation; and</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain project documentation and Operations Manuals ensuring that these are current and reflecting lessons learned to support the improvement of projects/processes.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Technical Oversight</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review technical deliverables (e.g., design reports), work plans and physical work progress through desk reviews, site visits, progress meetings, etc., and provide guidance and direction to contractors;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Consolidate project statistics from multiple sources and review these for accuracy and compliance with established formats to support implementation, monitoring, and analytics; and</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">As required, interpret technical issues and progress for communication to internal and external audiences.</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\"><strong>Requirements</strong> (<em>Education, Experience, Technical Competencies</em>)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s University degree in Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or related field;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advanced degree in electrical or civil engineering preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Other qualifications (e.g., Project Management Professional) preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Seven (7) years professional experience in managing engineering works projects at a variety of stages, including pre-feasibility, feasibility, design construction, supervision and close out.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Five (5) years of project management experience in the construction of energy sector projects, particularly electricity sector construction projects, especially transmission/distribution;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience managing infrastructure contracts (&gt;$10 million);</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluency in Nepali and English;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong computer skills in email, word processing, spreadsheets, and the Internet. Experience and familiarity with MS Project, Primavera or other project management software and with Management Information Systems is preferred;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated understanding/experience with safeguards issues linked to infrastructure development including resettlement and environmental, health &amp; safety issue;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Willing to undertake regular field visits and interact with different stakeholders;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible and flexible attitude and capable of working with minimal supervision;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Have high integrity and exercise good judgement.</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:623px\">&nbsp;This Position Description is subject to revisions/updates as necessary to ensure alignment to the organization&rsquo;s strategic direction and structure. Revisions to the description are subject to applicable Human Resources policies and procedures, and official versions of each Position Description are maintained by Human Resources.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(149, '&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Job Purpose:</span></strong><br />\r\nThe Regional Operations Associate should play the role in the office as one of focal person for all regions of Nepal. He/she must perform tasks such as communication, system record-keeping, Reporting, Recruiting, Training and assisting in the establishment departments&rsquo; documentation. He/she has to have the ability to support sales/service employees operation by communicating, collecting, compiling, formatting and reporting information and material.<br />\r\nThe Coordinator has to assist the Group HR in developing and managing documentation, according to the need. He/she should also keep abreast of developments in overall human resource management, day-to-day operations, handling issues &amp; complain, methodologies and technologies.<br />\r\n<strong>Duties and responsibilities</strong><br />\r\nThe primary job duties and responsibilities:<br />\r\n<strong><u>Sales force management, Information Management &amp; Documentation</u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To do Planning, Monitoring and reporting about daily attendance &amp; leave status and Coordinate with the employees to ensure they are present in their work stations.</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for&nbsp;managing and supervising people, and ability to act as a liaison between employees and company</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare daily HR progress report and make timely presentations.</li>\r\n	<li>Compile, review and act to meet company standards</li>\r\n	<li>Communicate processes and policies to employees</li>\r\n	<li>Confirm incorporation of requirements from HR, Compliance, Legal and Risk into end-to-end flow.</li>\r\n	<li>Collection of timesheet or attendance, complying and recording the detail on daily basis.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure proper documentation and dissemination of the logistics items&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Create and build strong key management relationship with employees &amp; client personnel</li>\r\n	<li>Create comprehensive&nbsp;operations report on daily &amp; monthly basis</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible for the analysis and reporting of the tasks</li>\r\n	<li>Responsible in coordinating and communicate work, Supervise and extract output</li>\r\n	<li>Must maintain databases, generate reports, and check emails, mails and send prompt replies for the action to be taken in a timely manner</li>\r\n	<li>Recruit new staffs and train</li>\r\n	<li>Provide operational support to client and the company in terms of preparing report, resolving pending issues and consulting for betterment of the sales force</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in the preparation of monthly operational plan wherever required</li>\r\n	<li>Assist in data and document collection to record keeping</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate with employee on any training and development activities or program on monthly or quarterly basis</li>\r\n	<li>Arrangement of venues, accessories and other items required for the training program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Job specifications:-</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 years and above of experience in Operations or management of 30-50+ employees or similar role</li>\r\n	<li>Must have possess Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or Masters preferable</li>\r\n	<li>Experience with Human Resources Information Systems including payroll tools</li>\r\n	<li>Good knowledge of labor legislation</li>\r\n	<li>Strong Leadership abilities with organizational skills&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to supervise and manage tasks and personnel to achieve organizational objectives.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to troubleshoot personnel or other business related issues.</li>\r\n	<li>Must possess a valid Driver&#39;s License</li>\r\n	<li>Be able to go to the regions wherever if necessary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(147, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>जडिबुटी</strong> <strong>उत्प</strong><strong>f</strong><strong>दन</strong> <strong>तथा</strong> <strong>प्रशोधन</strong> <strong>कं</strong><strong>.</strong><strong>ली</strong><strong>,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कोटेश्वर</strong><strong>,</strong><strong>काठमाडौ</strong>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:313px\"><strong>कार्य</strong> <strong>विवरण</strong> <strong>फारम</strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:310px\"><strong>सेवाः </strong>प्रशासनिक &nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong>६</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:313px\"><strong>१. पदको नामः &nbsp;</strong>प्रशासन अधिकृत &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलव (मासिक)ः </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३. काम गर्ने समयः </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४. कार्यक्षेत्रः </strong>काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५. जवाफदेहिताः </strong>मानव संशाधन विभाग प्रमुख समक्ष&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:310px\"><strong>शाखा - </strong>मानव संशाधन</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>कामको जिम्मेवारी र जिम्मेवारीहरू</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">मानव संशाधन विभाग प्रमुखको नियन्त्रण र निर्देशनमा रहि कम्पनीमा मानव संशाधनको आवश्यकतानुसार नियुक्ति,सरुवा, वढुवा र नियमानुसार विभागिय कारवाही र कार्य सम्पादन मूल्यांकन कार्यहरु गर्ने, गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कामको आवश्यकताको आधारमा कर्मचारीहरुको वार्षिक रुपमा दरवन्दी थपघट, संशोधन गराउन थप गर्नु पर्ने पदहरुको कार्य विवरणहरु तयार गरी पेश गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्पनीमा खुला तथा वढुवा पदपूर्तिको लागि परीक्षा संचालन गर्ने गराउने वा अन्र्तवार्ता लिने कार्यमा मानव संशाधन विभाग प्रमुखलाई मद्दत गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कर्मचारीहरुको मासिक, वार्षिक, हाजिर तथा विदाहरु एवं कार्य सम्पादन मूल्यांकन, ग्रेड, पुरस्कार, दण्ड, लगायतका काम कारवाहीहरुको रेकर्डहरु तयार गर्न लगाई व्यक्तिगत फायल तयार गरी राख्ने, राख्न लगाउने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्पनीका कर्मचारीका दक्षता ,क्षमता अभिवृद्धि गर्न जनशक्ति विकासको योजनाहरु तयार गर्ने ,गराउने&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">मानव संशाधन तथा प्रशासकीय काम कारवाहीमा आवश्यकतानुसारका तथ्यांक र विवरणहरु अद्यावधिक गराई राख्ने, राख्न लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रशासकीय काम कारवाहीहरुको सम्बन्धमा र कर्मचारी व्यवस्थापनका सम्बन्धमा अन्य कार्यालयहरु वा निकायहरुसंग गर्नु पर्ने पत्राचार एवम सो संग सम्वन्धित काम कारवाहीहरु गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अफिसमा दैनिक आदान प्रदान हुने चिठृी पत्रहरुको सुव्यवस्थापन मिलाउने । कर्मचारीहरुको दैनिक हाजिरी रेखदेख गर्ने । कार्यालयको अनुशासनलाई कडाइका साथ पालना गर्ने गराउने कार्यमा समुचित व्यवस्था गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अन्य कार्यालय र निकायहरुबाट माग भई आउने प्रशासकीय काम कारवाही सम्वन्धी र कर्मचारी व्यवस्थापन सम्वन्धी तथ्यांक र विवरणहरु तयार गरी गर्न लगाई पठाउने ।&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रशासकीय काम कारवाहीहरुलाई वढी सक्षम, प्रभावकारी र समय सापेक्ष वनाउन अध्ययन गरी राय परामर्शहरु मानव संशाधन विभाग प्रमुख समक्ष पेश गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">आन्तरिक प्रशासन सम्वन्धी कार्य जिम्वेवारीः</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कार्यालय र कार्यालय हाता वा वरिपरि सरसफाई गरी गर्न लगाई राख्ने । शान्ति सुरक्षाको उचित व्यवस्थापन मिलाई राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रशासकीय काम कारवाहीका लागि आवश्यक तथ्यांक फाराम, विवरण फाराम, आदि आवश्यकतानुसार छपाई गर्न लगाई कार्य संचालन गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">सवारी साधनहरुको नियमानुसार नविकरणको व्यवस्था मिलाउने,सवारी साधनको समुचित संरक्षण र सदुपयोग गर्ने&nbsp; सम्वन्धि कार्य गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्पनीको स्वामित्वमा रहेका वा उपयोगमा रहेका घर,जग्गा,जमिन लगायतका भौतिक सम्पत्तिहरु आदिको संरक्षण,व्यवस्थापनको समुचित व्यवस्था मिलाउने र त्यस्ता सम्पत्तिहरुको नियमानुसार तिर्नु वुझाउनु पर्ने कर वा दर्ता नविकरणको व्यवस्था मिलाउने र संरक्षणको काम गर्ने&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्पनीको लोगो,सन्चो लगायतका हर्वल केयर उत्पादनहरुमा प्राप्त व्यापारिक चिन्ह (ट््रेडमार्क),डिजाइन लगायतका वौद्धिक सम्पत्तीको दर्ता प्रमाणपत्रहरुको समुचित संरक्षणको व्यवस्था मिलाउने र&nbsp; नियमानुसार समय समयमा नविकरण गर्ने ,गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कार्यालय प्रयोजनका जिन्सी सर समानहरुको लगत खडा गरि तीनिहरुको समुचित रेखदेख, नियन्त्रण र संरक्षणको व्यवस्था गर्ने, मर्मतसंभार गराउने र लिलाम गर्नुपर्ने सरसामानहरुको विवरण तयार गरि नियमानुसार लिलाम विक्रीको प्रवन्ध मिलाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">केन्द्रीय कार्यालयको प्रयोजनका लागि आवश्यक मसलन्द ,छपाई लगायतका अन्य सर सामानहरुको आवश्यक्ता अनुसार खरिद गर्नका लागि लागत इष्टिमेट गरी गराई नियमानुसार खरिद प्रकृयाका लागि विभागिय प्रमुख समक्ष पेश गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">महाप्रवन्धक तथा शाखा प्रमुखले तोकेको अन्य कम्पनीको आवश्यक्ता अनुसार गर्नुपर्ने काम काज गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">मान्यता प्राप्त विश्वविद्यालयबाट सार्वजनिक प्रशासन सम्वन्धि विषयमा कम्तिमा स्नातक वा सो सरह उत्र्तीण भएको र कुनै कम्पनी वा संघ संस्थामा मानव संशाधन वा कर्मचारी प्रशासन,स्टोर किपिङमा कम्तीमा ४ वर्षको अनुभव प्राप्त तथा सो विषयमा स्नातकोत्तर भएमा&nbsp; २ वर्षकोे अनुभव प्राप्त भएको हुनुपर्नेछ ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">साथै टिमवर्कमा काम गर्नसक्ने दक्षता,क्षमता भएको , अंगे्रजी तथा नेपाली भाषामा राम्रो दख्खल भई पावर प्वाइन्ट प्रेजेन्टेसन दिन सक्ने, विषय वस्तुको शिघ्र ग्रहण क्षमता भएको र Computer सम्वन्धि (MS Word, MS Excell) राम्रो ज्ञानभएको, नेपाली तथा अगं्रेजीमा टाइप गर्न सकने ,आवश्यक्ता अनुसार काठमाण्डौ वाहिर गई कामकाज गर्न तत्पर हुनुपर्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(146, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div><strong>जडी बूटी प्रोडक्शंस र प्रोसेसिंग कम्पनी लिमिटेड</strong><br />\r\n<strong>जडीबूटी,</strong>&nbsp;<strong>कोटेश्वर, काठमाडौं</strong>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:313px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:310px\"><strong>तह-५</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:313px\"><strong>१.पदको नाम</strong><strong>-</strong> बजार सहायक<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक)</strong><strong>-</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय</strong><strong>-</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र</strong><strong>-</strong> काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता</strong><strong>-</strong> विभाग प्रमुख समक्ष</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:310px\"><strong>विभाग</strong>- मार्केटिंग</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>कामको जिम्मेवारी र जिम्मेवारीहरू</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">राष्ट्रिय र अन्तर्राष्ट्रिय ग्राहकहरूको&nbsp;निम्न पक्षले संभावित खरीदारहरूलाई पहिचान गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">ग्राहकको आवश्यकताहरू बुझि उत्पादनको पहिचान गरि सबै&nbsp; डेलिभरी कार्यक्रमहरू व्यवस्थित गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">विद्यमान र अवधारणात्मक ग्राहकहरूमा दैनिक बिक्री कलहरू गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">ग्राहकहरूको खरिद आदेशहरू प्रविष्ट गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">पुनर्विक्रय, योजना र परियोजनालाई&nbsp;अधिकतम&nbsp;गर्नका लागि सबै प्रचार सामग्रीको प्रकाशन प्रबन्ध गर्ने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रचार प्रसार र बाजार प्रबन्धन् को लागि कम्पनी को बाह्य एजेन्सी संग कार्यान्वयन गर्न सहायता&nbsp;गर्ने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">आफ्नो मौजूदा ग्राहकहरु लाई कम्पनी संदेश को संचार गर्न को लागि नयाँ नवीन तरिकाहरु विकास गर्ने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्पनीको अनलाइन ई-बैंकिंग साइट प्रबन्ध गर्ने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">वार्षिक बिक्री र मार्केटिंग प्लानमा सहयोग गर्ने</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>न्यूनतम आवश्यकता (शिक्षा र अनुभव)</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट मार्केटिंग, कम्युनिकेशन्समा&nbsp; न्यूनतम&nbsp;+2 स्तर वा प्रमाणपत्र स्तर&nbsp; शैक्षिक योग्यता प्राप्त गरेको</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">बजार सहायक वा सो सराहा कम्ति्मा २ बर्ष आनुभव भयको हुनुपर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्प्युटरमा MsWord,Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने छ</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(150, '<h1>TERMS OF REFERENCE</h1>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100.0%\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:38px; width:24.98%\"><strong>Position Title</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:38px; width:75.02%\">Brand Promoters-10</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:38px; width:24.98%\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:38px; width:75.02%\">To&nbsp;maximize sales&nbsp;of the company&#39;s product and achieve sales target.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:38px; width:24.98%\"><strong>Department </strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:38px; width:75.02%\">Sales</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Description of Role:</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Provide mobile handset experience/ demo to customer</li>\r\n	<li>Provide technical advice and assistance to customers</li>\r\n	<li>Update consumer about the ongoing offers and changes in the product line</li>\r\n	<li>Target achievement</li>\r\n	<li>Collect and report market information on interested matters to company management</li>\r\n	<li>Market feedback (Product ,Competition) as required</li>\r\n	<li>Stock Status Reporting, support retailer in order replenishment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Specification:</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Intermediate (+2)</li>\r\n	<li>Age &ndash; 20 to 26 years</li>\r\n	<li>1-2 years of work experience in sales preferably from Mobile /Telecom Industry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(145, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली</strong><strong>,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; कोटेश्वर</strong><strong>,</strong><strong>काठमाडौ</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:690px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:348px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:342px\"><strong>सेवा-प्रशासन </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>तह-५</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:348px\">१.पदको नामः- स्टोर सहायक<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक):- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समयः- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र:- काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिताः- के.का. स्टोर शाखा</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:342px\">शाखाः केन्द्रीय कार्याल</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:690px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			शाखाप्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन, नियन्त्रण, सम्पर्क र समन्वयमा रही तल लेखिएका र तोकिएका आफ्नो शाखासंग सम्वन्धित कार्यहरु कम्पनीको उद्देश्य, नीति र निर्देशन भित्र रहेर इमान्दारिताकासाथ सम्पादन र सम्पन्न गर्नु पर्ने कर्तव्य स्टोर सहायकको हुने छ ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>कार्य जिम्मेवारी र दायित्वः</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">भण्डार गरिएका सुगन्धित तेल, आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थ, हर्वलकेयर उत्पादनको रेकर्ड लेजर अद्यावधिक गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखाको लागि आवश्यक सामानहरूको आम्दानी र खर्च स्पष्ट र व्यवस्थित खाता तयार गरी राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">सुगन्धित तेल, हर्वलकेयरउत्पादन तथा आवश्यक कच्चा पर्दाथको हरेक तीन तीन महिनामा गुणस्तर परिक्षण गरार्इ अभिलेख स्पष्ट गरार्इ राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">वार्षिक खर्चको लागि खरिद शाखाबाट खरिद भर्इ प्राप्त भएका सामानहरू स्टोर दाखिला गर्ने नियमानुसार आवश्यकतानुसार माग गरिएका सामानहरूको निकासा गर्ने र आम्दानी खर्च अभिलेख खाताहरू तयार गरि राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीको केन्द्रीय कार्यालय स्थित प्रशासकीय भवन, कारखाना भवन र स्टोर भवनमा रहेका सम्पूर्ण मेशिनरी र जिन्सी सरसामानहरुको बैज्ञानिक ढांचाको लगत तयार गरी राख्ने । जसमा मेशिन मेशिनरीहरु, जिन्सी सामानको विवरण, सामान, रहेको शाखा, जिम्मेवारी लिने अधिकारी आदिको स्पष्ट अभिलेख राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">हरेक आर्थिक वर्षको अन्त्यमा सम्पूर्ण मेशिनरी र जिन्सी सर सामानहरुको परिक्षण गरी गराई के कस्तो अवस्थामा छन् अभिलेखहरु स्पष्ट हुने गरी अद्यावधिक गराई राख्ने र सो को सम्वन्धित जिम्मेवारी लिने अधिकारीहरुलाई नियमित जानकारी गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">वाहिरबाट खरिद भई आउने तथा शाखा प्रशाखा एवं निजी क्षेत्रका कृषकहरुबाट प्राप्त हुन आउने सुगन्धित &nbsp;तेलहरुलाई छटृा छटै रुपमा स्टोर दाखिला गरी स्पष्टर सुरक्षित रुपमा भण्डार गर्ने व्यवस्था मिलाउने, मिलाउन लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीको हितका लागि एक अर्का शाखाका बीचमा सुमधुर सम्बन्ध कायम गर्ने, कार्यालयको गोप्यता पुर्ण रुपमा कायम गर्ने र गोप्य रहनु पर्ने शाखासंग सम्वन्धित जानकारी असम्वन्धित पक्षलाई भएमा त्यसको जिम्मेवारी शाखा प्रमुखको हुने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">विक्रि शाखाबाट विक्री गरिने हर्वलकेयर तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरुलाई सुरक्षित प्याकिंग गरी गर्न लगाई सामान दिने, पठाउने कार्य गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट कम्तीमा &nbsp;कुनै पनि फ्याक्ल्ती प्लस तु वा सो सरह उत्रिन्न भयि समबन्धित काममा कम्तीमा २ वर्षको अनुभव भएको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको &nbsp;।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(144, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">कार्य विवरण फारम</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">सेवा-प्राबिधिक<br />\r\n			तह-७</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">१.पदको नाम ;-प्रशोधन बिस्तार अधिकृत<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक);-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समय ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;: काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिता.-महाप्रबन्धक&nbsp; समक्ष।</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">शाखा :-प्रशोधन<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षा</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कम्पनि</strong> <strong>क</strong> <strong>बिविन्न</strong> <strong>प्रशोधन</strong> <strong>केन्द्र</strong> <strong>लाई</strong> <strong>सुचारु</strong> <strong>रुप</strong> <strong>मा</strong> <strong>सन्चालन</strong> <strong>गर्ने</strong> <strong>र</strong> <strong>प्रशोधन</strong> <strong>कार्य</strong> <strong>लाई</strong> <strong>बजार</strong> <strong>को</strong> <strong>माग</strong> <strong>अनुसार</strong> <strong>बिस्तार</strong> <strong>गर्ने</strong><strong>कार्य, जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">महा प्रबन्धकको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन,नियन्त्रण र समन्वयमा रहि आफ्नो शाखा संग सम्बन्धी कार्यहरू कम्पनिको उदेश्य नीति नियम अनुसार योजना कार्यान्वयनको कार्य इमान्दारीताका साथ सम्पादन गर्ने गराउनु पर्ने छ।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले प्रशोधनका लगि उपलब्ध गरार्इएका वस्तुहरूसु-व्ययवस्थित तरिकाले प्रशोधन गराउन कार्य योजना बनार्इ संचालन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">खेति शाखा लगायत प्रशोधनका लागि वस्तु उत्पादन एवम खरिद क्षेत्रमा भ्रमण गरि बस्तु आपूर्तिको तालिक तयार गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्यको आवश्यकता&nbsp; अनुगमन गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधनमा प्रयोग हुने टेक्टर मेशिनरी लगायत अन्य सामानहरूको आवश्यकता अनुसार खरिद तथा मर्मत कार्यको व्यवस्थापन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">वस्तु प्रशोधन भर्इ उत्पादन हुने तेल तथा सारहरूको उचित भण्डारणका लगि कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कच्चा पदार्थ र प्रशोधित बस्तुको नियमित अभिलेख राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">सम्बन्धित शाखाहरू र क्षेत्रबाट प्राप्त कच्चा पदार्थको कम्पनिले तोकेको दर रेट अनुसार भए नभएको हेरी अभिलेख राख्ने।एवम रका भुक्तानीको व्यवस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यक रकम निकासा का लागि केन्द्रिय कार्यालयमा पहल गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मातहतका कर्मचारीहरको बृद्दि विकाशका लागि तालिम,अबलोकन भ्रमण,उच्च् शिक्षा हासिलका लागि पहल गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु मातहतका सम्पूर्ण कर्मचारीहरूको निष्पक्ष मुल्याङकनकत्र कार्य गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागी भर्इ आफ्नो क्षेत्रको बार्षिक योजना र कार्ययोजना बनाउन सक्रिय सहभागिता जनाउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले सुम्पेको थप कार्यहरू गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\nमान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट न्युनता इण्डष्ट्रियल इन्जिनियरिङ वा केमिस्त्रि विषयमा स्नातकोतर उतिर्ण भर्इ सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा न्युनतम दुर्इ बर्षको अनुभव भएको तथा कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी MsWord, Ms Excel,Powerpointसम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(143, '<div><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली</strong><strong>,</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; कोटेश्वर</strong><strong>,</strong><strong>काठमाडौ</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:690px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:348px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:342px\"><strong>सेवा-प्राविधिक</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>तह</strong><strong>-</strong><strong>५</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:348px\">१.पदको नामः- खेति तथा संकलन सहायक<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक):- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समयः- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र:- <strong>काठमाडौ</strong><br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिताः- के.का.को.खेती तथा संकलन, प्रमुख<br />\r\n			&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; समक्ष</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:342px\">शाखाः केन्द्रीय कार्यालय, काठमाडौं</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:690px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षाः</u></strong><strong><u>&divide;</u></strong> कम्पनीको केन्द्र तथा विभिन्न इकार्इहरूमा कम्पनीको योजना अनुसार खेती तथा संकलन कार्यहरूमा सहजता आउने ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>कार्य जिम्मेवारी र दायित्वः</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">खटिएको क्षेत्रमा सम्वन्धित शाखा प्रमुखको निर्देशन र प्रत्यक्ष सम्पर्कमा रही कम्पनीले सुप्पेको कृषि र जडिवुटी संकलन सम्वन्धी कार्यहरू तोकिएको समयमा गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">खटिएको क्षेत्रमा कम्पनीको योजना तथा कार्यक्रम अनुसारका कार्य, जडिवुटी खेती सम्वन्धी कार्य सुचारू रूपले सम्पन्न गर्ने, गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिवुटी संकलन क्षेत्रमा कार्य गर्दा कम्पनीको संकलन लक्ष अनुरूप संकलन हुने क्षेत्रमा गर्इ अपनाउनु पर्ने संकलन प्रकृया अपनार्इ संकलन समय र परिमाण अनुसार गुणस्तरीय वस्तु संकलनको कार्य गर्ने, गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिवुटी खेती कार्य गराउनु पर्ने भए सो अनुसार गर्ने संकलित वा उत्पादित वस्तु सुव्यवस्थित तरिकाले प्रशोधन गर्नु पर्ने व्यापारिक इकार्इ वा कम्पनीले तोकेको स्थानसम्म ढुवानी गर्ने, गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिवुटी संकलन कार्य गर्दा संकलित वस्तु सुव्यवस्थित तरिकाले प्रशोधन गर्नु पर्ने व्यापारिक इकार्इ वा कम्पनीले तोकेको स्थानसम्म ढुवानी गर्ने, गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलित वस्तुको भुक्तानिका लागि व्यवस्था गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिल्डमा संकलन कार्य गर्दा सम्वन्धित क्षेत्रमा व्यक्ति, संस्थसित समन्वय गर्नु पर्ने भए सो समेत गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">खेती गरिका वालीहरूको समयमै हार्वेस्टिङ्क गरी गरार्इ प्रशोधनका लागि प्रशोधन संयन्त्रसम्म पुर्याउने व्यवस्था गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन स्थलमा भएका टेक्टर, हार्भेस्टर लगायत अन्य मेशिन उपकरणहरूको समुचित प्रयोग गर्ने गराउने साथै त्यस्ता मेशिन उपकरणहरूको संरक्षण गर्ने व्यवस्था मिलाउने र मर्मत संभार गराउन पर्ने भए सो गरी राख्ने, राख्न लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु खटिएको क्षेत्रमा सम्पन्न कार्यहरूको नियमित लेखा जोखा राख्ने, राख्न लगाउने तथा प्रतिवेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले वार्षिक योजना वनाउदा सभागी भै आवश्यक राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने, समय सापेक्ष कम्पनीले सुम्पेको थप कार्य गर्ने, गराउने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभबः</u></strong><br />\r\n			मान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट कम्तीमा कृषि विषयमा प्रमिता प्रमाणपत्र वा से सरह उतिर्ण भै कम्तीमा सम्वन्धित क्षेत्रको २ वर्षको अनुभव भएको एवम् कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी Ms. Word, Ms. Excel र Power point सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनुपर्ने छ।</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(142, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">कार्य विवरण फारम</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">सेवा-प्राबिधिक<br />\r\n			तह-७</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">१.पदको नाम ;-संकलन अधिकृत<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक);-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समय ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;: काठमाण्डौ ५.जवाफदेहिता.-महाप्रबन्धक&nbsp; समक्ष।</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">शाखा :-संकलन काठमाण्डौ</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षा</strong>-केन्द्रिय कार्यालय संकलन शाखाको जिम्वेवारी सम्हाल्दै बजार को माग अनुसार बिविन्न जदिबु्त्ती संकलन गर्ने<br />\r\n<strong>कार्य, जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">महा प्रबन्धकको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन ,नियन्त्रण र समवन्वयमा रहि जडीबुटी संकलनको कार्य सु-ब्यबस्थित तरिकाले गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलनका लागि क्षेत्र पहिचान गरि संकलन समयअनुसारको जडीबुटी संकलन कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडीबुठी संकलनका लागि कम्पनीको स.कलन लक्ष्य अनुसार संकलन पुर्ब गरिने छोडपूर्जी लगायतका कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलन कार्य गर्दा पाकेट क्षेत्रमा स्थानीय ब्यक्ती ,समुह वा अन्य निकाय सितको समन्वयका लागि पहल गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलित जडीबुटीको भण्डारण र प्रशोधन संयन्त्र&nbsp; सम्म् ढुवानीको व्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलित जडीबुटीहरूको भुक्तानीको व्यवस्था गर्ने गराउने एवम समय समयमा संकलित र प्रशोधन र्इकार्इको निरिक्षण भ्रमणमा जाने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलित जडीबुटी हरूको यथार्त विवरण तयार गरि, गरार्इ राख्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलन गरिएका जडीबुटीहरूबाट उत्पादन हुने&nbsp; तेल तथा सारको खर्च र आम्दानी सम्बन्धी बिश्लेषणात्मब प्रतिवेदन तयार गरि पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बजारमा माग भएका र आर्थिक दृष्टिकोणले मुनाफा मुलुक जडिबुटीहरूको संकलनका लागि पहल गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिल्डस्तरमा कार्यरत कर्मचारीहरू एवम संकलकहरूलार्इ संकलन र गुणस्तर सम्बन्धी आवश्यकता अनुसार तालिमको व्यबस्था गर्ने ,गराउने।नया संकलन क्षेत्रको पहिचान गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलित जडीबुटीहरूको प्रशोधन हुने र्इकाहरूमा समन्वय गरि ढुवानी दाखिला र प्रशोधित बस्तुवारे समय समयमा जानकारी लिर्इ राख्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले वार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागी भर्इ आफ्नो क्षेत्रको योजना र कार्य योजना बनार्इ छलफलका लागि पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">समय सापेक्ष कम्पनिले सुम्पेको थप जिम्वेवारि बहन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\nमान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा बोटनी बिषयमा स्नाकोतर वा सो सरह&nbsp;&nbsp; उतिर्ण भर्इ सम्बन्धीत क्षेत्रमा&nbsp; कम्तिमा&nbsp; दुर्इ बर्षको अनुभब भएको एवम कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धीMs.Word,Ms.Excelर,Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनुपर्ने छ। &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(141, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\nकोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\"><br />\r\n			<strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong> <strong>सहायक</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>५</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\">१. पदको नामः ल्याब सहायक<br />\r\n			२. तलव (मासिक) कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३. काम गर्ने समयः कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४. कार्य क्षेत्रः काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५. जवाफदेहिताः गुणस्तर अधिकृत&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\">शाखाः गुणास्तर निर्धारण शाखा<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			शाखा प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन, नियन्त्रण, सम्पर्क र समन्वयमा रही तल लेखिएका र तोकिएका आफ्नो शाखासंग सम्वन्धित कार्यहरु सम्पादन र सम्पन्न गर्न सहयोगीको भूमिका निर्वाह गर्ने ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशनमा रही तोकेको काम काज गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर कार्यका लागी आवश्यक&nbsp; Reagents आफु भन्दा माथिल्लो तहसंग&nbsp; समन्य गरी तयार पार्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर परिक्षण सम्वन्धी कामकाज गर्ने,गुणस्तर परिक्षणको लागी नमूना संकलन गर्ने र सो का लागि आवश्यक सहयोग गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर शाखालार्इ चुस्त दुरूस्त वनार्इ आफ्नो मातहतको कर्मचारीसंग समन्वय गरी कार्य सम्पादन गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर परिक्षणको रिपोर्ट तयार गर्ने,शाखा प्रमुखको दस्तखत गरार्इ सम्वन्धित शाखामा पठाउने,संकलित नमूनाको उचित तरिकाले सुरक्षित / भण्डारण गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर शाखबाट सम्पादन नहुने परिक्षणका लागी गुणस्तर अधकृतसंग समन्वय गरी अरू निकायमा गर्ने गराउने कार्यमा सहयोग गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो शाखामा प्राप्त चिठ्ठीपत्रहरू,परिक्षण रिपोर्टहरू तथा अन्य आवश्यक कागजपत्रहरू सुरक्षित राख्न फार्इलिङ गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">शाखा प्रमुख तथा कम्पनीले तोकेको अन्य कामकाज गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">विज्ञान विषयमा कम्तीमा Plus two&nbsp; गरी सुगन्धित तेल वा औषधिजन्य वस्तु उत्पादन गर्ने ल्यावमा काम गरी कम्तीमा २ वर्ष अनुभव भएको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको &nbsp;।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भइ अंग्रेजी नेपाली भाषामा टापर्इ गर्न सक्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(140, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\nकोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:313px\">कार्य विवरण फारम</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:311px\">सेवा-प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			तह- ५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:313px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">१.पदको नाम ;-जुनियर प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक);-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समय ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;:- टामाघदि, ेल्बारि-टर्हरा, टिकापूर<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिता&ndash; खेती प्रबन्धक&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:311px\">शाखा :-जडिबुटी खेति</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n<table align=\"left\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु खटिएको व्यापारीक र्इकार्इमा जडिबुटी खेती प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्षा सम्पर्क र निर्देशनमा रही कम्पनीले खेति गर्ने गरेका जडिवुटी खेती वालीहरूको खेती देखि वाली भित्र्याउने सम्ममा गर्नु पर्ने जे जति कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फार्म भित्र तथा निजि क्षेत्रमा खेती कार्य गराउदा वालीहरूको विमा गर्नु पर्ने भए सो का लागी पहल गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बिभिन्न वालीहरूको खेति ,जात तथा प्रबिधीवारे अनुसन्धान कार्य गर्नु पर्दा अनुसन्धान प्लटहरूको वैज्ञानीक तरीकाको व्यबस्थापन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तरिय बिउ बिजन उत्पादन र भण्डारणको समुचित कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">दैनिक ,मासिक र बार्षिक रूपमा फार्म तथा निजिक्षेत्रका खेतिको कार्य संचालन&nbsp; गर्दा आवश्यक जनशक्ती&nbsp; परिचालन गरी सो कार्यको अभिलेख राख्ने एवम कृषकलार्इ&nbsp; समय सापेक्ष&nbsp; खेति ,रोग ,किरा ,जात बारे राय परामर्श&nbsp; र तालिम दिने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फार्म तथा निजि क्षेत्रमा खेति कार्य संचालन गर्दा आवश्यक पर्ने साधनस्रोत, औजाहरूको व्यबस्थापन गरी आवश्यक परेकोवेला मर्मत संभारको कार्य समयमै गरी गरार्इ राख्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फार्म र निजि क्षेत्रमा लक्ष्यित बार्षिक कार्य योजना अनुसार बिभिन्न वालिको नर्सरी व्यबस्थापन ,रोपार्इ र कटनी&nbsp; कार्य तदारूकताका साथ गर्न गराउन आवश्यक निर्देशन लिने र मातहतका सम्पुर्ण जनशक्तीलार्इ परिचालन गर्ने ,दैनिक रेकर्ड राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फारममा प्रगति प्रतिबेदन तयार गर्दा आवश्यक सहयोग गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रत्येक वालीको छुट्टा छुट्टै खेतिको लागत खर्च उत्पादनको रेकर्ड बनार्इ प्रतिबेदनको रूपमा तयार गरि पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनिले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागि भइ राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले समय समयमा आवश्यक्ता अनुसार सुम्पिएको कार्य गर्ने गराउने<strong>।</strong></li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify; clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">मान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्था बाट न्युनतम कृषि बिषयमा प्रविणता प्रमाणपत्र तह वा सो सरह उतिर्ण गरि सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा दुर्इ बर्षको अनुभव भएको एवम कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी MS Word , Excel, PowerPoint सम्बन्धि ज्ञान हासिल गरेको हुनु पर्ने छ।</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(139, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\nकोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">कार्य विवरण फारम</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">सेवा-प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			तह-६</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">१.पदको नाम ;- खेती प्रभन्धक<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक);-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समय ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;: तामागढी<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिताः महाप्रवन्धक तथा केन्द्रीय कार्यालयको खेतिविस्तार प्रमुख समक्ष।</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">शाखा :-व्यापारिक र्इकार्इ ,तामागढी</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षा</strong>-फार्म तथा नीजि क्षेत्रममा ब्यबसायीक&nbsp; रूपले खेति हुने बालीहरूको अधिकतम उत्पादकत्वका लागी खेति कार्य एवम अन्य निर्देशित कम्पनीका कार्यहरू व्यबस्थित तरिकाले गर्ने गराउने ।<br />\r\n<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्वः</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">केन्द्रीय कार्यालयको खेती विस्तार प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन , नियन्त्रण र समन्वयमा&nbsp; रहीआफ्नो फारम भित्र तथा निजि क्षेत्रमा खेतीका कर्यहरू जिम्वेवार भर्इ र्इमानदारीका साथ सम्पादन गर्ने ,र गराउनु पर्ने छ।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बजारमा माग भएका आर्थिक दृष्टिकोणले नाफामुलुक बालीहरूको आफ्नो फारम तथा स्थानीयन निजि स्तरका कृषकहरूद्वारा समेत खेतिको कार्य गर्ने गराउने तथा बालिको विमा गर्नु पर्ने भए केन्द्रीय कार्यालयमा समन्बय गरी&nbsp; वीमा कार्य&nbsp; समपन्न् गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिबुटी खेतिका लागि प्रबिधी परिक्षण,उन्नतजात तथा उत्पादकतवको परिक्षण गरि उत्कृष्ट नतिजाको व्यबसायिक उत्पादनमा समाबेश गर्ने गराउने कार्यका लागि प्रतिबेदन तयार गरि पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो कार्य क्षेत्रमा खेति भैरहेका बालीहरूको आवश्यकता अनुसार गुणस्तरिय विउ बिजनको&nbsp; उत्पादन गरी राख्नु पर्ने बिउ बिजनका लागी उपयुक्त जग्गाको छनौ गरि गुणस्तरीय बिउ बिजन उत्पादनको कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">निजि स्तरमा खेति गरिएका बालिहरूका सम्बन्धीत कृषकहरूलार्इ समयमा आश्ककता अनुसारखेति प्रविधि, रोग किरा र संकलन समय बारे आवश्यक तालिम प्रदान गर्ने।</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">फार्ममा प्रयोग हुने टेक्टर,हार्बेस्टर, पम्पसेटजस्ता मेशिन,मेशिनरि एवम कुटो कोदालो , जस्ता अौजारहरूको मर्मत संभार,भण्डारण र आवश्यक परिमाणको लेखा जोखा गरि आवश्यक ब्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बार्षिक कार्य योजनाअनुसार सम्पूर्ण कार्य संपादन गर्न दैनिक र मासिक रूपमा&nbsp; कार्य बिभाजन&nbsp; र आफ्नो क्षेत्रमा आवहश्यक जनशक्ती स्रोतसाधन परिचालन गरी परिमाण मुखि कार्य गर्ने गराउने।साथै माग अनुसार प्रगति प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">खेति कार्य गर्दा भौतिकपुर्बाधार,उत्पादन लागत ,कार्य क्षेत्रहरू लगायत कार्यको दैनिक ढाचामा&nbsp; रेकर्डहरू अध्यावधीक&nbsp; गरार्इ राख्ने राख्न लगाउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">खेती भैराखेका बालिहरूको छुट्टा छुट्टै कूल उत्पादन लागत र उत्पादन परिमाणको दैनिक र मासिक रूपमा रेकर्ढ बनाइ राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।साथै सोही आधारमा बार्षिक प्रतिबेदन तथार गरि&nbsp; पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो मातहतका सम्पुर्ण कर्मचारीहरूलार्इ&nbsp; निर्देशन र परिचालन गरी निजहरूको कार्य संपादन समेत निष्पक्ष&nbsp; तरिकाले मूल्याङकन गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीको बार्षिक योजना एवम कार्य योजना बनाउदा आफ्नो क्ष्रेत्रको कार्य संपादनका लागि गरिने सम्पुर्ण कामकारवाही तथा गतिविधीहरूका वारेमा आवश्यक छलफल गरी तयार गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनिले समय समयमा आवश्यक्ता अनुसार तोकेका अन्य कार्यहरू गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु र मातहतका कर्मचारीहरूको बृति विकासका लगि तालिम ,अबलोकन भ्रमण तथा उच्च् शिक्षाका लागि पहल गर्ने।</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\nमान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा बाली बिज्ञान बिषयममास स्नातक भर्इ सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा कम्तिमा दुर्इ बर्षको अनुभब भएको।एवम कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी (MS Word MS .Excel , PowerPoint ) ज्ञान भएको साथै हुनुपर्ने छ। &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(138, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">जडिबुटी उत्पfदन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; कोटेश्वर,काठमा</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">कार्य विवरण फारम</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">सेवा-प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			तह-७</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">\r\n			<div>१.पदको नाम ;- खेती बिस्तार अधिकृत<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक);-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समय ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;:-काठमाण्डौ र अवश्यकता अनुसार अन्य बाह्य जिल्लाहरू<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिता.महाप्रबन्धक समक्ष<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">शाखा :-जडीबुटी खेती बिस्तार</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:5px; width:638px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षा</strong>- बजारमा माग भएका आर्थिक दृष्टिकोणले मुनाफामुलक बालीहरूको खेति कार्यमा अधिकतम उत्पादकत्व ,नया बिउ बिजन,फारमहरूमा आधुनिकिकरण तथा नया खेतिको क्षेत्र पहिचान भर्इ कम्पनीको खेती िस्तार &nbsp;कार्यमा उल्लेखनीय योग्दान&nbsp; पूर्याऊने<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">महाप्रवन्धकको प्रत्यक्ष निर्देशन र समन्वयमा रही आफनो शाखा संग सम्बन्धीत कार्यहरूकम्पनीको उदेश्य,नीति नियमानुसार योजना कार्यान्वयनको&nbsp; कार्य इमान्दारीताका साथ सम्पादन गर्ने , गराउनु पर्ने छ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बजारमा माग भएका ,आर्थिक दृष्टिकोणले नाफामुलक बनस्पतीहरूको खेतिको लागी थप कार्य गर्ने ।निजि क्षेत्रलार्इ प्रोत्साहीत गर्न खेति र प्रशोधनबारे राय सुझाव र सल्लाह दिने कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिबुटी खेतिको प्रबिधीको परिक्षण ,उत्पादकत्व तथा उन्नतजात बारे कम्पनीको उपलब्ध जग्गामा परिक्षण गरि गराइ सो को&nbsp; प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने ,गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">औषधोउपयोगी&nbsp; तथा बिभिन्न किसिमका सुगन्धीत तेलधारी बन्सपतीहरूमा हाल खेती भैरहेका बनस्पतीहरूको उन्नतजात को बिउ र खेती प्रबिधीका लागी थप अध्ययन ,अनुसंधान एबम बैदेशिक क्षेत्रमा पत्राचार गरी उपयुक्त प्रबिधी र बिउ बिजन सम्बन्धी ब्यापारीक र्इकाइहरूमा खेतिका लागि सिफारिस गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">निजी क्षेत्रका कृषकहरूलाइ प्रोत्साहीत गर्न समय समयमा&nbsp; भेटघाट ,तालीम&nbsp; तथा उत्कृष्ठ कृषकलार्इ सम्मानीत हुने कार्य&nbsp; गर्ने, गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीका बिभिन्न ब्यापारीक र्इकार्इ हरूमा खेति भैरहेका बनस्पतीको आवश्यकताअनुसार बिउ बिजनको उत्पादन ,भण्डारण गराउने कर्यमा तदारूकता देखार्इ गुणस्तरीय बिउ बिजनका लागी जिम्वेवारी पुर्बक कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीका शाखा,कार्यालय वा खेति इकाइहरूले गरेको वा गर्ने जडिवुटी खेती वालीहरू सम्वन्धमा समय समयमा निरिक्षण अनुगमन गरी आवश्यक्ता अनुसार खेतीका लागि निर्देशन ,राय सुझाव दिने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीका बिभिन्न ब्यापारीक इकार्इहरूको खेति सँम्बन्धी बार्षिक योजना&nbsp; र कार्य योजना&nbsp; बनाउन सहयोग गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बिभिन्न फार्ममा खेति गरिने बालीहरूको आवश्यकता अनुसार वीमा गर्न सम्बन्धीत संस्थासित सम्पर्क र समन्वय गरी&nbsp; कार्यान्वयनका लागि पहल गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिबुटी फार्म तथा कार्यक्रमहरूमा खेति गरिएका बनस्पति हरूको खेतिको विवरण ,उत्पादन लागत आदिको छुट्टा छुट्टै स्पसष्ट र व्यबस्थित ढाचामा रेकर्डहरू अध्यावधीक गरार्इ राख्ने एबम राख्न लगाउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मातहतका र्इकार्इहरूको प्रगती प्रतिबेदनका&nbsp; लागि संयोजक भर्इ कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बिभिन्न बालीको मूल्य निर्धारण गर्न सम्बन्धित शाखालार्इ आबश्यक पर्ने डकुमेन्टको अडिटिङ गरि स्वीकृतीका लागि सिफारीस गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बार्षिक रूपमा खेतिको योजना कार्य योजना अनुसार कम्पनीका खेति गरिएका क्षेत्रहरूको अनुगमन तथा मुल्याङकन तालिका अनुसार भ्रमण गरि राय सुझाव सहितको प्रतिबेदन तथार गरी पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">निजीस्तरमा प्राकृतीक सुगन्धीत वनस्पतिहरूको प्रशोधनको संभाब्यता अध्ययन गर्ने ।बजारको संभावना भएका आर्थिक दृष्टिले मुनाफामूलक&nbsp; वनस्पतिहरूको प्रशोधको क्षेत्र बिस्तारका लागि पहल गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">केन्द्रीय कार्यलयको हाता भित्र संभव भए सम्म जडिबुटीजन्य&nbsp; वनस्पतिको नमुना प्लट तयार गर्ने तथा गार्डेनिङको व्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु र मातहतका कर्मचारीहरूलार्इ थप ज्ञान, सिप,तालीमका लागि अबलोकन भ्रमण ,शैक्षिक&nbsp; स्तर बृद्रीका लागि कार्य गर्ने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\n			मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट कृषि बाली बिज्ञानमा&nbsp; स्नातकोतर शैक्षिक योग्यता प्राप्त गरेको एबम कम्प्युटरमा MsWord,Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।कम्तिमा&nbsp; दुर्इ&nbsp; बर्ष&nbsp; सम्बन्धीत क्षेत्रमा अनुभब प्राप्त भएको।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(137, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>जडिबुटी</strong> <strong>उत्प</strong><strong>f</strong><strong>दन</strong> <strong>तथा</strong> <strong>प्रशोधन</strong> <strong>कं</strong><strong>.</strong><strong>ली</strong><strong>,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कोटेश्वर</strong><strong>,</strong><strong>काठमाडौ</strong>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:313px\"><strong>कार्य</strong> <strong>विवरण</strong> <strong>फारम</strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:310px\"><strong>तह </strong>६</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:313px\"><strong>१.पदको नाम </strong><strong>-</strong> लेखा अधिकृत<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक) </strong><strong>-.</strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय &nbsp;</strong><strong>- </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;</strong><strong>- </strong>काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता </strong><strong>- </strong>महाप्रबन्धक समक्ष&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:310px\"><strong>शाखा - </strong>लेखा बिभाग</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br />\r\n			<strong>कामको</strong> <strong>जिम्मेवारी</strong> <strong>र</strong> <strong>जिम्मेवारीहरू</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">भौचर भर्न र लेखा सोफटवेरमा लेखा हिसाब&nbsp;&nbsp; राख्नन सहायोग गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रप्त बिलहरुको भुक्तानि&nbsp; गर्न सहयोग गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">सबै कर्मचारीहरुको मासिक तलब खर्च बाड्न र तलब को रेकर्ड राख्न&nbsp;सहायोग गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अग्रिमरूपमा भुक्तानी भयको लेखाको नियमित खाता विवरण जाँच गर्न</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">लेखांकन प्रणाली या सफ्टवेयर संग सबै व्यावसायिक एकाइहरुमा सबै लेखांकन प्रक्रिया या प्रक्रिया भय नभयको सुनिचित गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">साझेदारहरूको लागि कोष स्थानान्तरण ड्राफ्टको सन्दर्भमा बैंकसँग सम्झौता गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">परियोजनाको खातामा पठाइएको र प्राप्त सामग्रीको लागत र चार्जको चे्कजाच गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रमुख कार्यलय र परियोजना खाताहरू बीचको खाता जाँच गर्न र नियमित भ्रमण गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">निर्देशन अनुसार साझेदारहरूको खाता बुकिङ प्रणाली सुनिश्चित गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रमुख कार्यलय र परियोजना खाताहरू बीचको लेखा &nbsp;सूची रेकर्ड &nbsp;ठिक गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">लेखा चे्कजाच को लागि पर्याप्त समर्थन कागजातहरूको लागि समितिहरू / कर्मचारीहरू (को लागी जिम्मेवार व्यक्तिहरू, आधिकारिक टिकट, कर कटौती, सभाहरूबाट अनुमोदन अद्यावधिक अनुमोदन गरी लेखा परीक्षा प्रश्नहरू अपडेट गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अन्य विभाग द्वारा अनुदेशको रूपमा अन्य वित्तीय कार्यलाई सहयोग&nbsp;गर्ने&nbsp;।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">नेपाल सरकार बाट मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट व्यवस्थापन वा&nbsp;अन्य सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रहरूमा&nbsp;न्यूनतम स्नातक डिग्री&nbsp;प्राप्त गरेको हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">लेखा शाहायक वा सो सरहको श्रेत्रमा खाता मा कम्तिमा 2 वर्ष को &nbsp;अनुभवभयको</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अङ्ग्रेजी र नेपाली दुवै राम्रो लेखन र बोलन साक्ने हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">बम कम्प्युटरमा MsWord, Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(136, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\"><strong>सेवा-प्रशासनिक<br />\r\n			तह-५</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">१.पदको नाम ;-योजना र अनुगमन&nbsp; सहायक<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक);-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समय ;-.कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;: काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिता.-योजना र अनुगमन मुल्याङकन शाखा प्रमुख समक्ष।</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:319px\">शाखा :-काठमाण्डौ र आवश्यकता अनुसार बाह्रय जिल्लाहरू</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षाः</strong>- तामागढी व्यापारिक इकाइको प्रशोधन शाखामा सुगन्धीत घास एवम कोरा जडीबुट प्रशोधन कार्य सुचारू रूपले संचालन भै कम्पनीकत्र उतपादन कार्यमा सहयोग पुग्ने छ।<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">तामागढी व्यापरीक इकाइमा प्रशोधन युनिट प्रमुखको निर्देशन,नियनत्रण मा&nbsp; रही सम्पूर्ण प्रशोधनका कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य गर्दा गराउदा तहा अवस्थित अौजार मेशिनरिको नियमित सरचारू रूपले संचालन गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यकता अनुसार अौजार ,मेशिनरीहरूको मर्मत संभार कार्यको जिम्मा लिइ मर्मत&nbsp; गरि गरार्इ संचालनमा ल्याउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">ब्वाइलर सेटमा जडित बिभिन्न प्रकारका मोटर लगायत वाइरिङ को दैनिक संचालन हुनु पुर्ब चेक जाच गरी संचालन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बस्तु प्रशोधन गर्दा कम्पनी बाट उपलब्ध मापदण्ड अनुसार प्रशोधन अवधि सम्म र प्रशोधन कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधित बस्तु भण्डारण पुर्ब राख्ने कन्टेनर बस्तु अनुसार व्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तिलाइ कार्य योजना अनुसार स्वस्थ वातावरणमा काम गर्नका लागि अभिप्रेरित तालिम दिने कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्राबिधिक कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तीलार्इ कार्य योजना अनुसार कार्य योजना बनार्इ संचालन गरी दैनिक एवम मासिक रेकर्ड राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।एवम सो को प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कमपनिले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागि भर्इ आफ्नो राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">१० कम्पनीले समय सापेक्ष सुम्पेको कार्य गर्ने गराउने।&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong><br />\r\nमान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा प्रविणता प्रमाणपत्र तह व सो सरह उतिर्ण भै सम्बन्धीत विषयमा&nbsp;&nbsp; तालिम प्राप्त गरेको एवम सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा कम्तिमा ५ बर्षको अनुभव भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(135, '<div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong>&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>६</strong>&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\">१. पद : उत्पादन अधिकृत&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n			२. तलव:कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३. काम गर्ने समयः कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४. कार्य क्षेत्रः काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५. जवाफदेहिताः उत्पादन प्रमुख &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\">उत्पादन व्यापार इकार्इ:Manufacturing<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong><br />\r\n			कम्पनीको हर्वल केयर तथा अन्य उत्पादनको उद्देश्य अनुरूप आफ्नो शाखावाट उत्पादन गर्ने वस्तुहरूको मासिक,चौमासिक,अर्ध बार्षिक तथा बार्षिक उत्पादन कार्य योजना वनार्इ सो अनुसार छिटो,छरितो ढंगले स्वच्छ,सफा र गुणस्तरिय वस्तु उत्पादन गर्न आफ्नो शाखाको काम कारवाहीलार्इ नियमित, व्यवस्थित,चुस्त, दुरूस्त वनाउने काम, कर्तव्य तथा जिम्मेवारी उत्पादन अधिकृतको हुनेछ ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीको वार्षिक उत्पादन कार्यक्रम अनुसार जडीबुटी तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरूको सार तथा तेल लगायत आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थहरूको प्रयोग गरी स्वीकृत फर्मुलेशन अनुसार वस्तु उत्पादन गर्ने,गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन प्रमुखको प्रत्यक्ष सम्पर्कमा रही कम्पनीको लक्ष्य अनुरूप उत्पादन गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यक्ता अनुसार आफ्नो शाखाबाट उत्पादन गरिने उत्पादनहरूको उत्पादन कार्य योजना तयार पार्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखाका कर्चमारीहरूको कार्यतालीका तयार गरी सो अनुसार काममा लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफु मातहतका कर्चारीहरूले तोके वमोजिम काम गरे नगरेको सम्वन्धमा कामको नियमित मूल्यांकन गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो शाखावाट उत्पादन भएको विभिन्न उत्पादनहरूको गुणस्तर परिक्षणको लागि सम्वन्धित शाखामा पठार्इ चेक जाँच गर्ने गराउने र प्राप्त जाँच रिपोर्ट सुरक्षित राख्ने राख्न लगाउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो शाखाको वार्षिक उत्पादन योजना तथा कार्यक्रम अनुसारको उत्पादनका लागि आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थको खरिदको लागी सम्वन्धित शाखासंग समन्वय गरी खरिद सम्वन्धि आवश्यक कार्य गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो शाखावाट उत्पादित वस्तुहरू नियमानुसार भण्डारण दाखिला गर्ने गराउने र सो नभएसम्म समुचित संरक्षणको व्यवस्था मिलाउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादनका लागी आवश्यक कच्चा पदार्थ तथा&nbsp; प्याकिङ सामाग्री समयमा माग गरी उत्पादन कार्यको लागी सहजिकरण गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा उत्पादन हुने वस्तु तथा सो संग सम्वन्धित कार्यहरूको विवरण&nbsp; तयार गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बजार माग अनुसारका उपयोगी उत्पादनको खोज तथा अनुसन्धान गरी गुणस्तर निर्धारण शाखा र उत्पादन इकार्इ&nbsp; प्रमुखसंग समन्वय तथा सहकार्य गरी नयाँ उत्पादनका लागि फर्मुलेशनहरू तयार गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन व्यापार युनिटमा उत्पादन गरिने वस्तुहरूको उत्पादनका लागि आवश्यक विभिन्न Manufacturing Process (Mixing, Filling, Sealing, Packaging) कार्यहरू गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">महाप्रवन्धक वा कम्पनीले तोके वमोजिमका अन्य आवश्यक कार्य गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मान्यता प्राप्त विश्वविद्यालयबाट फार्मेसि विषयमा कम्तीमा स्नातक तह उत्तिर्ण गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">औषधिजन्य उत्पादन क्षेत्रमा कम्तीमा २ वर्ष कार्य गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको,नयाँ नयाँ खोज अनुसन्धान गर्न तत्पर रहने&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको र नेपाली तथा अंग्रेजी भाषामा टार्इष गर्न सक्ने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(134, '<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; width:366px\"><strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; width:366px\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>६</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">१. पदको नामः गुणस्तर निर्धारण अधिकृत&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n			२. तलव (मासिक) कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३. काम गर्ने समयः कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४. कार्य क्षेत्रः काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५. जवाफदेहिताः महाप्रवन्धक</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">शाखाः गुणास्तर एवम अनुसन्धान तथा विकास शाखा</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीमा खेती, प्रशोधन,संकलन तथा उत्पादन भएका वस्तुहरूको गुणस्तर मापदण्ड तयार गरी राख्ने राख्न लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादित वस्तुहरू निर्धारित मापदण्ड अनुसार उत्पादन भए नभएको सम्वन्धमा गुणास्तर नांप जाच गरी गरार्इ गुणस्तरीय वस्तु उत्पादन गर्न भुमिका निर्वाह गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">नियमित कार्य तालिका वनाई हरेक ४ महिनामा कम्पनीमा रहेका सम्पूर्ण जडिबूटीहरु तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरुको गुणस्तर परीक्षण गरी&nbsp; रेकर्ड&nbsp; राख्ने ,राख्न लगाउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीद्धारा खरिद गरिने विभिन्न जडिबूटी,वनस्पति तथा सुगन्धित घांसहरुको गुणस्तर तथा जलांश आदिका वारेमा जाँच विश्लेषण गर्ने गराउने र आवश्यक्ता अनुसार सम्वन्धित शाखामा सो को रिपोर्ट पेश गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिवुटीजन्य अौषधिय गुण भएका वस्तु उत्पादनका लागि नयाँ नयाँ फर्मुलेशनहरूको अनुसन्धान तथा विकास गरी कम्पनीवाट त्यस्ता वस्तु उत्पादनमा आवश्यक सहयोग तथा समन्वय गर्ने एवम सो वस्तुहरुको&nbsp; गुणस्तर मापदण्ड&nbsp; तयार पार्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर परीक्षणका लागि अध्ययन अनुसन्धान गरी नयां प्रविधिहरुको विकास गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">गुणस्तर जांचका लागि अन्य निकाय वा व्यक्तिवाट मग भइ आए वमोजिम जडीबुटी तथा सुगन्धित तेलहरुको गुण्स्तर परिक्षण कार्य गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रयोगशालामा रहेका सम्पूर्ण उपरकणको जिम्मेवारी लिने, संचालन गर्ने गराउने, मर्मत संभारको आवश्यकता परेमा सम्विन्धत शाखासंग आवश्यक समन्वय राखी लागत स्टिमेट तयार गरी गराई मर्मत संभार गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यक परेको समयमा अन्य निकायहरुसंग सम्पर्क र समन्वय गरी गुणस्तर परिक्षण सम्वन्धी कार्यहरु गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रत्येक आर्थिक वर्षको कार्यक्रम र बजेट तर्जुमा हुनु पूर्व चालु आ.ब.को अन्त्य हुनु ३ महिना &nbsp;अगाडि नै आफ्नो उपरोक्त कार्यहरुसंग सम्वन्धित आगामी आ.ब.को कार्य योजना तयार गरी गराई पेश गर्ने &nbsp;गराउने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो मातहतमा कार्यरत कर्मचारीहरुलाई गुणस्तर निर्धारण सम्वन्धी कार्य योजना वनाई काममा लगाउने, जिम्मेवारी तोक्ने सोही आधारमा कार्य सम्पादन मूल्यांकन गरी गराई राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीलार्इ आवश्यक पर्ने कच्चा पदार्थहरूर्को गुणस्तर Parameters तयार गरी Specification तयार पार्ने .</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो शाखासंग सम्वन्धित नयां खोज तथा अनुसन्धानहरू गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">महाप्रवन्धक वा कम्पनीले तोकेको अन्य आवश्यक काम काज गर्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मान्यता प्राप्त विश्वविद्यालयबाट रसायन शास्त्रमा स्नातक वा सो सरह उत्तिर्ण</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">सुगन्धित तेल वा औषधिजन्य वस्तु उत्पादन गर्ने सस्थाको गुणस्तर निर्धारण( Quality Control)&nbsp; क्षेत्रमा कम्तीमा २ वर्ष कार्य गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको,नयाँ खोज,अनुसन्धान गर्न तत्पर ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको र नेपाली तथा अंग्रेजी भाषामा टार्इप गर्न सक्ने।&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(133, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,<br />\r\nकोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; width:319px\">कार्य विवरण फारम</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center; width:304px\">सेवा-प्राविधिक<br />\r\n			तह-५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:319px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">१.पदको नामः- टेक्निकल अपरेटर<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक):- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समयः- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र:-तामागढी,बारा<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिताः- प्रशोधन इकार्इ समक्ष</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:304px\">शाखा &ndash;व्यापारिक इकार्इ तामागढी</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">&nbsp;\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षाः</strong>- तामागढी व्यापारिक इकाइको प्रशोधन शाखामा सुगन्धीत घास एवम कोरा जडीबुट प्रशोधन कार्य सुचारू रूपले संचालन भै कम्पनीकत्र उतपादन कार्यमा सहयोग पुग्ने छ।</div>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">तामागढी व्यापरीक इकाइमा प्रशोधन युनिट प्रमुखको निर्देशन,नियनत्रण मा&nbsp; रही सम्पूर्ण प्रशोधनका कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य गर्दा गराउदा तहा अवस्थित अौजार मेशिनरिको नियमित सरचारू रूपले संचालन गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आवश्यकता अनुसार अौजार ,मेशिनरीहरूको मर्मत संभार कार्यको जिम्मा लिइ मर्मत&nbsp; गरि गरार्इ संचालनमा ल्याउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">ब्वाइलर सेटमा जडित बिभिन्न प्रकारका मोटर लगायत वाइरिङ को दैनिक संचालन हुनु पुर्ब चेक जाच गरी संचालन गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बस्तु प्रशोधन गर्दा कम्पनी बाट उपलब्ध मापदण्ड अनुसार प्रशोधन अवधि सम्म र प्रशोधन कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधित बस्तु भण्डारण पुर्ब राख्ने कन्टेनर बस्तु अनुसार व्यबस्था गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तिलाइ कार्य योजना अनुसार स्वस्थ वातावरणमा काम गर्नका लागि अभिप्रेरित तालिम दिने कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्राबिधिक कार्य संचालन गर्दा मातहतका जनशक्तीलार्इ कार्य योजना अनुसार कार्य योजना बनार्इ संचालन गरी दैनिक एवम मासिक रेकर्ड राख्ने र राख्न लगाउने।एवम सो को प्रतिबेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कमपनिले बार्षिक योजना बनाउदा सहभागि भर्इ आफ्नो राय सुझाव पेश गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">१० कम्पनीले समय सापेक्ष सुम्पेको कार्य गर्ने गराउने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट कम्तिमा प्रविणता प्रमाणपत्र तह व सो सरह उतिर्ण भै सम्बन्धीत विषयमा&nbsp;&nbsp; तालिम प्राप्त गरेको एवम सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रमा कम्तिमा 3 बर्षको अनुभव भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(132, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<table align=\"left\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><br />\r\n			<strong>जडीबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य विवरण फाराम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\"><strong>सेवाः </strong><strong>प्राविधिक</strong> <strong>सहायक</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>तहः </strong><strong>५</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:366px\">१. पदको नामः टेक्निकल अपरेटर<br />\r\n			२. तलव (मासिक): कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३. काम गर्ने समयः कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४. कार्य क्षेत्रः काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			५. जवाफदेहिताः उत्पादन अधिकृत&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"width:366px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">शाखाः उत्पादन व्यापार इकार्इ</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>कार्य जिम्मेवारी</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>दायित्वः</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">जिम्मेवारी दिएका उत्पादन शाखामा प्रयोग हुने मेशिन मेशिनरीहरूलार्इ सूचारू रूपमा संचालन गर्ने, संरक्षाण गर्ने, यथाशक्य मर्मत गरी गराइ वस्तु उत्पादन लक्ष्य अनुसारको प्रगति हासिल गर्ने प्रमुख भुमिका निर्वाह गर्ने ।</div>\r\n			&nbsp;\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन व्यापार इकार्इमा उत्पादन अधिकृतको प्रत्यक्ष निगरानीमा रही काम गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिलिङ्ग तथा मिक्सिङ्क मेसिनमा उत्पादनका लागि हरेक व्याचमा आवश्यक कच्चा पर्दाथको सहि परिमाणा चेकजांच गरी&nbsp; उत्पादन अधिकृतसंग समन्वय गरी मेसिन संचालन गर्ने गराउने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिलिङ्ग तथा सिलिङ्ग भर्इ सकेको सामाग्रीको रेकर्ड राख्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा रहेका मेशिन मेशिनरीको Manual follow गरी मेशिन सन्चालन गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा प्रयोग भएका मेशिनहरू विग्रिन गएमा यथाशक्य सम्भव भएसम्म आफै गर्ने र नभएमा सम्वन्धित निकायसंग समन्वय गरी मर्मत गर्ने पहल गरी मेशिन सूचारू गराउने&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादन शाखामा भएको उत्पादनका लागी प्रयोग गरिने मेसिनको संरक्षण गर्ने, उपयोग गर्ने, मर्मत&nbsp; गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">फिलिङ्क तथा मिक्सिङ्क मेसिनबाट उत्पादन भर्इ निस्केको बस्तुहरूको भौतिक चेकजांच, शिल भए नभएको र परिमाणा जांच गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मेसिनममा आर्इपर्ने खराबिका बारेमा उत्पादन अधिकृत मार्फत सम्वन्धित शाखालार्इ तुरून्त रिर्पोट गर्ने ।&nbsp;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मेसिन सञ्चालनमा आर्इपर्ने साना तिना कठिनार्इलार्इ सकेसम्म छिटो सुधार गरी सुचारू&nbsp; गर्ने गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:732px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता </u></strong><strong><u>/ </u></strong><strong><u>अनुभव</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">विज्ञान विषयमा कम्तीमा Plus two&nbsp; गरी &nbsp;Machine सम्वन्धी ज्ञान शिप भएको&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडीबुटी जन्य वा अन्य औषधि वनाउने कम्पनीमा मेशिन चलाउने अनुभव भएको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्तीमा २ वर्ष सोही क्षेत्रमा काम गरेको ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अग्रेजी राम्रो बोल्न र लेख्न सक्ने,&nbsp; टिमवर्कमा काम गर्न सक्ने दक्षता, क्षमता भएको&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्यूटर सम्वन्धी (Ms Word, Ms Excel, Power Point) ज्ञान र शीप भएको तथा नेपाली र अंग्रेजी भाषामा टार्इप गर्न सक्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(131, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div><strong>जडिबुटी उत्पादन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली</strong><strong>,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>कोटेश्वर</strong><strong>,</strong><strong>काठमाडौ</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:690px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:348px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:342px\"><strong>सेवा-प्राविधिक </strong><br />\r\n			<strong>तह-६</strong><br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:348px\">१.पदको नामः- प्रशोधन अधिकृत<br />\r\n			२.तलब(मासिक):- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			३.काम गर्ने समयः- कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			४.कार्य क्षेत्र:- तरहरा- वेलवारी<br />\r\n			५.जवाफदेहिताः- के.का.को.प्रशोधन विस्तार अधकृत<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:342px\">शाखाः व्यापारिक इकfर्इ तरहरा, वेलवारी</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:690px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>समष्ठिगत अपेक्षाः-</u></strong>व्यापारिक इकार्इहरूमा कम्पनीका प्रशोधनका लागि संकलित सुगन्धित घाँस र कोरा जडीबुटी लगायत अन्य वस्तुहरू सुचारू एवं सुव्यवस्थित तरिकाले प्रशोधन हुने छन् ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>कार्य जिम्मेवारी र दायित्वः</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">केन्द्रीय कार्यालको प्रशोधन इकार्इ विस्तार अधिकृतको प्रत्यक्ष निर्दशन र समन्वयमा रही फार्ममा उत्पादन भएका सुगन्धित घाँस, कोरा जडीबुटी तथा अन्य वस्तुहरू कम्पनीको कार्य योजना अनुसार प्रशोधन गर्ने,गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">व्यापारिक इकार्इहरूको फार्म भित्र र वाह्य क्षेत्रमा खेती गरिएका सुगन्धित तेलधारी वनस्पतिहरूको हार्भेस्टीङ तालिका अनुसार प्रशोधनको समय तालिका मिलार्इ प्रशोधन गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीबाट कार्य योजना अनुसार उपलब्ध कोरा जडीबुटीहरूको फार्मको घाँस प्रशोधनको तालिकालार्इ ख्याल गरी खाली समयमा प्रशोधन गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कोरा जडीबुटी प्रशोधन पूर्व समुचित भण्डारणको व्यवस्था मिलाउने, गुणस्तरमा ह्रास नदिन आवश्यक उपायहरूको अवलम्वन गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">संकलित कोरा जडीबुटीहरूको समुचित भण्डार प्रस्चात चाडो प्रशोधन गर्नु पर्ने वा ढिलो प्रशोधन गर्दा हुने वस्तुको अवस्था हेरी प्राथमिकता अनुसार प्रशोधन कार्य गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">वस्तु प्रशोधन गर्दा के कति समयसम्म कुन विधिबाट प्रशोधन गर्ने हो सो को मापदण्ड अनुसार प्रशोधन कार्य गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन कार्य सञ्चालन गर्दा औजार, मेशिन र जनशक्ति एवं अन्य आवश्यक पूर्वाधारको व्यवस्था भए नभएको हेरी के कस्तो व्यवस्था गर्नु पर्ने हो सो गर्ने,गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रत्येक प्रशोधन गरिने वस्तुको प्रशोधनका लागि प्राप्त भए देखी प्रशोधन भै तेल तथा सार उत्पादनसम्म वस्तु अनुसार छुट्टा छुट्टै रेर्कड राख्ने, राखन, लगाउने ,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">वस्तु प्रशोधन भै रहेको नियमित अनुगमन गर्ने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्पादित वस्तुको मासिक तथा वार्षिक प्रतिवेदन तयार गरी पेश गर्ने, गराउने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">प्रशोधन गर्दा आवश्यक टेक्टर, प्रशोधन संयन्त्र एवं अन्य आवश्यक पुर्वाधारहरूको आवश्यक अनुसार खरिद गर्ने, मर्मत गर्ने कार्यहरू व्यवस्थित तवरले गर्ने, गराउने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले वार्षिक योजना वनाउदा आफ्नो शाखासंग सम्वधित कामहरूको योजना वनाउदा तथा कार्य योजना वनार्इ छलफलका लागि पेश गर्ने,</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">जडिवुटी तथा सुगन्धित घाँस वालीहरू प्रशोधनका नयाँ नयाँ प्रविधिहरूको जानकारी लिर्इ कम्पनीलार्इ उपयोगी र मितव्ययी हुने किसिमका प्रशोधन तरिकाहरूको पहिचान गरी सिफारिश गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्पनीले समय सापेक्ष रूपमा गर्नुपर्ने अन्य कामहरू गर्ने, गराउने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong><u>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभबः</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">मान्यता प्राप्त शैक्षिक संस्थाबाट कम्तीमा इण्डस्ट्रियल इन्जिनियरिङ्कमा स्नातक वा विज्ञान विषयमा स्नातक वा से सरह उतिर्ण भै कम्तीमा सम्वन्धित क्षेत्रको २ वर्षको अनुभव भएको,समूहमा काम गर्न तत्पर,नेत्तृत्व गर्न सक्ने,रचनात्मक क्षमता भएको एवम् कम्प्युटर सम्बन्धी Ms. Word, Ms. Excel र Power point सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनुपर्ने छ।</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(130, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div>&nbsp;<strong>जडीबूटी</strong> <strong>प्रोडक्शंस</strong> <strong>र</strong> <strong>प्रोसेसिंग</strong> <strong>कम्पनी</strong> <strong>लिमिटेड</strong><br />\r\n<strong>जडीबूटी</strong><strong>,</strong>&nbsp;<strong>कोटेश्वर</strong>&nbsp;<strong>, </strong><strong>काठमाडौं</strong>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:16px; text-align:left; width:312px\"><strong>कार्य</strong> <strong>विवरण</strong> <strong>फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:16px; text-align:left; width:311px\"><strong>तह</strong> <strong>-</strong>&nbsp;५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:77px; text-align:left; width:312px\"><strong>१.पदको नाम &nbsp;</strong><strong>-</strong> व्यवस्थापक सहायक<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक) </strong><strong>-</strong> कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय </strong><strong>- </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र &nbsp;</strong><strong>- </strong>काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता.</strong> मानवश्रोत एवं प्रशासन विभाग&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:77px; text-align:left; width:311px\"><strong>विभाग</strong><strong> -</strong>&nbsp;मानवश्रोत एवं प्रशासन विभाग</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"height:108px; width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>कामको</strong> <strong>जिम्मेवारी</strong> <strong>र</strong> <strong>जिम्मेवारीहरू</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कार्यालयका कार्यहरू, जस्तै फाइलहरू, रिपोर्टहरू र प्रस्तुतीकरणहरू सिर्जना गर्ने, बैठकहरूको लागि सेट अप, र कार्यालयका सामानहरू व्यवस्था प्रदान गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">पत्राचार, रिपोर्टहरू, ड्राफ्टहरू, मेमोहरू र इ-मेलहरू सहित कागजातहरू तयार र परिमार्जन गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">वरिष्ठ प्रबन्धकहरूको अनुरोधहरू र प्रश्नहरू समाधान गर्न कार्यकारीसँग सम्पर्क गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">नियुक्ति बुकिंग गर्ने तथा विवाद रोक्न वास्तविक समयमा नियुक्ति बुकिंगमा समर्थन प्रदान गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">फोन जाच पास गर्ने र सम्बन्दिध वि्भाग मा फोने को त्रन्स्फर गर्ने।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">फोन, इ-मेल, र मेल मार्फत विनम्र र व्यावसायिक संचार सम्बन्ध रख्ने।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>शैक्षिक</strong> <strong>योग्यता</strong> <strong>र</strong> <strong>अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">नेपाल सरकार द्वारा मान्यता प्राप्त विश्वविद्यालय बाट व्यवस्थापन वा अन्य सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रहरुमा न्यूनतम स्नातक डिग्री हासिल गारेको हुनुपर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्तिमा&nbsp; दुर्इ&nbsp; बर्ष&nbsp; सम्बन्धीत क्षेत्रमा अनुभब प्राप्त भएको।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अङ्ग्रेजी र नेपाली दुवै राम्रो लेखन र बोलन साक्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्प्युटरमा MsWord,Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने छ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(128, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div><strong>जडीबूटी प्रोडक्शंस र प्रोसेसिंग कम्पनी लिमिटेड</strong><br />\r\n<strong>जडीबूटी,&nbsp;कोटेश्वर&nbsp;, काठमाडौं</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:287px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:335px\"><strong>तह</strong><strong> -</strong>&nbsp;७</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:287px\"><strong>१ पदको नाम</strong><strong> - </strong>मार्केटिंग अधिकृत<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक)</strong><strong> - </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय </strong><strong>-</strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र </strong><strong>-</strong>&nbsp; काठमाडौं<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता -</strong> महाप्रबन्धक समक्ष&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify; width:335px\"><strong>शाखा </strong><strong>&ndash; </strong>मार्केटिंग</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			समष्ठिगत अपेक्षा:&nbsp;मार्केटिङ अधिकृत उचित योजना र कार्यन्वयन मार्केटिङ रणनीति राष्ट्रिय र विश्वव्यापी बजार मा कम्पनी उत्पादनहरु (आवश्यक तेल र हर्बल हेरविचार उत्पादन) बेच्न बनाउन जिम्मेवार छ।<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, </strong><strong>जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उचित मार्केटिङ रणनीति र योजनाको साथ मार्केटमा कम्पनी उत्पादन तयारी, योजना र व्यवस्थापन गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">अधिकतम&nbsp;प्रचार गर्न सबै प्रचार सामग्री प्रकाशनको तयारी, योजना र परियोजना&nbsp;कम्पनीको&nbsp;पदोन्नति गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मार्केटिङ अभियान सिर्जना र&nbsp;तिनीहरूलाई&nbsp;हेर्न&nbsp;कार्यान्वयन&nbsp;कम्पनी र बाह्य एजेन्सी&nbsp;काम गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">आफ्नो मौजूदा ग्राहकहरु लाई कम्पनी संदेश को संचार गर्न को लागि नयाँ नवीन तरिकाहरु को निर्माण र विकास गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">वार्षिक बिक्री र मार्केटिंग प्लानमा योगदान दीने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">योजना र परियोजना मार्केटिंग घटनाहरु को प्रबंधन र त्सको सफलता को मूल्यांकन गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">सबै मार्केटिङ गतिविधिको प्रभावकारिताको मूल्यांकन गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">योजना, समयकेल्स भित्र सहमतिको रूपमा अभियानहरू विकास र वितरण गर्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>न्यूनतम आवश्यकता (शिक्षा र अनुभव)</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट व्यवस्थापन, मार्केटिंग, कम्युनिकेशन्स वा अन्य सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रहरुमा&nbsp;न्यूनतम&nbsp;मास्टर&nbsp;डिग्री&nbsp;प्राप्त गरेको हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्तिमा&nbsp; दुर्इ&nbsp; बर्ष&nbsp; सम्बन्धीत क्षेत्रमा अनुभब प्राप्त भएको हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">विपणन प्रविधिहरू र सिद्धान्तहरूको ठोस ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">बजार अनुसन्धान प्रविधि, सांख्यिकीय र डेटा विश्लेषण विधिहरूको राम्रो बुझाइ हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">कम्प्युटरमा MsWord, Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">सोशल मिडिया र वेब एनालिटिक्सको राम्ररी बुझाइ हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्कृष्ट संगठनात्मक र बहु-कार्यकारी क्षमताहरू भएको हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">उत्कृष्ट संचार र पारस्परिक क्षमता भएको हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">रचनात्मकता र व्यावसायिक जागरूकता भएको हुनु पर्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(127, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div><strong>जडिबुटी उत्प</strong><strong>fदन तथा प्रशोधन कं.ली,</strong><br />\r\n<strong>जडिबुटी</strong><strong>&nbsp; कोटेश्वर,काठमाडौ</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; width:312px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong>&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:28px; text-align:left; width:311px\"><strong>तह</strong><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:312px\"><strong>१.पदको नाम</strong><strong> - </strong>Secretary to GM<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक) </strong><strong>- </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय </strong><strong>- </strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र </strong><strong>-</strong>काठमाण्डौ<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता - </strong>महाप्रबन्धक समक्ष</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:311px\"><strong>शाखा</strong><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;जीएम सचिवालय</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>कार्य</strong><strong>, जिम्वेवारी र दायित्व</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कार्यकारी एजेन्डाको संरक्षण र नियुक्ति योजना, बोर्ड बैठकहरू, सम्मेलन आदिको वेवास्तापन गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">बैठकहरूमा संलग्न हुने र रेकर्ड राख्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्राप्त र फोन कलहरू स्क्यान गर्ने र उपयुक्त हुँदा तिनीहरूलाई रिडिरेक्ट गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">सबै बहिर्गमन वा आगमन पत्राचारलाई (ई-मेल, पत्र, प्याकेजहरू) प्राथमिकता दिर्ने&nbsp; ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अधिकारीहरूको लागि यात्राको व्यवस्था वव्वोस्थित गर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">गोपनीय कागजातहरूलाई सँधै सुचारु बनाउर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">सूचना व्यवस्थित र सजिलै पहुँचयोग्य सुनिश्चित गर्न इलेक्ट्रोनिक र पेपर रेकर्डहरू राख्नर्ने ।</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">शोध संचालन गर्ने र नियुक्तिको रूपमा प्रस्तुतीकरणहरू वा रिपोर्टहरू तयार पार्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">नेपाल सरकार बाट मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट व्यवस्थापन वा&nbsp;अन्य सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रहरूमा&nbsp;+2&nbsp; वा प्रमाणिकरण प्राप्त गरेको हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">Secretary to GM वा सो सरहको श्रेत्रमा कम्तिमा १ वर्ष को&nbsp; अनुभवभयको हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अङ्ग्रेजी र नेपाली दुवै राम्रो लेखन र बोलन साक्ने हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">कम्प्युटरमा MsWord, Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(126, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n<div><strong>जडीबूटी प्रोडक्शंस र प्रोसेसिंग कम्पनी लिमिटेड </strong><br />\r\n<strong>जडीबूटी , कोटेश्वर , काठमाडौं </strong>\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:312px\"><strong>कार्य विवरण फारम</strong> &nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:311px\"><strong>स्तर:</strong> ५</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:312px\"><strong>१.पदको नाम -</strong> व्यवस्थापक / लेखा<br />\r\n			<strong>२.तलब(मासिक) -&nbsp;</strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>३.काम गर्ने समय -&nbsp;</strong>कम्पनीको नियमानुसार<br />\r\n			<strong>४.कार्य क्षेत्र&nbsp; -</strong> ( तारहरा-बेलबारी ) / टिकापुर / काठमाडौं<br />\r\n			<strong>५.जवाफदेहिता</strong> - महाप्रबन्धक समक्ष</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:left; width:311px\"><strong>शाखा -&nbsp;</strong>खेती / प्रशोधन / विनिर्माण</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:623px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<strong>कामको जिम्मेवारी र जिम्मेवारीहरू</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;भौचर भर्न र लेखा सोफटवेरमा लेखा हिसाब&nbsp;&nbsp; राख्नन साहायता गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रप्त बिलहरुको भुक्तानि&nbsp; गार्न साहायता गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">सबै कर्मचारी हरु को मासिक तलब र खर्च तिर्न र तलब को रेकर्ड राख्न साहायता गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अग्रिमरूपमा भुक्तानी भयको लेखाको नियमित खाता विवरण जाँच गर्न साहायता गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">लेखांकन प्रणाली या सफ्टवेयर संग सबै व्यावसायिक एकाइहरुमा सबै लेखांकन प्रक्रिया या प्रक्रिया भय नभयको सुनिचित गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">साझेदारहरूको लागि कोष स्थानान्तरण ड्राफ्टको सन्दर्भमा बैंकसँग सम्झौता गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रोजेक्टको खातामा पठाइएको र प्राप्त सामग्रीको लागत र चार्जको चे्कजाच गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रमुख कार्यलय र परियोजना खाताहरू बीचको खाता जाँच र समर्थन गर्न र नियमित भ्रमण गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">निर्देशन अनुसार साझेदारहरूको खाता बुकिङ प्रणाली सुनिश्चित गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">प्रमुख कार्यलय र प्रोजेक्ट रेकर्ड बीचको लेखा&nbsp; सूची रेकर्ड&nbsp; ठिक गर्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">लेखा चे्कजाच को लागि पर्याप्त समर्थन कागजातहरूको लागि समितिहरू / कर्मचारीहरू (को लागी जिम्मेवार व्यक्तिहरू, आधिकारिक टिकट, कर कटौती, सभाहरूबाट अनुमोदन अद्यावधिक अनुमोदन गरी लेखा परीक्षा प्रश्नहरू अपडेट गर्ने ।</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अन्य विभाग द्वारा अनुदेशको रूपमा अन्य वित्तीय कार्यलाई सहयोग गर्ने</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>&nbsp;शैक्षिक योग्यता र अनुभब</strong></div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">नेपाल सरकार बाट मान्यता प्राप्त शिक्षण संस्थाबाट व्यवस्थापन वा अन्य सम्बन्धित क्षेत्रहरूमा न्यूनतम स्नातक डिग्री प्राप्त गरेको</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">लेखा शाहायक वा सो सरहको श्रेत्रमा खाता अधिकारी वा समान भूमिकाको रूपमा सिद्ध अनुभवको न्यूनतम 2 वर्ष को&nbsp; अनुभवभयको</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">अङ्ग्रेजी र नेपाली दुवै राम्रो लेखन र बोलन साक्ने</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:left\">बम कम्प्युटरमा MsWord,Ms Excel तथा Powerpoint सम्बन्धी ज्ञान भएको हुनु पर्ने&nbsp;</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(148, '<h1 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:16px\"><span style=\"color:#FF0000\">Candidates who had already applied for the job position during the first advertisement need not have to re-apply.</span></span><br />\r\nTERMS OF REFERENCE</strong>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:justify; width:228px\"><strong>Position Title</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:justify; width:18px\"><strong>:</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:justify; width:396px\">Field Supervisor</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:65px; text-align:justify; width:228px\"><strong>Position Objective</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:65px; text-align:justify; width:18px\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>:</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:65px; text-align:justify; width:396px\">Technical and supervision support for construction of 22 school construction sites in Ramechhap and Sindhuli</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:justify; width:228px\"><strong>Position Duration</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:justify; width:18px\"><strong>:</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:30px; text-align:justify; width:396px\">12 Months renewable</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>General Background: </strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nAfter their schools have been destroyed or damaged by the 2015 earthquakes, many Nepali children had to drop out of school or to attend classes in unfavourable conditions, either outside or in temporary classrooms with little protection from the elements. Others have had to enrol further away from home, burdening their families with boarding or transportation&nbsp;costs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn spite of significant efforts to rebuild educational facilities, there are still major gaps in permanent school reconstruction, leaving children from the most underserved Districts behind. According to the Nepal Reconstruction Authority (NRA), Central-Level Project Implementation Unit of the Nepalese Ministry of Education (MoE-CLPIU), over 9,000 school buildings were affected and 7553 were damaged across the country due to devastating 2015 earthquake in Nepal. In total, 21,169 classrooms completely collapsed, 12,522 classrooms were severely damaged and 15,990 classrooms were damaged partially. As of December 2018, reconstruction of only 4172 schools has been achieved or ongoing.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRealizing the contextual need in the education sector, the reconstruction of new 142 class rooms in 24 new school buildings is proposed with the aim to reach 5520 beneficiaries in remote earthquake-affected Districts of Nepal.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>The Project Scope</strong><br />\r\nThe scope of the construction works in each school is limited to;<br />\r\n1. Construction of a new classroom building of either 4, 6 or 8 classrooms.<br />\r\n2. Construction of a new toilet block<br />\r\n3. Securing the boundary of the school with a chain link fence and gate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWithin this main scope, the requirement to address land stabilization (retaining walls), solar provision for lighting and small power, minor external works around the new proposed buildings have been included.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWe are to construct these new schools in 4 Districts in Nepal as follows;<br />\r\n1. Ramechaap district - 13 schools<br />\r\n2. Sindhuli district - 9 schools<br />\r\n3. Kathmandu district - 1 special needs school<br />\r\n4. Bhaktapur district - 1 special needs school<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nFor each school site in Sindhuli and Ramechhap, the project shall be requiring a Field Supervisor to be stationed on site throughout the construction period. This means a total of 22 Field Supervisors will be required.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Roles, Deliverables &amp; Expected Outputs</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:25px; text-align:justify; width:180px\"><strong>Description of Role</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:25px; text-align:justify; width:264px\"><strong>Deliverable</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:25px; text-align:justify; width:198px\"><strong>Expected Output</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90px; text-align:justify; width:180px\">Work under the direct supervision and guidance of Associate District Engineers responsible for the work site.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Work as on-site representative of the implementing agency (UNOPS) and supervises the work being performed by contractor.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Responsible for observing the work being performed and reporting any deviations from plan and specification.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Bring to the attention of the Associate District Engineer any unforeseen field conditions in time for remedial measures to be taken without creating delays in work or changes in existing work to correct a problem.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			The field supervisor is the on-site eyes and ears of the employer and should be capable of evaluating field problems and submitting competent recommendations to his supervisor.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Be conversant with mobile construction mobile tablet-based monitoring applications and use the application for monitoring of houses being constructed from the start to completion. Collect collaborative pictures through each phase of house construction.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Liaise and coordinate with SMC, local government bodies/DLPIU engineers, community leaders and other relevant stakeholders on technical issues if required.</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90px; text-align:justify; width:264px\">Shall be present on the construction site at all working hours ensuring that contractor carries out construction works as per plan, drawings, specifications and contract documentation.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Support in preparing the daily site report, weekly reports and monthly progress reports as instructed by the Associate District Engineer.<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Ensure safeguards requirements for HSSE and Gender are adequately addressed in the construction sites.</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:90px; text-align:justify; width:198px\">Provide daily and weekly reports through the tablet software back to the Associate District Engineers<br />\r\n			&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Material delivery and labour personnel details quality check reports completed on time and issues reported back up to the ADE.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Qualification, Work Experience, Language &amp; other Mandatory Requirements</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Bachelor&#39;s Degree in civil engineering with minimum 1 year of relevant experience in the building construction field.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Civil diploma with minimum 2 years of relevant experience.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Working knowledge in Microsoft Office and internet. Ability to maintain various types of documentation in English is required.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Certificate from Nepal Engineering Council for engineering degree holders.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Working knowledge of English and fluency in Nepali is mandatory.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fair knowledge in operating smart phone and sharing the project informations such as project pictures, georeferences etc.. via mobile messaging Apps is mandatary.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Professional knowledge of earthquake resistant design and construction of buildings will be an advantage.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Good communication, rapport building, planning and reporting skills will be an advantage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;<strong>Gross salary package: NPR 50,000.00</strong></div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(153, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px\"><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION OF DEPUTY DIRECTOR</strong></span></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:14px\">SUMMARY OF POSITION</span></strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:13px\">To undertake overall responsibility for the management of NEWAH with the Director retaining key responsibilities. Kathmandu based with frequent field visits for overall support, monitoring and evaluation.</span></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>LINE MANAGER</u></strong></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The Deputy Director reports to the Director.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><em><u>Key Responsibilities:</u></em></strong>&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage and lead the senior management team of the organization in conducting meetings, recording minutes and achieving the organization&rsquo;s objectives.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Oversee the performance, guide and support the HQ Managers in reviewing policies, procedures and guidelines for submission to the Director and the donor.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Monitor and support the provincial and central level program and activities of the organization in coordination with the concerned managers.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Undertake the roles and responsibilities of the Admin Manager from April 2020.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Conduct regular monthly meetings among managers at HQ and a coordination meeting involving provincial managers at least once a quarter or earlier whenever required.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist the Fund-Raising department with required information in preparing the funding proposals for the organization.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain a cordial relationship with donors and all other stakeholders and join weekly calls with charity: water along with the program manager.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Take responsibility and manage the day to day management of HQ.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Represent the organization at all National forums.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Assist the Director in fulfilling the tasks as decided by the Executive Committee/General Assembly/Audit Committee and any other committees formed by the AGM/EC.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Keep the Director informed on progress, issues and events.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Seek advice &amp; support from the Director when needed.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Any other specific tasks of the organization as assigned by the Director.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;<strong><em><u>Person specifications: </u></em></strong></span></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Master&rsquo;s Degree with at least 8 years&rsquo; experience in development related field at management level. Those with experiences in WASH will be an added benefit</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Applicant should not be above 40 years of age</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fluent in Nepali and English both in speaking and writing</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer skills in Microsoft Word, Excel and Power Point</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with gender sensitivity</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to lead a team of senior member of staff</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to work under pressure and deadlines</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Possesses a valid driving license for a car or motorbike&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong><u>Salary &amp; Benefits</u></strong></span></em></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Salary scale per Month NRS 75,000.00</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Dearness Allowance per month NRS 34,500.00</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">PF, Gratuity &amp; other benefits as per the rules of the organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Note: </strong><strong>Candidates must submit their CV along with the name &amp; contact detail of two references.</strong></span></div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(115, 'Rolling Plans Private Limited (RPPL) is a specialized service outsourcing firm having intensity of its services in various functions of human resource management and development (HRM/D), research and innovation, and institutional development since 2004. Our vision is to be an internationally acclaimed service provider in HR solutions and research and innovation. For this, we have a mission to support organizations by providing them with strategic as well as operational solutions, and at the same time, we help organizations maintain highest level of socio-ethical standards. For more info, please check our website <a href=\"http://www.rollingplans.com.np\">www.rollingplans.com.np</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nRPPL entered the contract with UNOPS for Human Resource services for implementation of various project of UNOPs in different districts of Nepal.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<strong>Job purpose</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;The Officer-HR &amp; Admin is responsible for providing support in the various human resources functions, which include recruitment, staffing, training and development, performance, monitoring, payroll management, leave management and employee counseling. Maintain recruitment and selection policies, procedures and templates to ensure effective, fair and consistent management of staffs throughout the project duration and ensure that the staffs are oriented about job to perform, up-to-date and aligned to RPPL standard with compliance to legislation. He/she should play the role in the project as one of focal person for the employees and perform tasks such as communication, system record-keeping, Reporting, Recruiting, Training and assisting in the establishment project documentation.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe administration officer has to assist the project coordinator in developing and managing documentation, according to the need. He/she should also keep abreast of developments in issues, methodologies and technologies.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Duties and responsibilities</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;The primary job duties and responsibilities:<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coordinate in staff recruitment and selection process in order to ensure that organized and comprehensive procedure is used to hire staffs.</li>\r\n	<li>Ensure and organize receipt of all applications for further screening processes.</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate with the IT Consultant to maintain track record of the recruitment process.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide and facilitate in logistic support during pre and post-recruitment &amp; selection process.</li>\r\n	<li>Report to the Project Coordinator and be responsible for the daily functions such as documentations, record keeping, and maintaining daily work schedule for the team members during assignment.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide basic counseling to staffs in performance related obstacles.</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate in organizing staff orientation sessions, workshops and activities.</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor scheduled absences such as holidays or travel and coordinate with Program Coordinator to ensure the staff absence has been adequately covered off to ensure continuity of services.</li>\r\n	<li>Recording and handling of grievances.</li>\r\n	<li>Constant communication with the field supervisor and RPPL team.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide advice and assistance to supervisors and team members on staff recruitment and support on replacement.</li>\r\n	<li>Facilitate in issuance of employment contracts and renewal of contracts.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide support for the program/projects including assisting with administration of project work appropriate and when agreed.</li>\r\n	<li>Minute taking for Board, team meetings and other meetings as required.</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare Project report as per the requirement of the project.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintain the general filling system, general database and archive.</li>\r\n	<li>Direct and control the processing and fulfillment of client requirement.</li>\r\n	<li>Liaise and work closely with departments / departmental head, increasingly in a consultancy role to understand all necessary aspects and needs of HR services development, objectives, purpose and achievements for the project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Competencies</strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Communication</strong>:&nbsp; Speaks and writes clearly and effectively; listens to others, correctly interprets messages from others and responds appropriately; asks questions to clarify, and exhibits interest in having two-way communication; tailors&rsquo; language, tone, style and format to match audience; demonstrates openness in sharing information and keeping people informed.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Teamwork: </strong>Works collaboratively with colleagues to achieve organizational goals. Solicits input by genuinely valuing others&rsquo; ideas and expertise; is willing to learn from others. Places team agenda before personal agenda. Supports and acts in accordance with final group decision, even when such decisions may not entirely reflect own position. Shares credit for team accomplishments and accepts joint responsibility for team shortcomings.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;<strong>Planning &amp; Organizing: </strong>Develops clear goals that are consistent with agreed strategies. Identifies priority activities and assignments; adjusts priorities as required. Allocates appropriate amount of time and resources for completing work. Foresees risks and allows for contingencies when planning. Monitors and adjusts plans and actions as necessary. Uses time efficiently.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Client Orientation</strong>: Considers all those to whom services are provided to be &ldquo;clients&rdquo; and seeks to see things from clients&rsquo; point of view; establishes and maintains productive partnerships with clients by gaining their trust and respect; identifies clients&rsquo; needs and matches them to appropriate solutions; monitors ongoing developments inside and outside the clients&rsquo; environment to keep informed and anticipate problems; keeps clients informed of progress or setbacks in projects; meets timeline for delivery of products or services to client.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Technological Awareness</strong>: Keeps abreast of available technology; understands applicability and limitation of technology to the work of the office; actively seeks to apply technology to appropriate tasks; shows willingness to learn new technology.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Qualifications</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;Qualifications include:&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Master&rsquo;s degree in management or social sciences or related field OR Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in management or social sciences or related studies relevant to the assignment.</li>\r\n	<li>At least one year of professional experience, preferably in human resource management for Master&rsquo;s degree and three years of professional experience, in human resource management for Bachelor&rsquo;s degree.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>High degree of proficiency in office procedures and use of computers including Microsoft Word and Excel programs.</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to work independently and make decisions in accordance with established policies and regulations.</li>\r\n	<li>Proven ability to maintain confidential information with good health, high moral character and good attendance record.</li>\r\n	<li>Should be hardworking, respectful and tactful with all stakeholders, superiors and peers.</li>\r\n	<li>Should be detail oriented, organized and able to meet tight deadlines.</li>\r\n	<li>Fluency in Nepali and English language.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Working conditions</strong>&nbsp;<br />\r\nHR &amp; Admin work in office environment from Sunday- Friday (9:30am- 5:30pm) with frequent requirement to work beyond office hours and traveling to project location based upon company&rsquo;s requirements and deadlines.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Direct reports</strong><br />\r\nProject Coordinator<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(154, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>NEPAL WATER FOR HEALTH</strong></span></div>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Nepal Water for Health</span></h5>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><u>Job Description for Finance Manager</u></span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;</span>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u>Summary of the position</u></strong><br />\r\nResponsible for overall financial management of NEWAH. Responsible for releasing funds to provincial offices, obtaining financial reports, spot checking, support to inventory management, consolidating all financial statement, quarterly reconciliation for NEWAH and report to the management and all funding partners as required.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>Line Manager</strong></u><br />\r\nReports to the Director<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible for overall financial related matter of the organization.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Overall budget sheet formatting, planning and compiling.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop and review financial rules and regulation for approval.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage monthly transfer of amount to provincial offices</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Checking financial reports and instruct to the concerned as required.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Linkage and coordination between NEWAH and funding partner in all financial matters.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible to deal and provide all required information to internal, external and all donor related audits and to SWC on time upon demand.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare final accounts of the year-end and present to the management and Board.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review the financial system and make recommendation to the director and board.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Attend meeting and hold discussion on financial matters as invited by the Board and the Audit Committee.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Coordinate and mange to inform all staff on any changes in financial rules and regulation and provide training to financial staff wherever required.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Advise the Director and Managers on financial management aspect.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Responsible for management response of Internal, External and Donor Audits&rsquo; queries and ensure the implementation of recommendations through the development of action plan.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare quarterly financial management report and present to the SMT and Treasurer.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Prepare annual financial report for the Treasurer to present in the General Assembly.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure the proper financial system in place at all provincial offices and headquarter.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure the safety of all financial documents as per financial policy.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Identify gaps and capacity needs of finance staffs and provide required training &amp; support.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Any other finance related specific tasks of the organization as assigned by the line manager.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><u><strong>Working Condition</strong></u><br />\r\nHeadquarter based with at least quarterly visits to provincial offices and to the project sites.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<u><strong>Person&rsquo;s specification&nbsp;</strong></u></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">S/he should be Master degree in management stream with five years of work experience or CA/ACCA with two years of experience in similar works.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Computer Knowledge - Word, Excel, Access and PowerPoint.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Excellent communication skill in both English and Nepali.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Able to supervise a team of finance staff and their function.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Analytical skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<strong><u>Salary &amp; Benefits</u></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Salary scale per Month NRS 62,000.00</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Dearness Allowance per month NRS 25,630.00</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">PF, Gratuity &amp; other benefits as per the rules of the organization.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Note: </strong>Candidates must submit their CV along with the name &amp; contact detail of two references.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>To apply: www.rollingnexus.com/NEWAH</strong></div>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(151, '<strong>Vacancy Announcement:</strong><br />\r\nDesignation: Network Administrator<br />\r\nNo. of vacancy: 1<br />\r\nWork location: Bijulibazar, Kathmandu<br />\r\nSalary: Negotiable<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Requirement:</u></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Must be a graduate in computer engineering or relevant degree.</li>\r\n	<li>Multi-tasking, good attitude, punctual and dedicated in work.</li>\r\n	<li>Must be flexible with working hours.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Job Description:</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Should be able to install and configure computer networks and systems</li>\r\n	<li>Should be able to identify and solve any problems that arise with computer networks and systems</li>\r\n	<li>Must consult with clients to specify system requirements and design solutions</li>\r\n	<li>Ability to perform budgeting for equipment and assembly costs.</li>\r\n	<li>Must be able to assemble new systems.</li>\r\n	<li>Should maintain existing software and hardware and keep them updated.</li>\r\n	<li>Must monitor computer networks and systems to identify how performance can be improved</li>\r\n	<li>Should work with IT support personnel and report to the supervisor on a daily basis.</li>\r\n	<li>Must provide network administration and support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', ''),
(14, '<strong><u>Main Duties and Responsibilities</u></strong><br />\r\nTo handle calls from new and existing customers regarding a variety of requests.<br />\r\nTo utilize their knowledge of products or services in order to cater the customer queries.<br />\r\nTo display great customer service skills.<br />\r\nTo address issues of the customer and provide support.<br />\r\nTo offer information, as and when required.<br />\r\nTo be responsible for improving customer retention through programs and service provided to the customer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong><u>Job Specifications</u></strong><br />\r\n+2 passed<br />\r\nGood communication skills in both English &amp; Nepali.<br />\r\nAvailable to work in shifts and flexible in different working timings.<br />\r\nAble to perform multitasking.<br />\r\nHaving sound health to work in call center environment.<br />\r\nBasic computer skills.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong><u>Recruitment &amp; Selection Process</u></strong><br />\r\n1. Candidate CV review &amp; screening of profile for computer test.<br />\r\n2. Telephonic Interview.<br />\r\n3. Computer Test.<br />\r\n4. Interview Session.<br />\r\n5. Orientation Program.<br />\r\n6. Training Program for 2-3 weeks (A test will be conducted for the final selection by trainer).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNo prior experience required. Fresher&rsquo;s can apply.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', '', '');
INSERT INTO `job_requirements` (`jobs_id`, `description`, `specification`, `education_description`, `specific_requirement`, `specific_instruction`) VALUES
(110, '<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:gill sans mt,sans-serif\">Our Vision:</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:gill sans mt,sans-serif\"> &ldquo; Our commitment to all children, to have opportunity for quality education&rdquo;</span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Introduction: </strong><br />\r\nRural Education and Environment Development Centre (REED) &ndash;Nepal was established in 2000 as an Non-Governmental organization registered in District Administration Office, Kathmandu and affiliated with Social Welfare Council (SWC). REED Nepal was initiated by the first Everest climbers who witnessed that children in the Himalayan region has been backward to reach of basic level of education and felt the need to assist Nepal Government&rsquo;s attempts for the improvement of overall standard of School Education in the Himalayan regions. REED&rsquo;s activities focus on imparting Quality Education through Teachers&rsquo; training, Child Protection Program, Environment and climate change, Gender and social inclusion, and Learning &amp; life skills using holistic approaches. Since then, REED Nepal has been conducting its various educational programs to enhance the quality teaching and learning environment both for teachers and students in 10 districts of Nepal with the support of national and international donors.</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>Key Position Information </strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>Job Title</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>Programme Director (PD)</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>Position Location</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">70% Kathmandu and 30% Fields/Projects</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>Position Reports To</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">Chief Executive Officer (CEO)</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>No. Direct Report:</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">06</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:12px; text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><strong>Decision&nbsp;Making Authority</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"height:12px; text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">With REED policy and procedure.</div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n			<div><strong>Key Objectives of the Position </strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:33px\">\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Major Responsibilities:</div>\r\n\r\n			<ul>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Manage and lead the program team and ensure quality delivery of all the&nbsp; REED programs</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead and manage by motivating program staff to remain optimistic even when faced with challenges and encouraging good performance and values</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with CEO develop and implement staff professional development plan of program team and fill in the gaps to support the staff as per the need</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">With&nbsp; the CEO and board lead efforts&nbsp; to write proposals and secure long &ndash;term funding for organisation</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure excellent coordination and communication between the funding partners and REED</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Sustain an effective level of communication, co-ordination and liaison with local, national and international partners, Ministry of Education and stakeholders</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Create programs and challenges that are as effective and efficient as possible</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ensure that all implemented activities are relevant to the mission and vision of the organization</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">In coordination with CEO, refine the current HR system to motivate the employees and ensure the culture of &#39;team work&#39;</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Organize, plan and carry out planned activities effectively, using participatory methods with all stakeholders, particularly for children, and raise any issues related to plans.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Develop communication and coordination strategies with Donor organizations and take a lead in implementing the strategy in coordination with program team</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Co-ordinate and work with national and international training institutions related to teacher training according to the government policy.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Refine the existing Monitoring and Evaluation system of programs to ensure the quality delivery and long-term sustainability of programs</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Review cash and budget forecasts regularly and ensure through the program and finance team that the variance between forecast and the spending is kept at the minimal.&nbsp; - Ensure that there is close coordination between finance and the program team on reconciling spending with ongoing program implementation, thus ensuring that reports to Donors are accurate and sent in a timely manner.</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Continuously improve program delivery and manage risks with the development of an effective monitoring and evaluation of REED Nepal&rsquo;s programs and performance together with accurate analysis and quality reporting to donors and other stakeholders</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Contribute to periodic performance management activities, particularly in the appraisal of performance against job descriptions and work ethics</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Maintain access to, and familiarity with, relevant donors policies, guidelines and regulations</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Lead the project team in developing project strategies, implementing project, report writing and influencing policies related to:</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strengthening capacities of district program team to achieve program related objectives</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Enhancing technical and community level work of the team</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strengthening and capacitating the current team in project related objectives</li>\r\n				<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Developing and disseminating key learning documents and collaborate amongst likeminded organizations to influence policy makers and other stakeholders</li>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Person Specification</strong></div>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n				<tbody>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td>\r\n						<ul>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Minimum Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree, Master&rsquo;s Degree (preferred) in Education /Sociology/ Management or other relevant field.</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Master&rsquo;s Degree with minimum of 5 years working experience or Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree with Minimum of 7 years working experience at the management level (preferably in I/NGO sector).&nbsp;</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong operational management ability: a clear focus on results &ndash; sets goals, plans and prioritizes effectively, monitors quality and progress of work against plans</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Should have prior proven record of <em>long-term</em> <em>program development</em> in education</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Experience in <em>education Strategy Development and Implementation</em> will be an added value to the position</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong verbal and written communication skills in English</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Strong budgeting and financial management</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">A sound understanding of challenges in the sector of education with focus in government school system&nbsp;</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to liaise and conduct business with senior levels of government and I/NGOs.</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Exceptional analysis and reporting skills</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability in developing excellent internal and external communication tools</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Demonstrated ability to transfer knowledge through informal and formal trainings</li>\r\n							<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Ability to travel frequently to districts where REED operates. The job requires at least 30% of time travelling to the fields/projects</li>\r\n						</ul>\r\n						</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n					<tr>\r\n						<td style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n					</tr>\r\n				</tbody>\r\n			</table>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.'),
(152, '<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>TERMS OF REFERENCE &ndash; Community Mobilizer</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n<strong>Position title</strong>:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Community Mobilizer<br />\r\n<strong>Position Duration</strong>:&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1 month to 6 months renewable&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Job Description</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Will reach out to the population to which they are assigned to in order to promote each projects&rsquo; objectives.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Minimum Requirements</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least 2 years of experience in working closely with communities for 10+2 (intermediate)</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">At least 1 year of experience in working closely with communities for Bachelor degree.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Working knowledge in Microsoft Office 2010 and internet. Ability to maintain various types of documentation in English is required.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Working knowledge of English and fluency in Nepali is mandatory.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Planning and reporting; identification of field level issues</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Meeting/ Training management and facilitation skills.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Liaison and communications; awareness raising.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align:justify\">Fair knowledge in operating smart phone and sharing the project information such as project pictures, georeferenced etc. via mobile messaging Apps is mandatory.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '<span style=\"color:#0033cc\"><strong>&ldquo;Protocols for the confidentiality&rdquo;</strong></span> is designed to collect and maintain identifiable information about applicants. Data will be collected anonymously by the specified person and will be removed and destroyed as soon as possible by the completion of this specific assignment. No access to any other organizations/ person and shall be based on a &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; and &quot;minimum necessary&quot; standard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"color:#FF0000\"><strong>CONFIDENTIALITY PROTOCOL&mdash; PROTECTION OF INFORMATION OF APPLICANTS</strong></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nInformation, applications and documents that are deemed to be of a highly sensitive nature or to be inadequately protected by the CONFI&not;DENTIAL classification shall be classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL and access to them shall be restricted solely to persons with a specific need for specific assignment only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe staffs of the Rolling Plans including client institution shall establish a control and tracking system for documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL, including the maintenance of control logs. Documents classified as STRICTLY CONFIDENTIAL shall be (i) maintained by only specific staff with written commitment; (ii) kept under security key or given equivalent protection when not in use; and (iii) in the case of physical documents, transmitted by an inner envelope indicating the classification marking and an outer envelope indicating no classification, or, in the case of documents in electronic form, transmitted by encrypted or password-secured system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor purposes of this protocol, the following individuals are deemed to have a specific need to know: (i) the executive consultant; (ii) the project manager/recruitment and selection consultant; (iii) the international consultant of Rolling Plans and; (v) the respective designated representatives of Government of Nepal.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nConfidentiality pertains to the treatment of information that an individual has disclosed in any documents/files of trust and with the expectation that it will not be divulged to others/ process without permission in ways that are inconsistent with the understanding of the original disclosure. Rolling Plans assure that the information shall be used for specific purpose published in this system and service only.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen it is necessary to collect and maintain identifiable data, Rolling Plans will ensure that the protocol includes the necessary safeguards to maintain confidentiality of identifiable data and data security appropriate to the degree of risk from disclosure.');
